var listOfSnippets = [{PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EB779F4A-62DF-4184-8491-BE9D5C6E34B2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='2345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='2345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EB779F4A-62DF-4184-8491-BE9D5C6E34B2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:113111F5-2E98-4C4C-8EA6-8EA86E3DA81E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' opt-key='opt-N70787'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p> No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party<em opt-key='opt-D733AC17'>, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any securities exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem52b8262f-83f4-481e-a3e0-95e8d8a98954'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This is a short form announcements provision. For a longer form see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>This clause is drafted on the basis that:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>it binds all of the parties to the Agreement</p></div></li><li><div><p>the general prohibition on announcements and other public disclosures relates to the existence of the contract itself and any of the matters contained in it</p></div></li><li><div><p>the parties will remain bound for the duration of the Agreement (if the clause is intended to survive termination of the agreement, this may be stated in the clause itself or elsewhere in the Agreement, eg in the termination or survival clause)</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made with the prior written consent of the other party, with no express process being set out to obtain such consent, although it must not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made as required by law, a court or any other authority, without any prior written consent from the other party or any consultation with them being required.</p></div><div><p>The announcements clause normally forms part of the main agreement relating to a transaction or arrangement and, as such, will take effect on the signing of the agreement. Prior to signing, any announcement relating to the proposed transaction or arrangement will normally be restricted by the terms of a confidentiality agreement entered into between the parties. The terms of such a confidentiality agreement should be considered in drafting an announcements clause; it would be usual for the announcements clause (along with any confidentiality clause) to replace this initial confidentiality agreement.</p></div><div><p>It is necessary to consider an announcements clause in an agreement in conjunction with any confidentiality clause, to ensure that the two work effectively together</p></div></li></ul></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:113111F5-2E98-4C4C-8EA6-8EA86E3DA81E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' opt-key='opt-N69736'><p class='main_heading'><lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party></p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1494506087-33817162'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Guarantor</p><div><p>This guarantee clause is suitable for use where the Seller requires some security that the Buyer will observe its obligations in the Agreement. The guarantee clause provides that if the Buyer defaults the guarantor will perform those obligations (and this will include the obligation to pay the purchase price to the Seller). The guarantor also indemnifies the Seller against any losses or liability incurred because of the Buyer&#8217;s default. Delete if no guarantor is being provided.</p></div></div></lnb-prec:title><div><p>In consideration of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> entering into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> at the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>'s request the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> agrees with the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> as a primary obligation as follows:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem6ee7430d-2436-4cbd-a424-5998ea800fc6'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> must perform and observe all of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem10d54eae-693d-4a1f-b86a-88d839de7f41'><div><p>if the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> defaults in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will perform them;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItembb7685cb-daff-41b1-b57c-8b7c6326d0f8'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will indemnify the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> against all claims, demands, damages, losses, liability, costs, fees and expenses sustained by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> by reason of, or arising in any way directly or indirectly out of, the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e'><div><p>if this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> has been disclaimed following the insolvency of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may serve notice in writing on the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> (the &#8216;<b>Guarantor Notice</b>&#8217;) requiring the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> in accordance with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> with the following modifications:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemd421ca62-727b-49e6-9240-91993f13ced3'><div><p>all obligations of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be deemed to have been entered into by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> as though it were named as <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in place of the party defined as the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem816b7794-9d86-4cb3-84fa-81079304136a'><div><p>if a notice to complete served by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> on the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> has expired at the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b> the <b>Completion Date</b> shall be <em type='number'>5</em> working days after the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem545c300a-9165-4d26-9d02-5ef27f83db51'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> is to pay:</p></div><div number-type='loweralpha'><div id='ukContentItemaacf6481-adc4-4d44-9044-072c062496b1'><div><p><b>Interest</b> on the balance of the <b>Price</b> from the contractual <b>Completion Date</b> until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdbf94e06-289b-4a0a-bce1-84e84f47f6ec'><div><p>all money expended by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in consequence of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default from the date of expenditure until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days;</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7203eb7e-1bf8-472d-bd14-67e4f0494902'><div><p>for the avoidance of doubt no further deposit shall be payable by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem64b572ca-3e0c-48bf-9c51-f30482836137'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Disclaimer</p><div><p>This gives the Seller the ability to require the Guarantor to take a transfer of the Property in the event that the Agreement is disclaimed. See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM3_149095'>The process of disclaimer by a liquidator or trustee in bankruptcy under sections 178 or 315 of the Insolvency Act 1986</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1'><div><p>the liability of the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> shall not be affected reduced or extinguished by:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb2b70c21-0e1a-4ca0-a124-6ad25dd6e5f4'><div><p>any time or indulgence granted by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> to the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemfb07de4a-86ee-446c-b76f-346d6ca05a86'><div><p>any neglect or forbearance of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in enforcing its rights under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemaa2a78f2-df61-4f7b-8af6-482506233419'><div><p>any variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> agreed between the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>; or</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89'><div><p>the fact that any other person or entity comprising the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> or intended to comprise the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> has not executed this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or is not bound by the guarantee in clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>;</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem94e8ddef-544f-4d85-bd54-629d58779cbf'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89' type='clause'/>&#8212;Signatories</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Harvey v Dunbar Assets [2013] All ER (D) 400 (Jul)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>In <em class='it'>Harvey</em> the court decided a bank guarantee was subject to a condition that it would be signed by all the other intended guarantors named in the deed, and so liability as a &#8216;Guarantor&#8217; was only imposed on an individual signatory to the document in circumstances where all the named individuals did indeed sign the guarantee. This meant the individual being sued was never on the hook as guarantor because one of the intended guarantors had not signed the document (his signature had been forged). The guarantee was a single composite document, which sought to impose joint and several liability on four individuals together defined as &#8216;the Guarantor&#8217; and envisaged it would be signed by all four individuals. There was nothing in the wording excluding the result that all intended guarantors had to sign for an individual guarantor to be liable. It is assumed that the contract into which this clause is inserted provides for joint and several liability where obligations are owed by more than one party. This sub-clause is an attempt to avoid the problem in <em class='it'>Harvey</em> as, whilst the case relates to a bank guarantee it could, of course, be of wider application in the context of guarantees. It has not been tested in court.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf2e07994-da50-4aed-8b93-04436780dc3b'><div><p>anything else by which apart from clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1' type='clause'/> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> would be released other than a release under seal.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:113111F5-2E98-4C4C-8EA6-8EA86E3DA81E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' opt-key='opt-N68621'><p class='main_heading'>Capital allowances</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d'><div><p>In clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/> the following definitions apply:</p></div><div><lnb-prec:definition><b>CAA&#160;2001</b><div><p>Capital Allowances Act 2001;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Election</b><div><p>an election in respect of the <b>Fixtures</b> under section 198 of <b>CAA 2001</b> in the form annexed in <a id-ref='ukContentItem25240d33-51c6-42e8-97f8-42341d859179' type='schedule'/>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem7ffa5e9f-e1cc-4d3e-a8e7-2a787fd78282'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Election</p><div><p>For details of elections in real estate transactions, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Fixtures</b><div><p>means all plant and machinery which is installed or otherwise fixed in or to the <b>Property</b> so as to become (in law) part of the <b>Property</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem047859c8-e9af-4c86-a104-979d3ffe03cc'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Fixtures</p><div><p>Fixtures are plant or machinery installed or fixed so that they become, in law, part of a building or land. Examples include boilers, alarm systems and fitted kitchen units. There are special rules to determine whether a taxpayer is eligible to claim allowances for expenditure on a fixture. In order to claim allowances, the taxpayer must have an interest in the land or building of which the fixture is part. Further rules determine who may claim allowances where more than one person might have a claim, for instance where a person constructs a building, installs fixtures, then leases the building to another person for a capital sum that includes a payment for those fixtures. For new fixtures, the capital allowances claim is based on the actual expenditure. For more information see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>HMRC</b><div><p>means HM Revenue &amp; Customs;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Integral Features</b><div><p>means those Fixtures that are integral features for the purposes of section 33A of <b>CAA 2001</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4e35b866-138c-4854-b7bd-368945e25f2e'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Integral Features</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Capital Allowances Act 2001, s 33A</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>Integral features are a special category of plant and machinery. They are defined by statute and include electrical systems, cold water systems, space and water heating systems, air conditioning systems and lifts. Integral features represent an exception to the general rule that the definition of plant comes from case law. Statute specifically provides that integral features always qualify as plant (although they attract allowances at a lower rate). For more information, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_161955'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;integral features</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Non-integral Features</b><div><p>means those Fixtures that are not <b>Integral Features</b>;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Prior Right</b><div><p>has the meaning of prior right for the purposes of section 181(2) of <b>CAA 2001</b>.</p></div></lnb-prec:definition></div></div><div id='ukContentItem501d9779-1046-4b61-8f0d-f5f5c15d812a'><div><p>On <b>Completion</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall make the <b>Election</b> and shall each, within <em type='number'>insert number</em> working days of <b>Completion</b>, deliver an executed original <b>Election</b> to their respective tax inspector at <b>HMRC</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Integral Features</b> shall be &#163; <em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7d07a11-1d76-48f8-9e04-c9c4b70af874'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/>&#8212;Integral and Non-integral Features</p><div><p>Dividing the fixtures into integral and non-integral features is the absolute minimum HMRC that will accept. Depending upon which fixtures exist in the property, it may be necessary to subdivide them further and provide more details, such as 'electrical systems' or 'cold water systems'. In this case it may be better to delete clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650' type='clause'/> and to rely upon on a more detailed breakdown in the proforma election in <a id-ref='ukContentItem25240d33-51c6-42e8-97f8-42341d859179' type='schedule'/>. See Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_163854'>Election&#8212;capital allowances apportionment on sale of land&#8212;CAA 2001, s 198</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Non-integral Features</b> shall be <em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem319cec81-cb14-4d36-926e-ce949f567f03'><div><p>Each of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemc5df0ee3-08eb-4925-a8e3-33f52238585a'><div><p>provide all necessary information to each other and take all reasonable steps required to validly make the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem144eeb00-b956-485c-a895-427af7748ae9'><div><p>submit a copy of the <b>Election</b> to <b>HMRC</b> with their tax return for the first period affected by the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItema8e4c85b-ffc7-4568-ace2-7967853612d1'><div><p>take all reasonable steps to ensure that the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> are accepted by <b>HMRC</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdce79faf-9fbc-4a52-afbb-21adf5a4abdf'><div><p>reflect the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> in their respective tax computations and returns.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemacc4de87-96b3-4966-a239-c45bb9bfa360'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that no person has a <b>Prior Right</b> in relation to any of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemabc048f4-b70e-400c-bccd-ec560520ed1a'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that the total and individual figures in the Election are no greater than the amounts incurred by it in accordance with <b>CAA 2001</b> for the provision of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema8c561ba-3721-4e44-b601-b05c3c8c5a73'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/>&#8212;Capital allowances</p><div><p>It is important on any sale of property to consider the position in relation to capital allowances. In order to qualify for plant and machinery allowances, expenditure must be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>capital</p></div></li><li><div><p>on plant and machinery, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>wholly or partly for the purposes of a qualifying activity</p></div></li></ul><div><p>In addition, the person incurring the expenditure must own the plant and machinery as a result of that expenditure. See <a normcite='0OLU_123942'>Captial allowances&#8212;overview Document</a> for further information on the qualification criteria.</p></div><div><p>Properties often have substantial plant and machinery. This may be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>fixtures, and/or</p></div></li><li><div><p>integral features</p></div></li></ul><div><p>For information on the practicalities of capital allowance-related warranties and pre-contract enquiries on a property transfer, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185796'>Plant and machinery allowances on property acquisitions and disposals (including pre-contract enquiries)</a>.</p></div><div><p>The drafting in this clause is for use where the Seller has claimed allowances and the parties will enter into a section 198 election on Completion. For alternative drafting clauses where the Seller:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>has claimed allowances and the parties will apply to the First-tier Tax Tribunal for a just and reasonable allocation of allowances; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has claimed allowances but the information is not available on completion to enable a section 198 election to be entered into at completion; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has not claimed capital allowances, and was not entitled to do so; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>was entitled to claim capital allowances but has not done so</p></div></li></ul><div><p>see the drafting alternatives and notes in Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>.</p></div><div><p>The purpose of a section 198 election is to determine, for capital allowances purposes, the amount of the price for the property that should be attributed to fixtures on which the Seller has claimed allowances.</p><p>Depending upon the circumstances, it may be necessary to use more than one variation of the capital allowances clauses in this Precedent and also in Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>. For example, the property may contain fixtures on which the Seller has claimed allowances, but also fixtures on which the Seller was not entitled to claim allowances, such as cold water or electrical systems acquired before April 2008. In this situation it may be appropriate to use both the drafting in this Agreement as well as option 4 in Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>, with modifications to make clear which clause applies to which category of fixture.</p></div><div><p>For more information see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a> and <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34097125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:113111F5-2E98-4C4C-8EA6-8EA86E3DA81E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125'><p class='main_heading'>Joint and several liability</p><div><p>Where the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> is more than one person, the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may release or compromise the liability of any of those persons under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or grant time or other indulgence without affecting the liability of any other of them.</p></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34327125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:113111F5-2E98-4C4C-8EA6-8EA86E3DA81E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation <em opt-key='opt-N65620'>(including non-contractual disputes or claims)</em> shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1490085952-34560125'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause provides that the agreement and certain disputes and claims shall governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales, although a reference to another substantive law may be inserted instead.</p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217; and this wording can been made narrower if that is preferred. However, consideration should then be given as to the law that will govern any such disputes or claims that do not fall within the scope of the clause.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Regulation (EC) 864/2007</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The words &#8216;[(including non-contractual disputes or claims)]&#8217; may be included for the purpose of Rome II, which sets out the rules used to determine the governing law for non-contractual claims. However, parties pursuing a commercial activity can specify the governing law that will apply to their non-contractual obligations at any time before an event giving rise to damage occurs, save that such governing law cannot prevent the application of:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>any laws of the country in which all of the elements relevant to the situation are located when the event occurs (if it is not the country whose law has been chosen), if those laws cannot be derogated from by agreement, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>European Community law that cannot be derogated from by agreement, if all of the elements relevant to the situation are located in one or more EU member states when the event occurs and the law that has been chosen is not that of an EU member state</p></div></li></ul><div><p>In the absence of the phrase &#8216;[(including non-contractual disputes or claims)]&#8217; the wording of this clause may be wide enough in its scope to catch non-contractual claims relating to the agreement, its subject matter or formation. However, these words are a helpful addition to provide certainty to the parties.</p></div><div><p>If the intention of the parties is to restrict the governing law clause only to contractual claims, the wording of the clause should be amended to refer only to disputes or claims arising under the agreement, eg:</p></div><div><p>&#8216;This agreement and any dispute or claim arising under it shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of [England and Wales/insert details of alternative governing law].&#8217;</p></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34828125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:113111F5-2E98-4C4C-8EA6-8EA86E3DA81E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have exclusive jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation <em opt-key='opt-N65640'>(including non-contractual disputes or claims)</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem6a4733a3-5990-4eba-b100-19fe125ff259'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This clause provides that the courts of England and Wales shall have jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, the agreement. </p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217; and this wording can been made narrower if that is preferred. However, consideration should then be given as to the courts that will have jurisdiction to settle any such disputes or claims, which do not fall within the scope of the clause.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Fiona Trust v Privalov and others [2007] All ER (D) 233 (Oct) </a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>UBS AG v HSH Nordbank AG [2009] EWCA Civ 585, para 82</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The inclusion of the wording 'arise out of, or in connection with' and similar terms in a jurisdiction clause used to cause difficulties as to exactly what type of disputes were brought within its scope. The House of Lords has, in an arbitration case, upheld a wide interpretation of these words. This was on the assumption that the parties, as rational businessmen, were likely to have intended <em class='it'>any</em> dispute arising out of their relationship to be decided by the tribunal referred to in the relevant clause. The wording was held to be so wide as to cover claims arising before inception of the relevant agreement, such as misrepresentation. This wide interpretation has subsequently been followed in a number of litigation cases.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Fiona Trust v Privalov and others [2007] All ER (D) 233 (Oct)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The words &#8216;[(including non-contractual disputes or claims)]&#8217; may be included if the same wording is included in the agreement&#8217;s governing law clause for the purpose of Rome II. However, following the decision in the <em class='it'>Fiona Trust</em> case, such wording is not strictly necessary.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "::Home", id: "ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E9AFE023-D5CF-4502-9D3D-5453F9E03698'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' opt-key='opt-N70726'><p class='main_heading'>Capital allowances</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d'><div><p>In clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/> the following definitions apply:</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema8c561ba-3721-4e44-b601-b05c3c8c5a73'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/>&#8212;Capital allowances</p><div><p>It is important on any sale of property to consider the position in relation to capital allowances. In order to qualify for plant and machinery allowances, expenditure must be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>capital</p></div></li><li><div><p>on plant and machinery, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>wholly or partly for the purposes of a qualifying activity</p></div></li></ul><div><p>In addition, the person incurring the expenditure must own the plant and machinery as a result of that expenditure. See: <a normcite='0OLU_123942'>Capital allowances&#8212;overview</a> for further information on the qualification criteria.</p></div><div><p>Properties often have substantial plant and machinery. This may be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>fixtures, and/or</p></div></li><li><div><p>integral features</p></div></li></ul><div><p>For information on the practicalities of capital allowance-related warranties and pre-contract enquiries on a property transfer, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185796'>Plant and machinery allowances on property acquisitions and disposals (including pre-contract enquiries)</a>.</p></div><div><p>The drafting in this clause is for use where the Seller has claimed allowances and the parties will enter into a section 198 election on Completion. For alternative drafting clauses where the Seller:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>has claimed allowances and the parties will apply to the First-tier Tax Tribunal for a just and reasonable allocation of allowances; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has claimed allowances but the information is not available on completion to enable a section198 election to be entered into at completion; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has not claimed capital allowances, and was not entitled to do so; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>was entitled to claim capital allowances but has not done so</p></div></li></ul><div><p>see the drafting alternatives and notes in Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>.</p></div><div><p>The purpose of a section 198 election is to determine, for capital allowances purposes, the amount of the price for the Property that should be attributed to fixtures on which the Seller has claimed allowances.</p><p>Depending on the circumstances, it may be necessary to use more than one variation of the capital gains clauses in this Precedent and also in <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>. For example, the Property may contain fixtures on which the Seller has claimed allowances, but also fixtures on which the Seller was not entitled to claim allowances, such as cold water or electrical systems acquired before April 2008. In this situation it may be appropriate to use both the drafting in this contract as well as option 4 in <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>, with modifications to make clear which clause applies to which category of fixture.</p></div><div><p>For more information see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a> and <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div></div></div><div><lnb-prec:definition><b>CAA&#160;2001</b><div><p>Capital Allowances Act 2001;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Election</b><div><p>an election in respect of the <b>Fixtures</b> under section 198 of <b>CAA 2001</b> in the form annexed to this Agreement as <a id-ref='ukContentItem1526898061-880715161' type='schedule'/>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem7ffa5e9f-e1cc-4d3e-a8e7-2a787fd78282'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Election</p><div><p>For details of elections in real estate transactions, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Fixtures</b><div><p>all plant and machinery which is installed or otherwise fixed in or to the <b>Property</b> so as to become (in law) part of the <b>Property</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem047859c8-e9af-4c86-a104-979d3ffe03cc'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Fixtures</p><div><p>Fixtures are plant or machinery that is installed or fixed so that they become, in law, part of a building or land. Examples include boilers, alarm systems and fitted kitchen units. There are special rules to determine whether a taxpayer is eligible to claim allowances for expenditure on a fixture. In order to claim allowances, the taxpayer must have an interest in the land or building of which the fixture is part. Further rules determine who may claim allowances where more than one person might have a claim, for instance where a person constructs a building, installs fixtures, then leases the building to another person for a capital sum that includes a payment for those fixtures. For new fixtures, the capital allowances claim is based on the actual expenditure. For more information see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Integral Features</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> that are integral features for the purposes of section 33A of <b>CAA 2001</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4e35b866-138c-4854-b7bd-368945e25f2e'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Integral Features</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Capital Allowances Act 2001, s 33A</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>Integral features are a special category of plant and machinery. They are defined by statute and include electrical systems, cold water systems, space and water heating systems, air conditioning systems, and lifts. Integral features represent an exception to the general rule that the definition of plant comes from case law. Statute specifically provides that integral features always qualify as plant (although they attract allowances at a lower rate). For more information, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_161955'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;integral features</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Non-integral Features</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> that are not <b>Integral Features</b>; </p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Prior Right</b><div><p>has the meaning of &#8216;prior right&#8217; for the purposes of section 181(2) of CAA 2001.</p></div></lnb-prec:definition></div></div><div id='ukContentItem501d9779-1046-4b61-8f0d-f5f5c15d812a'><div><p>On <b>Completion</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall make the <b>Election</b> and shall each, within <em type='number'>insert number</em> working days of <b>Completion</b>, deliver an executed original <b>Election</b> to their respective tax inspector at <b>HMRC</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Integral Features</b> shall be &#163; <em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7d07a11-1d76-48f8-9e04-c9c4b70af874'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/>&#8212;Integral and Non-integral Features</p><div><p>Dividing the fixtures into integral and non-integral features is the absolute minimum HMRC will accept. Depending on which fixtures exist in the Property, it may be necessary to subdivide them further and provide more details, such as 'electrical systems' or 'cold water systems'. In this case it may be better to delete clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650' type='clause'/> rely on a more detailed breakdown in the proforma election in <a id-ref='ukContentItem1526898061-880715161' type='schedule'/>. See Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_163854'>Election&#8212;capital allowances apportionment on sale of land&#8212;CAA 2001, s 198</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Non-integral Features</b> shall be <em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem319cec81-cb14-4d36-926e-ce949f567f03'><div><p>Each of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemc5df0ee3-08eb-4925-a8e3-33f52238585a'><div><p>provide all necessary information to each other and take all reasonable steps required to validly make the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem144eeb00-b956-485c-a895-427af7748ae9'><div><p>submit a copy of the <b>Election</b> to <b>HMRC</b> with their tax return for the first period affected by the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItema8e4c85b-ffc7-4568-ace2-7967853612d1'><div><p>take all reasonable steps to ensure that the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> are accepted by <b>HMRC</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdce79faf-9fbc-4a52-afbb-21adf5a4abdf'><div><p>reflect the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> in their respective tax computations and returns.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemacc4de87-96b3-4966-a239-c45bb9bfa360'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that no person has a <b>Prior Right</b> in relation to any of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemabc048f4-b70e-400c-bccd-ec560520ed1a'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that the total and individual figures in the <b>Election</b> are no greater than the amounts incurred by it in accordance with <b>CAA 2001</b> for the provision of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "::Home", id: "ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E9AFE023-D5CF-4502-9D3D-5453F9E03698'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' opt-key='opt-N73574'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p> No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party <em type='text'>such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any securities exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem52b8262f-83f4-481e-a3e0-95e8d8a98954'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This is a short form announcements provision. For a longer form clause see: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>This clause is drafted on the basis that:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>it binds all of the parties to the contract</p></div></li><li><div><p>the general prohibition on announcements and other public disclosures relates to the existence of the contract itself and any of the matters contained in it</p></div></li><li><div><p>the parties will remain binding for the duration of the contract (if the clause is intended to survive termination of the contract, this may be stated in the clause itself or elsewhere in the contract, eg in the termination or survival clause)</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made with the prior written consent of the other party, with no express process being set out to obtain such consent, although it must not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made as required by law, a court or any other authority, without any prior written consent from the other party or any consultation with them being required.</p></div><div><p>The announcements clause normally forms part of the main contract relating to a transaction or arrangement and, as such, will take effect on the signing of the contract. Prior to signing, any announcement relating to the proposed transaction or arrangement will normally be restricted by the terms of a confidentiality agreement entered into between the parties. The terms of such a confidentiality agreement should be considered in drafting an announcements clause; it would be usual for the announcements clause (along with any confidentiality clause) to replace this initial confidentiality agreement.</p></div><div><p>It is necessary to consider an announcements clause in the contract in conjunction with any confidentiality clause, to ensure that the two work effectively together.</p></div></li></ul></div></div>"}, {PA: "::Home", id: "ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E9AFE023-D5CF-4502-9D3D-5453F9E03698'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' opt-key='opt-N72516'><p class='main_heading'><lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party></p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1494500282-101398358'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Guarantor</p><div><p>This guarantee clause is suitable for use where the Seller requires some security that the Buyer will observe its obligations in the contract. The guarantee clause provides that if the Buyer defaults the guarantor will perform those obligations (and this will include the obligation to pay the purchase price to the Seller). The guarantor also indemnifies the Seller against any losses or liability incurred because of the Buyer&#8217;s default. Delete if no guarantor is being provided.</p></div><div><p>Where the agreed heads of terms incorporate a rental guarantee by the Seller for void occupational rents post-Completion, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OL6_245546'>Rental guarantee schedule</a>.</p></div></div></lnb-prec:title><div><p>In consideration of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> entering into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> at the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor's</lnb-prec:party> request the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> agrees with the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> as a primary obligation as follows:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem6ee7430d-2436-4cbd-a424-5998ea800fc6'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> must perform and observe all of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem10d54eae-693d-4a1f-b86a-88d839de7f41'><div><p>if the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> defaults in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will perform them;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItembb7685cb-daff-41b1-b57c-8b7c6326d0f8'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will indemnify the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> against all claims, demands, damages, losses, liability, costs, fees and expenses sustained by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> by reason of, or arising in any way directly or indirectly out of, the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e'><div><p>if this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> has been disclaimed following the insolvency of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may serve notice in writing on the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> (the &#8216;<b>Guarantor Notice</b>&#8217;) requiring the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> in accordance with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> with the following modifications:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemd421ca62-727b-49e6-9240-91993f13ced3'><div><p>all obligations of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be deemed to have been entered into by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> as though it were named as <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in place of the party defined as the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem816b7794-9d86-4cb3-84fa-81079304136a'><div><p>if a notice to complete served by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> on the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> has expired at the date of service of the Guarantor Notice the <b>Completion Date</b> shall be <em type='number'>5</em> working days after the date of service of the Guarantor Notice;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem545c300a-9165-4d26-9d02-5ef27f83db51'><div><p>the Guarantor is to pay:</p></div><div number-type='loweralpha'><div id='ukContentItemaacf6481-adc4-4d44-9044-072c062496b1'><div><p><b>Interest</b> on the balance of the <b>Price</b> from the contractual <b>Completion Date</b> until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdbf94e06-289b-4a0a-bce1-84e84f47f6ec'><div><p>all money expended by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in consequence of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default from the date of expenditure until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days;</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7203eb7e-1bf8-472d-bd14-67e4f0494902'><div><p>for the avoidance of doubt no further deposit shall be payable by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem64b572ca-3e0c-48bf-9c51-f30482836137'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Disclaimer</p><div><p>This gives the Seller the ability to require the Guarantor to take a transfer of the Property in the event that the contract is disclaimed. See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM3_149095'>The process of disclaimer by a liquidator or trustee in bankruptcy under sections 178 or 315 of the Insolvency Act 1986</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1'><div><p>the liability of the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> shall not be affected reduced or extinguished by:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb2b70c21-0e1a-4ca0-a124-6ad25dd6e5f4'><div><p>any time or indulgence granted by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> to the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemfb07de4a-86ee-446c-b76f-346d6ca05a86'><div><p>any neglect or forbearance of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in enforcing its rights under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemaa2a78f2-df61-4f7b-8af6-482506233419'><div><p>any variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> agreed between the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>; or</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89'><div><p>the fact that any other person or entity comprising the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> or intended to comprise the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> has not executed this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or is not bound by the guarantee in clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>;</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem94e8ddef-544f-4d85-bd54-629d58779cbf'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89' type='clause'/>&#8212;Signatories</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Harvey v Dunbar Assets plc [2013] All ER (D) 400 (Jul)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>In <em class='it'>Harvey</em> the court decided a bank guarantee was subject to a condition that it would be signed by all the other intended guarantors named in the deed, and, so, liability as a &#8216;Guarantor&#8217; was only imposed on an individual signatory to the document in circumstances where all the named individuals did indeed sign the guarantee. This meant the individual being sued was never on the hook as guarantor because one of the intended guarantors had not signed the document (his signature had been forged). The guarantee was a single composite document, which sought to impose joint and several liability on four individuals together defined as &#8216;the Guarantor&#8217; and envisaged it would be signed by all four individuals. There was nothing in the wording excluding the result that all intended guarantors had to sign for an individual guarantor to be liable. It is assumed that the contract into which this clause is inserted provides for joint and several liability where obligations are owed by more than one party. This sub-clause is an attempt to avoid the problem in <em class='it'>Harvey</em> as whilst the case relates to a bank guarantee it could, of course, be of wider application in the context of guarantees. It has not been tested in court.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf2e07994-da50-4aed-8b93-04436780dc3b'><div><p>anything else by which apart from clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1' type='clause'/> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> would be released other than a release under seal.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0D76E13D-C1AD-49AE-BF09-C0BA14E28980'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the deed of assignment and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0D76E13D-C1AD-49AE-BF09-C0BA14E28980'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='2345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='2345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the deed of assignment. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6951CDC9-B908-4969-AE8B-E22905965FE0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its employees, agents and representatives will comply with all applicable laws and regulations, provided that neither <b>party</b> shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by the other <b>party</b> (or its employees, agents and representatives).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3F1F4DB1-95EF-484C-9A47-986A6E1BB522'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply with all laws, enactments, regulations, regulatory policies, guidelines and industry codes applicable to them and shall maintain such authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform their obligations under or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6F6F610F-2DA0-45B0-BE44-026AA32FEDF4'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' opt-key='opt-N72516'><p class='main_heading'><lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party></p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1494500282-101398358'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Guarantor</p><div><p>This guarantee clause is suitable for use where the Seller requires some security that the Buyer will observe its obligations in the contract. The guarantee clause provides that if the Buyer defaults the guarantor will perform those obligations (and this will include the obligation to pay the purchase price to the Seller). The guarantor also indemnifies the Seller against any losses or liability incurred because of the Buyer&#8217;s default. Delete if no guarantor is being provided.</p></div><div><p>Where the agreed heads of terms incorporate a rental guarantee by the Seller for void occupational rents post-Completion, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OL6_245546'>Rental guarantee schedule</a>.</p></div></div></lnb-prec:title><div><p>In consideration of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> entering into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> at the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor'</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s request the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> agrees with the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> as a primary obligation as follows:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem6ee7430d-2436-4cbd-a424-5998ea800fc6'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> must perform and observe all of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem10d54eae-693d-4a1f-b86a-88d839de7f41'><div><p>if the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> defaults in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will perform them;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItembb7685cb-daff-41b1-b57c-8b7c6326d0f8'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will indemnify the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> against all claims, demands, damages, losses, liability, costs, fees and expenses sustained by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> by reason of, or arising in any way directly or indirectly out of, the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e'><div><p>if this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> has been disclaimed following the insolvency of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may serve notice in writing on the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> (the &#8216;<b>Guarantor Notice</b>&#8217;) requiring the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> in accordance with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> with the following modifications:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemd421ca62-727b-49e6-9240-91993f13ced3'><div><p>all obligations of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be deemed to have been entered into by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> as though it were named as <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in place of the party defined as the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem816b7794-9d86-4cb3-84fa-81079304136a'><div><p>if a notice to complete served by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> on the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> has expired at the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b> the <b>Completion Date</b> shall be <em type='number'>5</em> working days after the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem545c300a-9165-4d26-9d02-5ef27f83db51'><div><p>the <b>Guarantor</b> is to pay:</p></div><div number-type='loweralpha'><div id='ukContentItemaacf6481-adc4-4d44-9044-072c062496b1'><div><p><b>Interest</b> on the balance of the <b>Price</b> from the contractual <b>Completion Date</b> until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdbf94e06-289b-4a0a-bce1-84e84f47f6ec'><div><p>all money expended by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in consequence of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default from the date of expenditure until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days;</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7203eb7e-1bf8-472d-bd14-67e4f0494902'><div><p>for the avoidance of doubt no further deposit shall be payable by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem64b572ca-3e0c-48bf-9c51-f30482836137'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Disclaimer</p><div><p>This gives the Seller the ability to require the Guarantor to take a transfer of the Property in the event that the contract is disclaimed. See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM3_149095'>The process of disclaimer by a liquidator or trustee in bankruptcy under sections 178 or 315 of the Insolvency Act 1986</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1'><div><p>the liability of the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> shall not be affected reduced or extinguished by:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb2b70c21-0e1a-4ca0-a124-6ad25dd6e5f4'><div><p>any time or indulgence granted by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> to the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemfb07de4a-86ee-446c-b76f-346d6ca05a86'><div><p>any neglect or forbearance of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in enforcing its rights under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemaa2a78f2-df61-4f7b-8af6-482506233419'><div><p>any variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> agreed between the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>; or</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89'><div><p>the fact that any other person or entity comprising the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> or intended to comprise the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> has not executed this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or is not bound by the guarantee in clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>;</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem94e8ddef-544f-4d85-bd54-629d58779cbf'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89' type='clause'/>&#8212;Signatories</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Harvey v Dunbar Assets plc [2013] All ER (D) 400 (Jul)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>In <em class='it'>Harvey</em> the court decided a bank guarantee was subject to a condition that it would be signed by all the other intended guarantors named in the deed, and, so, liability as a &#8216;Guarantor&#8217; was only imposed on an individual signatory to the document in circumstances where all the named individuals did indeed sign the guarantee. This meant the individual being sued was never on the hook as guarantor because one of the intended guarantors had not signed the document (his signature had been forged). The guarantee was a single composite document, which sought to impose joint and several liability on four individuals together defined as &#8216;the Guarantor&#8217; and envisaged it would be signed by all four individuals. There was nothing in the wording excluding the result that all intended guarantors had to sign for an individual guarantor to be liable. It is assumed that the contract into which this clause is inserted provides for joint and several liability where obligations are owed by more than one party. This sub-clause is an attempt to avoid the problem in <em class='it'>Harvey</em> as whilst the case relates to a bank guarantee it could, of course, be of wider application in the context of guarantees. It has not been tested in court.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf2e07994-da50-4aed-8b93-04436780dc3b'><div><p>anything else by which apart from clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1' type='clause'/> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> would be released other than a release under seal.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6F6F610F-2DA0-45B0-BE44-026AA32FEDF4'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' opt-key='opt-N70726'><p class='main_heading'>Capital allowances</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d'><div><p>In clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/> the following definitions apply:</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema8c561ba-3721-4e44-b601-b05c3c8c5a73'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/>&#8212;Capital allowances</p><div><p>It is important on any sale of property to consider the position in relation to capital allowances. In order to qualify for plant and machinery allowances, expenditure must be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>capital</p></div></li><li><div><p>on plant and machinery, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>wholly or partly for the purposes of a qualifying activity</p></div></li></ul><div><p>In addition, the person incurring the expenditure must own the plant and machinery as a result of that expenditure. See: <a normcite='0OLU_123942'>Capital allowances&#8212;overview</a> for further information on the qualification criteria.</p></div><div><p>Properties often have substantial plant and machinery. This may be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>fixtures, and/or</p></div></li><li><div><p>integral features</p></div></li></ul><div><p>For information on the practicalities of capital allowance-related warranties and pre-contract enquiries on a property transfer, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185796'>Plant and machinery allowances on property acquisitions and disposals (including pre-contract enquiries)</a>.</p></div><div><p>The drafting in this clause is for use where the Seller has claimed allowances and the parties will enter into a section 198 election on Completion. For alternative drafting clauses where the Seller:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>has claimed allowances and the parties will apply to the First-tier Tax Tribunal for a just and reasonable allocation of allowances; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has claimed allowances but the information is not available on completion to enable a section 198 election to be entered into at completion; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has not claimed capital allowances, and was not entitled to do so; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>was entitled to claim capital allowances but has not done so</p></div></li></ul><div><p>see the drafting alternatives and notes in Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>.</p></div><div><p>The purpose of a section 198 election is to determine, for capital allowances purposes, the amount of the price for the Property that should be attributed to fixtures on which the Seller has claimed allowances.</p><p>Depending on the circumstances, it may be necessary to use more than one variation of the capital gains clauses in this Precedent and also in <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>. For example, the Property may contain fixtures on which the Seller has claimed allowances, but also fixtures on which the Seller was not entitled to claim allowances, such as cold water or electrical systems acquired before April 2008. In this situation it may be appropriate to use both the drafting in this contract as well as option 4 in <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>, with modifications to make clear which clause applies to which category of fixture.</p></div><div><p>For more information see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a> and <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div></div></div><div><lnb-prec:definition><b>CAA&#160;2001</b><div><p>Capital Allowances Act 2001;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Election</b><div><p>an election in respect of the <b>Fixtures</b> under section 198 of <b>CAA 2001</b> in the form annexed to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> as <a id-ref='ukContentItem1529398155-94474267' type='schedule'/>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem7ffa5e9f-e1cc-4d3e-a8e7-2a787fd78282'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Election</p><div><p>For details of elections in real estate transactions, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Fixtures</b><div><p>all plant and machinery which is installed or otherwise fixed in or to the <b>Property</b> so as to become (in law) part of the <b>Property</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem047859c8-e9af-4c86-a104-979d3ffe03cc'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Fixtures</p><div><p>Fixtures are plant or machinery that is installed or fixed so that they become, in law, part of a building or land. Examples include boilers, alarm systems and fitted kitchen units. There are special rules to determine whether a taxpayer is eligible to claim allowances for expenditure on a fixture. In order to claim allowances, the taxpayer must have an interest in the land or building of which the fixture is part. Further rules determine who may claim allowances where more than one person might have a claim, for instance where a person constructs a building, installs fixtures, then leases the building to another person for a capital sum that includes a payment for those fixtures. For new fixtures, the capital allowances claim is based on the actual expenditure. For more information see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Integral Features</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> that are integral features for the purposes of section 33(A) of <b>CAA 2001</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4e35b866-138c-4854-b7bd-368945e25f2e'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Integral Features</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Capital Allowances Act 2001, s 33A</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>Integral features are a special category of plant and machinery. They are defined by statute and include electrical systems, cold water systems, space and water heating systems, air conditioning systems, and lifts. Integral features represent an exception to the general rule that the definition of plant comes from case law. Statute specifically provides that integral features always qualify as plant (although they attract allowances at a lower rate). For more information, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_161955'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;integral features</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Non-integral Features</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> that are not <b>Integral Features</b>; </p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Prior Right</b><div><p>has the meaning of &#8216;prior right&#8217; for the purposes of section 181(2) of CAA 2001.</p></div></lnb-prec:definition></div></div><div id='ukContentItem501d9779-1046-4b61-8f0d-f5f5c15d812a'><div><p>On <b>Completion</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall make the <b>Election</b> and shall each, within <em type='number'>insert number</em> working days of <b>Completion</b>, deliver an executed original <b>Election</b> to their respective tax inspector at <b>HMRC</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Integral Features</b> shall be &#163;<em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7d07a11-1d76-48f8-9e04-c9c4b70af874'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/>&#8212;Integral and Non-integral Features</p><div><p>Dividing the fixtures into integral and non-integral features is the absolute minimum HMRC will accept. Depending on which fixtures exist in the Property, it may be necessary to subdivide them further and provide more details, such as 'electrical systems' or 'cold water systems'. In this case it may be better to delete clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650' type='clause'/> rely on a more detailed breakdown in the proforma election in <a id-ref='ukContentItem1529398155-94474267' type='schedule'/>. See Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_163854'>Election&#8212;capital allowances apportionment on sale of land&#8212;CAA 2001, s 198</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Non-integral Features</b> shall be <em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem319cec81-cb14-4d36-926e-ce949f567f03'><div><p>Each of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemc5df0ee3-08eb-4925-a8e3-33f52238585a'><div><p>provide all necessary information to each other and take all reasonable steps required to validly make the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem144eeb00-b956-485c-a895-427af7748ae9'><div><p>submit a copy of the <b>Election</b> to <b>HMRC</b> with their tax return for the first period affected by the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItema8e4c85b-ffc7-4568-ace2-7967853612d1'><div><p>take all reasonable steps to ensure that the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> are accepted by <b>HMRC</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdce79faf-9fbc-4a52-afbb-21adf5a4abdf'><div><p>reflect the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> in their respective tax computations and returns.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemacc4de87-96b3-4966-a239-c45bb9bfa360'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that no person has a <b>Prior Right</b> in relation to any of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemabc048f4-b70e-400c-bccd-ec560520ed1a'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that the total and individual figures in the <b>Election</b> are no greater than the amounts incurred by it in accordance with <b>CAA 2001</b> for the provision of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6F6F610F-2DA0-45B0-BE44-026AA32FEDF4'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' opt-key='opt-N73574'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p> No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party <em type='text'>such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any securities exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem52b8262f-83f4-481e-a3e0-95e8d8a98954'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This is a short form announcements provision. For a longer form clause see: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>This clause is drafted on the basis that:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>it binds all of the parties to the contract</p></div></li><li><div><p>the general prohibition on announcements and other public disclosures relates to the existence of the contract itself and any of the matters contained in it</p></div></li><li><div><p>the parties will remain binding for the duration of the contract (if the clause is intended to survive termination of the contract, this may be stated in the clause itself or elsewhere in the contract, eg in the termination or survival clause)</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made with the prior written consent of the other party, with no express process being set out to obtain such consent, although it must not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made as required by law, a court or any other authority, without any prior written consent from the other party or any consultation with them being required.</p></div><div><p>The announcements clause normally forms part of the main contract relating to a transaction or arrangement and, as such, will take effect on the signing of the contract. Prior to signing, any announcement relating to the proposed transaction or arrangement will normally be restricted by the terms of a confidentiality agreement entered into between the parties. The terms of such a confidentiality agreement should be considered in drafting an announcements clause; it would be usual for the announcements clause (along with any confidentiality clause) to replace this initial confidentiality agreement.</p></div><div><p>It is necessary to consider an announcements clause in the contract in conjunction with any confidentiality clause, to ensure that the two work effectively together.</p></div></li></ul></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E678409E-E427-471F-8C4C-0B18CC277C0F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> shall comply with <b>Applicable Law</b> and shall maintain such licences, authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform its obligations under or in connection with the <b>Contract</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on the customer to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F855D9C1-39C2-4FC8-BEEB-1C1AF12D7739'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> shall comply with <b>Applicable Law</b> and shall maintain such licences, authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform its obligations under or in connection with the <b>Contract</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on the customer to comply with applicable laws. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>. Ensure that this clause is compatible with the data protection law compliance provisions.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:A5B40CD9-4333-49F1-9C08-511061D55B9B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its employees, agents and representatives shall comply with all applicable laws and regulations, provided that neither <b>party</b> shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by the other <b>party</b> (or its employees, agents and representatives).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E965E33B-B78B-4B24-B29F-21D5CF641782'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' opt-key='opt-9F1EAECD'><p class='main_heading'>Force Majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from any <b>Force Majeure</b>. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such a <b>Force Majeure</b> causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such a <b>Force Majeure</b> continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force Majeure</p><div><p>This clause is most likely to benefit the supplier. Remove this clause (and associated definition) if not appropriate.</p></div><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:C40D4A4C-F5D3-4041-B257-3812AF3CCB38'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each party shall comply with all laws, enactments, regulations, regulatory policies, guidelines and industry codes applicable to them and shall maintain such authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform their obligations under or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:ADC4302E-1803-4321-9DAA-78249BF6188A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p><em class='bf'>Interpretation</em></p></div><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;party&#8217; includes that party&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p> a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p> words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow 'include', 'includes', 'including', &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D18E3970009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D18E3970009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DCF82925-4EC4-4D47-B1C4-07AA8A4A05E9'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p><em class='bf'>Interpretation</em></p></div><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;party&#8217; includes that party&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p> a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D18E3970009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D18E3970009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:173D92E0-4C60-46C5-973B-15358DD67A2B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/> is legally binding within this Precedent (see clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1524823586-37670563' type='clause'/>).</p></div><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:173D92E0-4C60-46C5-973B-15358DD67A2B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/> is legally binding within this Precedent (see clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1524823586-37670563' type='clause'/>).</p></div><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:173D92E0-4C60-46C5-973B-15358DD67A2B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <lnb-prec:party>Party A</lnb-prec:party> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <lnb-prec:party>Party B</lnb-prec:party>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <lnb-prec:party>Party A</lnb-prec:party> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <lnb-prec:party>Party B</lnb-prec:party>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/> is legally binding within this Precedent (see clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1524823586-37670563' type='clause'/>).</p></div><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:173D92E0-4C60-46C5-973B-15358DD67A2B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;<b>party</b>&#8217; includes that <b>party</b>&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E800009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E800009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/></p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form version, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:173D92E0-4C60-46C5-973B-15358DD67A2B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/> is legally binding within this Precedent (see clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1524823586-37670563' type='clause'/>).</p></div><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:173D92E0-4C60-46C5-973B-15358DD67A2B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/> is legally binding within this Precedent (see clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1524823586-37670563' type='clause'/>).</p></div><div><p>This third party rights clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:173D92E0-4C60-46C5-973B-15358DD67A2B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/> is legally binding within this Precedent (see clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1524823586-37670563' type='clause'/>).</p></div><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:173D92E0-4C60-46C5-973B-15358DD67A2B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>party</b> without the prior written consent of the other <b>party</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/> is legally binding within this Precedent (see clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1524823586-37670563' type='clause'/>).</p></div><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:173D92E0-4C60-46C5-973B-15358DD67A2B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/> is legally binding within this Precedent (see clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1524823586-37670563' type='clause'/>).</p></div><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. This clause would need to be made subject to the provisions of any dispute resolution clause preventing the parties from issuing court proceedings until the chosen form of dispute resolution procedure has been concluded without success. Note this Precedent does not include a dispute resolution clause.</p></div><div><p>For a dispute resolution clause and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>For a long form jurisdiction clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CA642FE7-0FCC-4F85-A554-9715788FE04C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='2345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='2345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b>Letter</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the letter of novation. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CA642FE7-0FCC-4F85-A554-9715788FE04C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b>Letter</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the letter of novation and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:25F6EA54-F377-45BF-B029-AE0AB2898465'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b>Letter</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the assignment letter and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:25F6EA54-F377-45BF-B029-AE0AB2898465'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='2345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='2345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b>Letter</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the assignment letter. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specified document[s]</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each party shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting party, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1558004870-437925162'><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1558004870-4382410162'><div><p>The parties agree to the issue of a <em opt-key='opt-N68139'>joint</em> press announcement, <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='0012'>in a form to be agreed, both parties acting reasonably</em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='0012'>in the agreed form, attached in Appendix <em type='number'>insert number of Appendix</em>, immediately following <em type='text'>insert details of relevant event</em></em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem28587cab-d412-4c44-a41c-33d9feafe87f'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1558004870-4382410162' type='clause'/></p><div><p>It may be that with a confidential research services agreement, the parties will want to keep the existence of the agreement confidential. And so if a contract is particularly commercially sensitive or a party is wanting to maintain a high level of control in relation to publicity surrounding its organisation and brand, then a more general clause requiring the other party to obtain that the first party&#8217;s prior written consent to any relevant public statements or announcements may be appropriate.</p></div></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither party shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that party. The party affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other party in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>the party not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>either party</em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>, the parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. The optional wording should be included where the agreement contains a dispute resolution clause preventing the parties from issuing court proceedings until the chosen form of dispute resolution procedure has been concluded without success. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E5020001'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, each</em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E5020001'>Each</em> party shall pay all sums that it owes to the other party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the parties nor make any party the agent of another party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a party to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's <em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E232E2E9-1F48-46E1-B9AD-AA7239B9BA90'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No party may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a party may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other party&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. Each party acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b>Affiliate</b> in relation to that party&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that party itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This assignment clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>. A definition of Affiliate should be added to the definitions section of the agreement. See Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_188755'>Affiliate definition</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:33DCDD29-616E-4254-A627-14A7BE4E010D'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This power of attorney and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Paragraph <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law paragraph specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:33DCDD29-616E-4254-A627-14A7BE4E010D'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='2345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='2345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this power of attorney, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Paragraph <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction paragraph specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E685B048-EA27-48A5-BE59-DBFD04781494'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b>Agreement</b> includes its schedules;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;<b>party</b>&#8217; includes that <b>party</b>&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-46916388'>without prejudice to the provisions of clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem19979021-e836-457d-aef1-f8fe8b7c8bef' type='clause'/>,</em> a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D72E8590009'>in force as at the date of this <b>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D72E8590009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a <b>party</b> under this <b>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1515143413-8461125'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a' type='clause'/></p><div><p>The data protection provisions in this precedent (see clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem19979021-e836-457d-aef1-f8fe8b7c8bef' type='clause'/>) are generally drafted on the basis that references to data protection laws means such laws as amended from to time (given that customers are placing increased emphasis on such provisions and since suppliers will usually need to comply with similar basic obligations for all customers) &#8212; and on the assumption that the option &#8216;amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time&#8217; will be used (without any qualification such as &#8216;except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this <b>Agreement</b>&#8217;). Adapt clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem19979021-e836-457d-aef1-f8fe8b7c8bef' type='clause'/> and other provisions if necessary to ensure the agreement clearly sets out how changes in legislation will apply for the purposes of data protection and other provisions of this agreement (and include &#8216;<em class='it'>Without prejudice to the provisions of...</em>&#8217; language if the generality of this clause is overridden in specific circumstances by other clauses).</p></div></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "CORPORATE", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:1CBEF27C-F33F-49CF-B967-21BEDAEB809D'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Parties</lnb-prec:party> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D43E37712345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D43E37712345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "CORPORATE", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:1CBEF27C-F33F-49CF-B967-21BEDAEB809D'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='notfound'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>Party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='notfound'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>Party</b>'s <em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>Party A</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>Party B</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party A</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party B</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='notfound'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>Party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>Party</b>. The <b>Party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>Party</b> in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>the <b>Party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>either <b>Party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other <b>Party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:1CC36257-F6FE-4BC4-A322-2FF71C38A0F4'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>Party</b> without the prior written consent of the other <b>Party</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:1CC36257-F6FE-4BC4-A322-2FF71C38A0F4'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:1CC36257-F6FE-4BC4-A322-2FF71C38A0F4'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem5b0e753b-ca4f-4dd0-a1cb-90a65562fb95' type='clause'/>, the <b>Parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. The optional wording should be included where the agreement contains a dispute resolution clause preventing the parties from issuing court proceedings until the chosen form of dispute resolution procedure has been concluded without success. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:1CC36257-F6FE-4BC4-A322-2FF71C38A0F4'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>Parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>Party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specified document[s]</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>Party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;If the parties entered into prior, related confidentiality agreements (see definition of &#8216;confidentiality agreement&#8217; and background clause) it is important to cover these here.</p></div><div><p>For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:1CC36257-F6FE-4BC4-A322-2FF71C38A0F4'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each <b>Party</b> shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting <b>Party</b>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "CORPORATE", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:ADE54CC1-5CDD-402B-951A-6F50DD958A58'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "CORPORATE", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:ADE54CC1-5CDD-402B-951A-6F50DD958A58'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Parties</lnb-prec:party> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D20E22782345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D20E22782345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "BANKINGANDFINANCE", id: "ukContentItemd153a234-e311-4cf9-b8c8-f7ac4f1aa5cd", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemd153a234-e311-4cf9-b8c8-f7ac4f1aa5cd'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemd153a234-e311-4cf9-b8c8-f7ac4f1aa5cd' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8BC7A568-E2D7-4F01-9CAB-6871835B8D1E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemd153a234-e311-4cf9-b8c8-f7ac4f1aa5cd'><p class='main_heading'>Counterparts</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentIteme51bc6df-0e4e-4717-82fc-f914132f11d1'><div><p>This <b>Agreement</b> may be signed in any number of separate counterparts and this has the same effect as if the signatures on those counterparts were on a single copy of this <b>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme0811463-9064-4103-98c0-0b67c08b9bb1'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-D26E88130001'>Each Party may evidence their signature of this <b>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N76453'>by faxing or</em> by emailing a signed signature page of this <b>Agreement</b> in PDF format together with the final version of this <b>Agreement</b> in PDF or Word format, which shall constitute an original signed counterpart of this <b>Agreement</b>. Each Party adopting this method of signing will, following circulation <em opt-key='opt-N76469'>by fax or</em> by email, provide the original, hard copy signed signature page to the other Party as soon as reasonably practicable.</em><em alt-key='alt-D26E88130001'><em class='caps'>to comply with option 2 or 3 of the Law Society guidance:<!--This doesn't come out in caps or bold in the word download--><!--Pete Maidens is aware of this issue--></em> Each Party may evidence their signature of this <b>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N76486'>by faxing or</em> by emailing a signed signature page of this <b>Agreement</b> in PDF format, which shall, together with the final version of this <b>Agreement</b>, constitute an original signed counterpart of this <b>Agreement</b>. Each Party adopting this method of signing will, following circulation <em opt-key='opt-N76502'>by fax or</em> by email, provide the original, hard copy signed signature page to the other Party as soon as reasonably practicable.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf91f9edb-7d46-4229-9633-c0c186846b98'><p class='main_heading'>Clause 27&#8212;Counterparts</p><div><p><em class='bf'>Purpose of the Clause</em></p></div><div><p>A counterparts clause is a common boilerplate clause which provides that the parties to an agreement may execute separate copies of it, rather than all parties having to sign the same copy of the agreement. It is common practice to sign an agreement in counterparts, and this mechanism can be particularly useful where there are a large number of parties, or where the parties are located in different regions or countries and will be unable to hold a physical completion meeting.</p></div><div><p>If an agreement does not contain a counterparts clause, the parties will not be prevented from executing a document in counterpart. However, using a counterparts clause is advisable for certainty, and to prevent any argument that the agreement is not binding because it has not been properly executed.</p></div><div><p>The counterparts clause commonly consists of:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>a statement that the document may be executed in counterparts, and that each signed counterpart is to be treated as an original, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>a sub-clause dealing with virtual signing (ie circulating the signature pages by email)</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The difference between original counterparts and original duplicates should be noted here. If all the parties sign a number of copies of the agreement, each copy is an original duplicate rather than a counterpart, and the counterparts clause will not be applicable.</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Key legal issues</em></p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>R (on the application of Mercury Tax Group and another) v HM Revenue &amp; Customs Commissioners and others [2008] All ER (D) 129 (Nov)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Law Society Guidance: Execution of documents by virtual means</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The <em class='it'>Mercury Tax</em> case considered the effectiveness of pre-signed signature pages and virtual signings and closings where signature pages are exchanged by email. Following this case, the Law Society issued guidance on good practice for virtual signings.</p></div><div><p>The Law Society guidance sets out three options for the virtual signing of an agreement or deed. The options are stated to be non-exhaustive, but it will be in the interests of the parties to follow them as closely as possible in order to avoid any later dispute over virtual signing.</p></div><div><p>Regardless of which option is being followed, the Law Society recommends that all parties&#8217; lawyers agree to the proposed arrangements for the virtual signing/closing well in advance of execution. For this reason, it has become common practice to include specific drafting on virtual signings in the counterparts clause (see Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme0811463-9064-4103-98c0-0b67c08b9bb1' type='clause'/>).</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 1</em> gives guidance on circulating the entire document and the signed signature page by email. This method is suitable for both deeds and simple contracts (such as the Facility Agreement). The detailed requirements for option 1 are as follows:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>execution copies of the documents are emailed as PDF or Word attachments to all parties that will be absent and/or their lawyers (as agreed); the signature page may be emailed as a separate PDF or Word document, for convenience</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent signatory then prints and signs the signature page only (there is no need to print off the full document)</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent party then returns a single email to their lawyer or to the lawyers coordinating signing/closing as agreed and attaches <em class='it'>both</em> the final version of the PDF or Word agreement and a PDF copy of the signed signature page, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>at or shortly after signing/closing, the parties may wish to evidence the execution by one of the law firms circulating a final version of the document together with copies of executed signature pages</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The Law Society guidance confirms that, for option 1, the PDF or Word final version of the document and the PDF of the signed signature page will constitute an original signed document and each counterpart taken together will equate to the same physical document.</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 2</em> allows the parties to circulate the signature page by email, without a copy of the final agreement (so is slightly less burdensome than option 1). This method is only suitable for simple contracts (not deeds). The detailed requirements for option 2 are as follows:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>the final execution copies of the documents must be emailed as a PDF or Word attachement to all absent parties and/or their lawyers, as agreed; the signature page may be emailed as a separate PDF or Word document, for convenience</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent signatory then prints and signs the signature page only (there is no need to print off the full document)</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent party then emails its signature page as a PDF attachment to their lawyer or to the lawyers coordinating signing/closing as agreed, giving authority to attach it to the final approved version of the document, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>at or shortly after signing/closing, the parties may wish to evidence the execution by one of the law firms circulating a final version of the document together with copies of executed signature pages</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The Law Society guidance confirms that for option 2, the print-off of the final execution version of the document together with the attached signed signature pages will constitute an original signed document.</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 3</em> allows the parties to sign and circulate the signature pages in advance of finalising a document. This method is only suitable for simple contracts (not deeds). The detailed requirements for option 3 are:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>enough time should be allowed to coordinate the circulation of the signature pages prior to signing/closing and each signature page should clearly identify the document to which it relates</p></div></li><li><div><p>the signature page should be executed by each of the signatories and returned to their lawyers or the law firm coordinating the signing/closing, as agreed, by email (as a PDF attachment) or by courier, to be held to the order of the signatory or their lawyers, until authority is given for it to be attached to the document to be signed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>when each document has been finalised, the law firm coordinating the signing/closing should email the final version of the document to each absent party and/or their lawyers and obtain confirmation from them or their lawyers that they have agreed the final version of the document, and authorising the relevant law firm to attach the pre-signed signature page to the final version and to date and release the document</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The guidance confirms that the final approved version of the agreement, with the pre-signed signature pages that have been attached with the prior approval of the parties or their lawyers, will constitute an original signed document. For further information on signing see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OJE_145100'>Virtual execution of documents</a>.</p></div><div><p>Agreements that are executed as simple contracts (such as the Facility Agreement) can use any of the three options outlined in the Law Society guidance. The wording set out in the first set of square brackets in sub-clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme0811463-9064-4103-98c0-0b67c08b9bb1' type='clause'/> follows option 1. The alternative wording in the second set of square brackets is suitable if the parties are following option 2 or 3.</p></div><div><p>The entire sub-clause can be deleted if the parties are not intending to circulate signature pages electronically.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>party</b> without the prior written consent of the other <b>party</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemce13760d-e083-4cc3-9005-8b09f025eb4e' type='clause'/>, each <b>party</b> shall pay all sums that it owes to the other <b>party</b> under this <b>Agreement</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement, but is subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemce13760d-e083-4cc3-9005-8b09f025eb4e' type='clause'/> which permits the customer to set off certain sums. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D72E59160020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D72E59160020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>(or to the email address set out below)</em>. Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-5A8EFAB8'><div><p><em>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D72E59760021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D72E59760021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b>Agreement</b> includes its schedules;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;<b>party</b>&#8217; includes that <b>party</b>&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;<b>person</b>&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p> a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p> words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-46916388'>without prejudice to the provisions of clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem812aca81-2fde-448d-ab4f-963cda193866' type='clause'/>,</em> a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D72E8590009'>in force as at the date of this <b>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D72E8590009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a <b>party</b> under this <b>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting <b>party</b>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D72E5856022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D72E5856022'><em>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D72E5871023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D72E5871023'><em>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D72E5882024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D72E5882024'><em>insert name[s] of specified document[s]</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>Save for relevant third parties expressed to be beneficiaries of the indemnities specified in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItemde6ec3b6-4a8f-46b1-93f2-562b327e1658' type='clause'/>,<a id-ref='ukContentItem25af238a-56c4-4dbf-9099-10349932565c' type='clause'/> or <a id-ref='ukContentItemb14a0874-f0c9-4235-be4b-096a27ae4193' type='clause'/> <em opt-key='opt-N69553'>and <a id-ref='ukContentItem54d4c754-49be-4249-a356-a28f800c8dd0' type='schedule'/></em> (who may enforce their respective rights and benefits under those indemnities in accordance with the Contracts (Rights of Third Parties) Act 1999), a person who is not a party to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> may not enforce any of its terms under the Contracts (Rights of Third Parties) Act 1999. For the avoidance of doubt however this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> may be amended or rescinded by agreement between the parties without the consent of any third party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. The clause expressly grants rights to affiliates of the customer to enforce the benefits granted to them. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b>Agreement</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b>. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>3</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D72E60440001'>the party not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D72E60440001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:392A7D18-1702-46FA-ADEA-88BBA1060A09'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the <b>parties</b> out of or in connection with this <b>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each <b>party</b> who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the <b>parties</b> <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'> may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either <b>party</b> may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'> Until the <b>parties</b> have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither <b>party</b> shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either <b>party</b> may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause requires the parties to use reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:947C82E7-92F7-4227-975D-497F05470BA0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the deed of novation and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:947C82E7-92F7-4227-975D-497F05470BA0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>party</b> without the prior written consent of each of the other <b>parties</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the deed of novation. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:947C82E7-92F7-4227-975D-497F05470BA0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by a <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:947C82E7-92F7-4227-975D-497F05470BA0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid the deed of novation inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:947C82E7-92F7-4227-975D-497F05470BA0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the deed of novation survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:947C82E7-92F7-4227-975D-497F05470BA0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b><em opt-key='opt-2FBF62E0'> or to the email address set out in clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' type='clause'/></em>. Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery<em alt-key='alt-2FBF7094'>.</em><em alt-key='alt-2FBF7094'>; and</em></p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-2FBF7A29'><div><p>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of the <lnb-prec:party>Incoming Party</lnb-prec:party>, <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of the <lnb-prec:party>Remaining Party</lnb-prec:party>, and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of the <lnb-prec:party>Outgoing Party</lnb-prec:party>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>read</em> return email.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/> does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings, or, if applicable, any arbitration or other dispute resolution proceedings.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the deed of novation and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:947C82E7-92F7-4227-975D-497F05470BA0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> and is duly signed or executed (as the case may be) by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>. For the avoidance of doubt, any variation of the <b>Original Contract</b> will be subject to any variation provisions contained therein.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the deed of novation and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>There is no requirement that a deed necessarily be varied by a deed, but there are specific considerations when altering or varying a deed itself. For more information, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OJE_118711'>Deeds</a> and the drafting notes to Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_238889'>Deed of variation</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:947C82E7-92F7-4227-975D-497F05470BA0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each of the <b>parties</b> shall, at the request, cost and expense of any other <b>party</b>, perform all acts and sign, execute and deliver all deeds and documents, as may be<em opt-key='opt-3471D62A'> reasonably</em> required for the purpose of giving full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of any other party, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the deed of novation. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:947C82E7-92F7-4227-975D-497F05470BA0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D3E8042345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D3E8042345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the deed of novation. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:947C82E7-92F7-4227-975D-497F05470BA0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the deed of novation.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E2F0E8EF-B502-4948-B30C-10429F58A137'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the novation agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E2F0E8EF-B502-4948-B30C-10429F58A137'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-2FBF62E0'> or to the email address set out in clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' type='clause'/></em>. Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery<em alt-key='alt-2FBF7094'>.</em><em alt-key='alt-2FBF7094'>; and</em></p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-2FBF7A29'><div><p>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of the <lnb-prec:party>Incoming Party</lnb-prec:party>, <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of the <lnb-prec:party>Remaining Party</lnb-prec:party>, and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of the <lnb-prec:party>Outgoing Party</lnb-prec:party>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>read</em> return email.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/> does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings, or, if applicable, any arbitration or other dispute resolution proceedings.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the novation agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E2F0E8EF-B502-4948-B30C-10429F58A137'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the novation agreement.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E2F0E8EF-B502-4948-B30C-10429F58A137'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D3E8042345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D3E8042345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the novation agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E2F0E8EF-B502-4948-B30C-10429F58A137'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid the novation agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E2F0E8EF-B502-4948-B30C-10429F58A137'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by a <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E2F0E8EF-B502-4948-B30C-10429F58A137'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>party</b> without the prior written consent of each of the other <b>parties</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the novation agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E2F0E8EF-B502-4948-B30C-10429F58A137'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the novation agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E2F0E8EF-B502-4948-B30C-10429F58A137'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each of the <b>parties</b> shall, at the request, cost and expense of any other <b>party</b>, perform all acts and sign, execute and deliver all deeds and documents, as may be<em opt-key='opt-34741E4D'> reasonably</em> required for the purpose of giving full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of any other party, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the novation agreement. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E2F0E8EF-B502-4948-B30C-10429F58A137'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed (as the case may be) by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>. For the avoidance of doubt, any variation of the <b>Original Contract</b> will be subject to any variation provisions contained therein.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the novation agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number<em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'> or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the <b>parties</b> out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each <b>party</b> who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the <b>parties</b> <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either <b>party</b> may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the <b>parties</b> have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither <b>party</b> shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either <b>party</b> may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause requires the parties to use reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> includes its Schedules, which form part of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>; </p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;<b>party</b>&#8217; includes that <b>party</b>&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E800009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E800009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting <b>party</b>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'><em type='text'>insert names of specified documents</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>, the <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. The optional wording should be included where the agreement contains a dispute resolution clause preventing the parties from issuing court proceedings until the chosen form of dispute resolution procedure has been concluded without success. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E5020001'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, each</em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E5020001'>Each</em> <b>party</b> shall pay all sums that it owes to the other <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>party</b> without the prior written consent of the other <b>party</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from a <b>Force Majeure</b> event. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12D1C097-159A-46AE-99F8-F10247825E7B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No <b>party</b> may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554' opt-key='opt-F926A035'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a <b>party</b> may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other <b>party</b>&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. Each <b>party</b> acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b>Affiliate</b> in relation to that <b>party</b>&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that <b>party</b> itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This assignment clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>. If clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554' type='clause'/> is used, a definition of affiliate should be added to the definitions section of the agreement. See Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_188755'>Affiliate definition</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "BANKINGANDFINANCE", id: "ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:26CA703B-0C34-4367-9FCB-862B46401F6A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6'><p class='main_heading'>Counterparts</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemcace7bfe-e8c6-4fb8-aa54-a0afc1f84b7a'><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> may be executed in any number of separate counterparts and this has the same effect as if the signatures on those counterparts were on a single copy of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf7d32354-9a69-4d8c-8ea1-8c8f8589cc98' opt-key='opt-N81044'><div><p>Each Party may evidence their execution of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> <em opt-key='opt-N81055'>by faxing or</em> by emailing an executed signature page of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> in PDF format together with the final version of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> in PDF or Word format, which shall constitute an original executed counterpart of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>. Each Party adopting this method of execution will, following circulation <em opt-key='opt-N81071'>by fax or</em> by email, provide the original, hard copy executed signature page to the other Party as soon as reasonably practicable.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem20a31ffd-8952-4d76-a285-b6bbd82da4c2'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6' type='clause'/>&#8212;Counterparts</p><div><p>A counterparts clause is a common boilerplate clause which provides that the parties to an agreement may execute separate copies of it, rather than all parties having to sign the same copy of the agreement. It is common practice to sign an agreement in counterparts, and this mechanism can be particularly useful where there are a large number of parties, or where the parties are located in different regions or countries and will be unable to hold a physical completion meeting.</p></div><div><p>If an agreement does not contain a counterparts clause, the parties will not be prevented from executing a document in counterpart. However, using a counterparts clause is advisable for certainty, and to prevent any argument that the agreement is not binding because it has not been properly executed.</p></div><div><p>The counterparts clause commonly consists of:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>a statement that the document may be executed in counterparts, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>a sub-clause dealing with virtual signing (ie circulating the signature pages by email)</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The difference between original counterparts and original duplicates should be noted here. If all the parties sign a number of copies of the agreement, each copy is an original duplicate rather than a counterpart, and the counterparts clause will not be applicable.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Re Mercury Tax [2008] All ER (D) 129 (Nov)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The <em class='it'>Mercury Tax</em> case considered the effectiveness of pre-signed signature pages and virtual signings and closings where signature pages are exchanged by email (<em class='it'>Re Mercury Tax</em> [2008] All ER (D) 129 (Nov)). Following this case, the Law Society issued guidance on good practice for virtual signings (<a class='http' href='www.lawsociety.org.uk/support-services/advice/practice-notes/execution-of-documents-by-virtual-means/'>Law Society Guidance: Execution of documents by virtual means</a>).</p></div><div><p>The Law Society guidance sets out three options for the virtual signing of an agreement or deed. Agreements that are to be executed as a deed should follow option 1 of the guidance.</p></div><div><p>The Law Society recommends that all parties&#8217; lawyers agree to the proposed arrangements for the virtual signing/closing well in advance of execution. For this reason, it has become common practice to include specific drafting on virtual signings in the counterparts clause (see Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf7d32354-9a69-4d8c-8ea1-8c8f8589cc98' type='clause'/>).</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 1</em> gives guidance on circulating the entire document and the signed signature page by email. This method is suitable for both deeds and simple contracts. The detailed requirements for option 1 are as follows:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>execution copies of the documents are emailed as PDF or Word attachments to all parties that will be absent and/or their lawyers (as agreed); the signature page may be emailed as a separate PDF or Word document, for convenience</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent signatory then prints and signs the signature page only (there is no need to print off the full document)</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent party then returns a single email to their lawyer or to the lawyers coordinating signing/closing as agreed and attaches <em class='it'>both</em> the final version of the PDF or Word agreement and a PDF copy of the signed signature page, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>at or shortly after signing/closing, the parties may wish to evidence the execution by one of the law firms circulating a final version of the document together with copies of executed signature pages</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The Law Society guidance confirms that, for option 1, the PDF or Word final version of the document and the PDF of the signed signature page will constitute an original signed document and each counterpart taken together will equate to the same physical document.</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 2</em> allows the parties to circulate the signature page by email, without a copy of the final agreement (so is slightly less burdensome than option 1). This method is only suitable for simple contracts (not deeds).</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 3</em> allows the parties to sign and circulate the signature pages in advance of finalising a document. This method is only suitable for simple contracts (not deeds).</p></div><div><p>For further information on signing see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OJE_145100'>Virtual execution of documents</a>.</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf7d32354-9a69-4d8c-8ea1-8c8f8589cc98' type='clause'/></em></p></div><div><p>It has become common practice to have a sub-clause within the counterparts clause which deals with virtual signing (ie the circulation of signature pages by email or fax) following the <em class='it'>Mercury Tax</em> case and subsequent Law Society guidance. The entire sub-clause can be deleted if the parties are not intending to circulate signature pages electronically.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:1CBC029A-6D56-4733-B23E-3683C3D88593'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D13E6352345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D13E6352345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the deed. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:1CBC029A-6D56-4733-B23E-3683C3D88593'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the deed and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:41AAE84A-3CB2-4474-87AA-8150C65EA23B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><!--CM note to self: inserted boilerplate--><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D69E37802345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E37802345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:41AAE84A-3CB2-4474-87AA-8150C65EA23B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><!--CM note to self: inserted boilerplate--><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting <b>party</b>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>Remember that clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem157b57b2-85a4-4dde-acf7-f4f4bcab2934' type='clause'/> also contains some further assurances on the part of the licensor. Make sure that the clauses are consistent.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:41AAE84A-3CB2-4474-87AA-8150C65EA23B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><!--CM note to self: inserted boilerplate--><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b><em opt-key='opt-N66047'> and <em alt-key='alt-D69E3358022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E3358022'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b><em opt-key='opt-N66098'> or <em alt-key='alt-D69E3373023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E3373023'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b><em opt-key='opt-N66116'> or <em alt-key='alt-D69E3384024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E3384024'><em type='text'>insert names of specified documents</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:41AAE84A-3CB2-4474-87AA-8150C65EA23B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><!--CM note to self: inserted boilerplate--><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D69E34190020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E34190020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> (or to the fax number<em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'> or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemcf966a48-118d-47ea-86a7-0a6c940eef93'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D69E34790021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E34790021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:41AAE84A-3CB2-4474-87AA-8150C65EA23B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><!--CM note to self: inserted boilerplate--><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid if any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:41AAE84A-3CB2-4474-87AA-8150C65EA23B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><!--CM note to self: inserted boilerplate--><div><p><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D69E35990001'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, each</em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D69E35990001'>Each</em> <b>party</b> shall pay all sums that it owes to the other <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:41AAE84A-3CB2-4474-87AA-8150C65EA23B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><!--CM note to self: inserted boilerplate--><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b>. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D69E25200001'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E25200001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:41AAE84A-3CB2-4474-87AA-8150C65EA23B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><!--CM note to self: inserted boilerplate--><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:41AAE84A-3CB2-4474-87AA-8150C65EA23B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><!--CM note to self: inserted boilerplate--><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:41AAE84A-3CB2-4474-87AA-8150C65EA23B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><!--CM note to self: inserted boilerplate--><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:41AAE84A-3CB2-4474-87AA-8150C65EA23B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><!--CM note to self: inserted boilerplate--></lnb-prec:title><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34327125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:70E8B5ED-B8EC-4607-AA6C-B77E4345E9C8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation <em opt-key='opt-N65620'>(including non-contractual disputes or claims)</em> shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1490085952-34560125'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause provides that the agreement and certain disputes and claims shall governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales, although a reference to another substantive law may be inserted instead.</p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217; and this wording can been made narrower if that is preferred. However, consideration should then be given as to the law that will govern any such disputes or claims that do not fall within the scope of the clause.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='http' href='eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=celex:32007R0864'>Rome II, arts 4 and 14</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The words &#8216;[(including non-contractual disputes or claims)]&#8217; may be included for the purpose of Rome II, which sets out the rules used to determine the governing law for non-contractual claims. However, parties pursuing a commercial activity can specify the governing law that will apply to their non-contractual obligations at any time before an event giving rise to damage occurs, save that such governing law cannot prevent the application of:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>any laws of the country in which all of the elements relevant to the situation are located when the event occurs (if it is not the country whose law has been chosen), if those laws cannot be derogated from by agreement, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>European Community law that cannot be derogated from by agreement, if all of the elements relevant to the situation are located in one or more EU member states when the event occurs and the law that has been chosen is not that of an EU member state</p></div></li></ul><div><p>In the absence of the phrase &#8216;[(including non-contractual disputes or claims)]&#8217; the wording of this clause may be wide enough in its scope to catch non-contractual claims relating to the agreement, its subject matter or formation. However, these words are a helpful addition to provide certainty to the parties.</p></div><div><p>If the intention of the parties is to restrict the governing law clause only to contractual claims, the wording of the clause should be amended to refer only to disputes or claims arising under the agreement, eg:</p></div><div><p>&#8216;This agreement and any dispute or claim arising under it shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of [England and Wales/insert details of alternative governing law].&#8217;</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34828125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:70E8B5ED-B8EC-4607-AA6C-B77E4345E9C8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales have exclusive jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation <em opt-key='opt-N65640'>(including non-contractual disputes or claims)</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem6a4733a3-5990-4eba-b100-19fe125ff259'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This clause provides that the courts of England and Wales shall have jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, the agreement. </p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217; and this wording can been made narrower if that is preferred. However, consideration should then be given as to the courts that will have jurisdiction to settle any such disputes or claims, which do not fall within the scope of the clause.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Fiona Trust v Privalov and others [2007] All ER (D) 233 (Oct) </a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>UBS AG v HSH Nordbank AG [2009] EWCA Civ 585, para 82</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The inclusion of the wording 'arise out of, or in connection with' and similar terms in a jurisdiction clause used to cause difficulties as to exactly what type of disputes were brought within its scope. The House of Lords has, in an arbitration case, upheld a wide interpretation of these words. This was on the assumption that the parties, as rational businessmen, were likely to have intended <em class='it'>any</em> dispute arising out of their relationship to be decided by the tribunal referred to in the relevant clause. The wording was held to be so wide as to cover claims arising before inception of the relevant agreement, such as misrepresentation. This wide interpretation has subsequently been followed in a number of litigation cases.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Fiona Trust v Privalov and others [2007] All ER (D) 233 (Oct)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The words &#8216;[(including non-contractual disputes or claims)]&#8217; may be included if the same wording is included in the agreement&#8217;s governing law clause for the purpose of Rome II. However, following the decision in the <em class='it'>Fiona Trust</em> case, such wording is not strictly necessary.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PLANNING::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34327125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:B6384499-2BDC-4533-9011-2A4C6ED55351'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation <em opt-key='opt-N65620'>(including non-contractual disputes or claims)</em> shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1490085952-34560125'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause provides that the agreement and certain disputes and claims shall governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales, although a reference to another substantive law may be inserted instead.</p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217; and this wording can been made narrower if that is preferred. However, consideration should then be given as to the law that will govern any such disputes or claims that do not fall within the scope of the clause.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='http' href='eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri=celex:32007R0864'>Rome II, arts 4 and 14</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The words &#8216;[(including non-contractual disputes or claims)]&#8217; may be included for the purpose of Rome II, which sets out the rules used to determine the governing law for non-contractual claims. However, parties pursuing a commercial activity can specify the governing law that will apply to their non-contractual obligations at any time before an event giving rise to damage occurs, save that such governing law cannot prevent the application of:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>any laws of the country in which all of the elements relevant to the situation are located when the event occurs (if it is not the country whose law has been chosen), if those laws cannot be derogated from by agreement, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>European Community law that cannot be derogated from by agreement, if all of the elements relevant to the situation are located in one or more EU member states when the event occurs and the law that has been chosen is not that of an EU member state</p></div></li></ul><div><p>In the absence of the phrase &#8216;[(including non-contractual disputes or claims)]&#8217; the wording of this clause may be wide enough in its scope to catch non-contractual claims relating to the agreement, its subject matter or formation. However, these words are a helpful addition to provide certainty to the parties.</p></div><div><p>If the intention of the parties is to restrict the governing law clause only to contractual claims, the wording of the clause should be amended to refer only to disputes or claims arising under the agreement, eg:</p></div><div><p><em class='it'>&#8216;This agreement and any dispute or claim arising under it shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of [England and Wales/insert details of alternative governing law].&#8217;</em></p></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PLANNING::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34097125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:B6384499-2BDC-4533-9011-2A4C6ED55351'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125'><p class='main_heading'>Joint and several liability</p><div><p>Where the <lnb-prec:party>Tenant</lnb-prec:party> is more than one person, the <lnb-prec:party>Landlord</lnb-prec:party> may release or compromise the liability of any of those persons under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or grant time or other indulgence without affecting the liability of any other of them.</p></div></div>"}, {PA: "PLANNING::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34828125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:B6384499-2BDC-4533-9011-2A4C6ED55351'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have exclusive jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation<em opt-key='opt-N65640'> (including non-contractual disputes or claims)</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem6a4733a3-5990-4eba-b100-19fe125ff259'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This clause provides that the courts of England and Wales shall have jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, the agreement. </p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217; and this wording can been made narrower if that is preferred. However, consideration should then be given as to the courts that will have jurisdiction to settle any such disputes or claims, which do not fall within the scope of the clause.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Fiona Trust v Privalov and others [2007] All ER (D) 233 (Oct) </a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>UBS AG v HSH Nordbank AG [2009] EWCA Civ 585, para 82</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The inclusion of the wording 'arise out of, or in connection with' and similar terms in a jurisdiction clause used to cause difficulties as to exactly what type of disputes were brought within its scope. The House of Lords has, in an arbitration case, upheld a wide interpretation of these words. This was on the assumption that the parties, as rational businessmen, were likely to have intended <em class='it'>any</em> dispute arising out of their relationship to be decided by the tribunal referred to in the relevant clause. The wording was held to be so wide as to cover claims arising before inception of the relevant agreement, such as misrepresentation. This wide interpretation has subsequently been followed in a number of litigation cases.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Fiona Trust v Privalov and others [2007] All ER (D) 233 (Oct)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The words &#8216;[(including non-contractual disputes or claims)]&#8217; may be included if the same wording is included in the agreement&#8217;s governing law clause for the purpose of Rome II. However, following the decision in the <em class='it'>Fiona Trust</em> case, such wording is not strictly necessary.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DE646AF1-B83E-4354-98CE-37FB093BA497'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>party</b> without the prior written consent of the other <b>party</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DE646AF1-B83E-4354-98CE-37FB093BA497'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DE646AF1-B83E-4354-98CE-37FB093BA497'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Transfer of rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No party may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent <em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a party may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other party&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>. Each party acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b> in relation to that party&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that party itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Transfer of rights</p><div><p>This transfer of rights clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. Note that this provision will need to be amended if the licence grant at clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem2666d6e4-bd96-42d9-8a91-01bf3a249089' type='clause'/> provides that the licence may be freely transferable and/or sublicenseable. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>. </p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DE646AF1-B83E-4354-98CE-37FB093BA497'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DE646AF1-B83E-4354-98CE-37FB093BA497'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D65E29000020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D65E29000020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> days after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> days after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;<em opt-key='opt-5BB2F125'> and</em></p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report<em alt-key='alt-5BB2D645'>; and</em><em alt-key='alt-5BB2D645'>.</em></p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-4C4D4963'><div><p>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D65E29530021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D65E29530021'>read</em> return email.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DE646AF1-B83E-4354-98CE-37FB093BA497'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DE646AF1-B83E-4354-98CE-37FB093BA497'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D65E2841022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D65E2841022'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> constitute<em opt-key='opt-05A309BC'>s</em> the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D65E2856023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D65E2856023'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D65E2867024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D65E2867024'><em type='text'>insert name of specified document</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DE646AF1-B83E-4354-98CE-37FB093BA497'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a party to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, <em opt-key='opt-N65821'>their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D69E37802345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E37802345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D69E3358022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E3358022'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D69E3373023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E3373023'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D69E3384024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E3384024'><em type='text'>insert names of specified documents</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' opt-key='opt-A0AE1DC4'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting <b>party</b>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. Consider this provision in line with the licensor&#8217;s obligations in clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem869b4f0a-a087-451a-a1be-f7a19c9bc1ba' type='clause'/>. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;<b>party</b>&#8217; includes that <b>party</b>&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-key='alt-D69E5050009' alt-connector='or'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b></em><em alt-key='alt-D69E5050009' alt-connector='or'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/></p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D69E34190020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E34190020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemcf966a48-118d-47ea-86a7-0a6c940eef93'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D69E34790021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E34790021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p><em alt-key='alt-D69E35990001' alt-connector='or'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, each</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E35990001' alt-connector='or'>Each</em> <b>party</b> shall pay all sums that it owes to the other <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the <b>parties</b> out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each <b>party</b> who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the <b>parties</b> <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either <b>party</b> may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the <b>parties</b> have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither <b>party</b> shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either <b>party</b> may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>The parties should decide how any disputes under the agreement should be dealt with.</p></div><div><p>It is usually appropriate to take a graduated approach&#8212;eg initially using reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation.</p></div><div><p>The parties should consider what their objectives are when agreeing a dispute resolution mechanism&#8212;eg arbitration might be appropriate if confidentiality is the key consideration, but court proceedings might prove less expensive and be follow more familiar procedures.</p></div><div><p>For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>For more information about alternative dispute resolution, see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0ONJ_166446'>Types of dispute resolution</a>, <a normcite='0ONJ_173056'>IP and mediation</a> and <a normcite='0ONJ_3421594'>IP and arbitration</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b>. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D69E25200001'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E25200001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DACF5B9B-C926-4219-90BA-99030CCC8DBD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid if any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D64E37452345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E37452345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' opt-key='opt-A119F40A'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting <b>party</b>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. Consider this provision in line with the licensor&#8217;s obligations in clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem869b4f0a-a087-451a-a1be-f7a19c9bc1ba' type='clause'/>. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b><em opt-key='opt-N66047'> and <em alt-key='alt-D64E3324022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E3324022'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D64E3339023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E3339023'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D64E3350024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E3350024'><em type='text'>insert names of specified documents</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>,<em opt-key='opt-N65821'> their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid if any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p><em alt-key='alt-D64E35650001' alt-connector='or'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, each</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E35650001' alt-connector='or'>Each</em> <b>party</b> shall pay all sums that it owes to the other <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the <b>parties</b> out of or in connection with this <b>Licence</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each <b>party</b> who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the parties <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either <b>party</b> may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the <b>parties</b> have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither party shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either party may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>The parties should decide how any disputes under the agreement should be dealt with.</p></div><div><p>It is usually appropriate to take a graduated approach&#8212;eg initially using reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation.</p></div><div><p>The parties should consider what their objectives are when agreeing a dispute resolution mechanism&#8212;eg arbitration might be appropriate if confidentiality is the key consideration, but court proceedings might prove less expensive and follow more familiar procedures.</p></div><div><p>For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>For more information about alternative dispute resolution, see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0ONJ_166446'>Types of dispute resolution</a>, <a normcite='0ONJ_173056'>IP and mediation</a> and <a normcite='0ONJ_3421594'>IP and arbitration</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b>. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D64E25500001'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E25500001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the parties nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CB68267C-2E7E-4B1A-B82F-1D405A93C0CA'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D64E33840020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E33840020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem63b756a3-539d-46ad-a1bb-e85f071e31fb'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-51DEDAD8'><div><p><em>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D64E34440021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E34440021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FFE511B1-768C-4E25-B3D5-4C6A4F4D3A8B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a party to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FFE511B1-768C-4E25-B3D5-4C6A4F4D3A8B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D78E1050022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D78E1050022'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D78E1065023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D78E1065023'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D78E1076024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D78E1076024'><em type='text'>insert name of specified document</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.<!--Added Entire agreement--></p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FFE511B1-768C-4E25-B3D5-4C6A4F4D3A8B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FFE511B1-768C-4E25-B3D5-4C6A4F4D3A8B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's <em alt-key='alt-D78E11100020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D78E11100020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-4C270E2E'><div><p>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D78E11690021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D78E11690021'>read</em> return email.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed Drafting Notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FFE511B1-768C-4E25-B3D5-4C6A4F4D3A8B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FFE511B1-768C-4E25-B3D5-4C6A4F4D3A8B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Transfer of rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No party may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent <em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a party may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other party&#160;prior&#160;written notice, including the identity of the relevant <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>. Each party acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b> in relation to that party&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that party itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Transfer of rights</p><div><p>This transfer of rights clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FFE511B1-768C-4E25-B3D5-4C6A4F4D3A8B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FFE511B1-768C-4E25-B3D5-4C6A4F4D3A8B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FF74D6EB-30BC-4E94-9E31-5D0CB9C4019F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FF74D6EB-30BC-4E94-9E31-5D0CB9C4019F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Transfer of rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No party may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a party may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> through any <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other party&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>. Each party acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b> in relation to that party&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that party itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Transfer of rights</p><div><p>This transfer of rights clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>. </p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FF74D6EB-30BC-4E94-9E31-5D0CB9C4019F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a party to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FF74D6EB-30BC-4E94-9E31-5D0CB9C4019F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D80E1217022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D80E1217022'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D80E1232023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D80E1232023'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D80E1243024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D80E1243024'><em type='text'>insert name of specified document</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FF74D6EB-30BC-4E94-9E31-5D0CB9C4019F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FF74D6EB-30BC-4E94-9E31-5D0CB9C4019F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D80E12770020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D80E12770020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-53671C4E'><div><p>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D80E13360021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D80E13360021'>read</em> return email.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FF74D6EB-30BC-4E94-9E31-5D0CB9C4019F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FF74D6EB-30BC-4E94-9E31-5D0CB9C4019F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from <b>Force Majeure</b>. The <b>party</b> subject to the <b>Force Majeure</b> event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such the event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If the event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D5E50920001'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D5E50920001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, in the event of Force Majeure. See clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemd7ce4350-1c1e-4d0e-a9a6-8a41ffb71616' type='clause'/> for the definition. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>party</b> without the prior written consent of the other <b>party</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D5E54162345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D5E54162345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D5E52530001'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, each</em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D5E52530001'>Each</em> <b>party</b> must pay all sums that it owes to the other <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D5E49600020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D5E49600020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on <b>Delivery</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850ccc'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D5E50200021'><b>Delivery</b></em><em alt-key='alt-D5E50200021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting <b>party</b>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D5E4901022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D5E4901022'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D5E4916023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D5E4916023'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D5E4927024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D5E4927024'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specified document[s]</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem541c12d2-6e32-4613-8eb3-2b581ac4ec59'><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem77cc4d8e-cd6d-48cc-adfc-d2404eafd529' type='clause'/>, no one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, <em opt-key='opt-N65821'>their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem77cc4d8e-cd6d-48cc-adfc-d2404eafd529'><div><p>The <b>Affiliate</b>s of the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> shall have the right to enforce the provisions of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the <b>parties</b> out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each <b>party</b> who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='number'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the <b>parties</b> <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either <b>party</b> may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the <b>parties</b> have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither <b>party</b> shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either <b>party</b> may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause requires the parties to use reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:6B665574-CBDF-4A52-A9B4-11B68D67657F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554' type='clause'/>, the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> may not assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. The <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b>Affiliate</b> in relation to the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This assignment clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:83971BFB-29F3-4A14-85BC-E2FDEAF3C012'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b><em opt-key='opt-N66047'> and <em alt-key='alt-D82E1396022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D82E1396022'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> constitute<em opt-key='opt-1EDA16AA'>s</em> the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b><em opt-key='opt-N66098'> or <em alt-key='alt-D82E1411023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D82E1411023'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b><em opt-key='opt-N66116'> or <em alt-key='alt-D82E1422024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D82E1422024'><em type='text'>insert name of specified document</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:83971BFB-29F3-4A14-85BC-E2FDEAF3C012'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:83971BFB-29F3-4A14-85BC-E2FDEAF3C012'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'> their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This third party rights clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:83971BFB-29F3-4A14-85BC-E2FDEAF3C012'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:83971BFB-29F3-4A14-85BC-E2FDEAF3C012'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Transfer of rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No <b>party</b> may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a <b>party</b> may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> through any <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other <b>party</b>&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>. Each <b>party</b> acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b> in relation to that <b>party</b>&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that <b>party</b> itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Transfer of rights</p><div><p>This transfer of rights clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>. </p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:83971BFB-29F3-4A14-85BC-E2FDEAF3C012'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;<b>party</b>&#8217; includes that <b>party</b>&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D82E5380009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D82E5380009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time<em opt-key='opt-N67007'> except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:83971BFB-29F3-4A14-85BC-E2FDEAF3C012'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:83971BFB-29F3-4A14-85BC-E2FDEAF3C012'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>party</b> without the prior written consent of the other <b>party</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:83971BFB-29F3-4A14-85BC-E2FDEAF3C012'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D82E14550020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D82E14550020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> (or to the fax number<em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'> or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-20CE0F79'><div><p>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D82E15150021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D82E15150021'>read</em> return email.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FD699CD2-2764-4B75-B77A-8B1D0EBBDBF8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FD699CD2-2764-4B75-B77A-8B1D0EBBDBF8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;party&#8217; includes that party&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D84E5130009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D84E5130009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FD699CD2-2764-4B75-B77A-8B1D0EBBDBF8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FD699CD2-2764-4B75-B77A-8B1D0EBBDBF8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a party to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FD699CD2-2764-4B75-B77A-8B1D0EBBDBF8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FD699CD2-2764-4B75-B77A-8B1D0EBBDBF8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FD699CD2-2764-4B75-B77A-8B1D0EBBDBF8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D84E13450020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D84E13450020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b class='referring'>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D84E14050021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D84E14050021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FD699CD2-2764-4B75-B77A-8B1D0EBBDBF8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Transfer of rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No party may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a party may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other party&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>. Each party acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b> in relation to that party&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that party itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Transfer of rights</p><div><p>This transfer of rights clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FD699CD2-2764-4B75-B77A-8B1D0EBBDBF8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D84E1286022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D84E1286022'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D84E1301023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D84E1301023'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D84E1312024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D84E1312024'><em type='text'>insert name of specified document</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D11E46262345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E46262345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb0431571-62fe-48ab-a86f-c3db99f9056d'><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem6f56f675-e0c8-4b54-a48a-3f81d5f80a31' type='clause'/>, no one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>,<em opt-key='opt-N65821'> their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6f56f675-e0c8-4b54-a48a-3f81d5f80a31'><div><p>The <b>Affiliate</b>s of the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> shall have the right to enforce the provisions of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D11E4131022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E4131022'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D11E4146023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E4146023'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D11E4157024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E4157024'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specified document[s]</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> without the prior written consent of the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party><em opt-key='opt-F31C87E8'> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure by the supplier of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from <b>Force Majeure</b>. The <b>party</b> subject to the <b>Force Majeure</b> event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such the event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If the event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D11E43240001'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E43240001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, in the event of force majeure. See clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme9424c1d-d92d-4979-95e1-de57eea39b56' type='clause'/> for the definition. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> may not assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s prior written consent<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554' opt-key='opt-897247F2'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party>&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. The <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b>Affiliate</b> in relation to its rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This assignment clause governs the extent to which the supplier&#8217;s rights and obligations may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the <b>parties</b> out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each <b>party</b> who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the <b>parties</b> <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'> may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either <b>party</b> may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the <b>parties</b> have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither <b>party</b> shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either <b>party</b> may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause requires the parties to use reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>For the effect of the term &#8216;reasonable endeavours&#8217; see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OJE_29710'>Reasonable and best endeavours</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D11E41900020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E41900020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number<em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'> or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850ccc'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D11E42500021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E42500021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting <em><b>party</b></em>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3C460C8-247F-4232-8EC5-0E6445B43305'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' opt-key='opt-F31CD58D'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D11E44640001'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, each</em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D11E44640001'>Each</em> <b>party</b> must pay all sums that it owes to the other <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:66196FD6-A8AE-4ABD-AF65-3B179F87A261'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply with all laws, enactments, regulations, regulatory policies, guidelines and industry codes applicable to them and shall maintain such authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform their obligations under or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "BANKINGANDFINANCE", id: "ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:DA404894-9B2B-44E7-863B-CD35BBD2BA5A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6'><p class='main_heading'>Counterparts</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemcace7bfe-e8c6-4fb8-aa54-a0afc1f84b7a'><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> may be executed in any number of separate counterparts and this has the same effect as if the signatures on those counterparts were on a single copy of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf7d32354-9a69-4d8c-8ea1-8c8f8589cc98' opt-key='opt-N74125'><div><p>Each <b>Party</b> may evidence their execution of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> <em opt-key='opt-N74139'>by faxing or</em> by emailing an executed signature page of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> in PDF format together with the final version of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> in PDF or Word format, which shall constitute an original executed counterpart of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>. Each <b>Party</b> adopting this method of execution will, following circulation <em opt-key='opt-N74158'>by fax or</em> by email, provide the original, hard copy executed signature page to the other Party as soon as reasonably practicable.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem20a31ffd-8952-4d76-a285-b6bbd82da4c2'><p class='main_heading'>Clause 35&#8212;Counterparts</p><div><p>A counterparts clause is a common boilerplate clause which provides that the parties to an agreement may execute separate copies of it, rather than all parties having to sign the same copy of the agreement. It is common practice to sign an agreement in counterparts, and this mechanism can be particularly useful where there are a large number of parties, or where the parties are located in different regions or countries and will be unable to hold a physical completion meeting.</p></div><div><p>If an agreement does not contain a counterparts clause, the parties will not be prevented from executing a document in counterpart. However, using a counterparts clause is advisable for certainty, and to prevent any argument that the agreement is not binding because it has not been properly executed.</p></div><div><p>The counterparts clause commonly consists of:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>a statement that the document may be executed in counterparts, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>a sub-clause dealing with virtual signing (ie circulating the signature pages by email)</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The difference between original counterparts and original duplicates should be noted here. If all the parties sign a number of copies of the agreement, each copy is an original duplicate rather than a counterpart, and the counterparts clause will not be applicable.</p></div><div><p>The <em class='it'>Mercury Tax</em> case considered the effectiveness of pre-signed signature pages and virtual signings and closings where signature pages are exchanged by email (<a>Re Mercury Tax [2008] All ER (D) 129 (Nov)</a>). Following this case, the Law Society issued guidance on good practice for virtual signings (<a class='http' href='www.lawsociety.org.uk/support-services/advice/practice-notes/execution-of-documents-by-virtual-means/'>Law Society Guidance: Execution of documents by virtual means</a>).</p></div><div><p>The Law Society guidance sets out three options for the virtual signing of an agreement or deed. Agreements that are to be executed as a deed should follow option 1 of the guidance.</p></div><div><p>The Law Society recommends that all parties&#8217; lawyers agree to the proposed arrangements for the virtual signing/closing well in advance of execution. For this reason, it has become common practice to include specific drafting on virtual signings in the counterparts clause (see Clause 35.2).</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 1</em> gives guidance on circulating the entire document and the signed signature page by email. This method is suitable for both deeds and simple contracts. The detailed requirements for option 1 are as follows:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>execution copies of the documents are emailed as PDF or Word attachments to all parties that will be absent and/or their lawyers (as agreed); the signature page may be emailed as a separate PDF or Word document, for convenience</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent signatory then prints and signs the signature page only (there is no need to print off the full document)</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent party then returns a single email to their lawyer or to the lawyers coordinating signing/closing as agreed and attaches <em class='it'>both</em> the final version of the PDF or Word agreement and a PDF copy of the signed signature page, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>at or shortly after signing/closing, the parties may wish to evidence the execution by one of the law firms circulating a final version of the document together with copies of executed signature pages</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The Law Society guidance confirms that, for option 1, the PDF or Word final version of the document and the PDF of the signed signature page will constitute an original signed document and each counterpart taken together will equate to the same physical document.</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 2</em> allows the parties to circulate the signature page by email, without a copy of the final agreement (so is slightly less burdensome than option 1). This method is only suitable for simple contracts (not deeds).</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 3</em> allows the parties to sign and circulate the signature pages in advance of finalising a document. This method is only suitable for simple contracts (not deeds).</p></div><div><p>For further information on signing see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OJE_145100'>Virtual execution of documents</a>.</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Clause 35.2</em></p><!--A?Q: there is no clause 38.2 in this precdent?--></div><div><p>It has become common practice to have a sub-clause within the counterparts clause which deals with virtual signing (ie the circulation of signature pages by email or fax) following the Mercury Tax case and subsequent Law Society guidance. The entire sub-clause can be deleted if the parties are not intending to circulate signature pages electronically.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "BANKINGANDFINANCE", id: "ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:12856B3D-7242-419C-92DB-C59045CC3962'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6'><p class='main_heading'>Counterparts</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemd5a7d49c-c40b-4248-9948-662e7ef95291'><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> may be executed in any number of separate counterparts and this has the same effect as if the signatures on those counterparts were on a single copy of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem5928381b-c19b-4e5f-9d8c-438e6dde396e' opt-key='opt-N81044'><div><p>Each Party may evidence their execution of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> <em opt-key='opt-N81055'>by faxing or</em> by emailing an executed signature page of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> in PDF format together with the final version of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> in PDF or Word format, which shall constitute an original executed counterpart of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>. Each Party adopting this method of execution will, following circulation <em opt-key='opt-N81071'>by fax or</em> by email, provide the original, hard copy executed signature page to the other Party as soon as reasonably practicable.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem20a31ffd-8952-4d76-a285-b6bbd82da4c2'><p class='main_heading'>Clause 40&#8212;Counterparts</p><div><p>A counterparts clause is a common boilerplate clause which provides that the parties to an agreement may execute separate copies of it, rather than all parties having to sign the same copy of the agreement. It is common practice to sign an agreement in counterparts, and this mechanism can be particularly useful where there are a large number of parties, or where the parties are located in different regions or countries and will be unable to hold a physical completion meeting.</p></div><div><p>If an agreement does not contain a counterparts clause, the parties will not be prevented from executing a document in counterpart. However, using a counterparts clause is advisable for certainty, and to prevent any argument that the agreement is not binding because it has not been properly executed.</p></div><div><p>The counterparts clause commonly consists of:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>a statement that the document may be executed in counterparts, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>a sub-clause dealing with virtual signing (ie circulating the signature pages by email)</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The difference between original counterparts and original duplicates should be noted here. If all the parties sign a number of copies of the agreement, each copy is an original duplicate rather than a counterpart, and the counterparts clause will not be applicable.</p></div><div><p>The <em class='it'>Mercury Tax</em> case considered the effectiveness of pre-signed signature pages and virtual signings and closings where signature pages are exchanged by email (<em class='it'>Re Mercury Tax</em> [2008] All ER (D) 129 (Nov)). Following this case, the Law Society issued guidance on good practice for virtual signings (<a class='http' href='www.lawsociety.org.uk/support-services/advice/practice-notes/execution-of-documents-by-virtual-means/'>Law Society Guidance: Execution of documents by virtual means</a>).</p></div><div><p>The Law Society guidance sets out three options for the virtual signing of an agreement or deed. Agreements that are to be executed as a deed should follow option 1 of the guidance.</p></div><div><p>The Law Society recommends that all parties&#8217; lawyers agree to the proposed arrangements for the virtual signing/closing well in advance of execution. For this reason, it has become common practice to include specific drafting on virtual signings in the counterparts clause (see Clause 40.2).</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 1</em> gives guidance on circulating the entire document and the signed signature page by email. This method is suitable for both deeds and simple contracts. The detailed requirements for option 1 are as follows:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>execution copies of the documents are emailed as PDF or Word attachments to all parties that will be absent and/or their lawyers (as agreed); the signature page may be emailed as a separate PDF or Word document, for convenience</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent signatory then prints and signs the signature page only (there is no need to print off the full document)</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent party then returns a single email to their lawyer or to the lawyers coordinating signing/closing as agreed and attaches <em class='it'>both</em> the final version of the PDF or Word agreement and a PDF copy of the signed signature page, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>at or shortly after signing/closing, the parties may wish to evidence the execution by one of the law firms circulating a final version of the document together with copies of executed signature pages</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The Law Society guidance confirms that, for option 1, the PDF or Word final version of the document and the PDF of the signed signature page will constitute an original signed document and each counterpart taken together will equate to the same physical document.</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 2</em> allows the parties to circulate the signature page by email, without a copy of the final agreement (so is slightly less burdensome than option 1). This method is only suitable for simple contracts (not deeds).</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 3</em> allows the parties to sign and circulate the signature pages in advance of finalising a document. This method is only suitable for simple contracts (not deeds).</p></div><div><p>For further information on signing see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OJE_145100'>Virtual execution of documents</a>.</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Clause 40.2</em></p></div><div><p>It has become common practice to have a sub-clause within the counterparts clause which deals with virtual signing (ie the circulation of signature pages by email or fax) following the Mercury Tax case and subsequent Law Society guidance. The entire sub-clause can be deleted if the parties are not intending to circulate signature pages electronically.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CAFAC412-F40E-40C3-9B21-30761872592D'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each party shall comply with all laws, enactments, regulations, regulatory policies, guidelines and industry codes applicable to them and shall maintain such authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform their obligations under or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E5020001'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, each</em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E5020001'>Each</em> party shall pay all sums that it owes to the other party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;party&#8217; includes that party&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p> a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p> words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow 'include', 'includes', 'including', &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E800009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E800009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time<em opt-key='opt-N67007'> except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's <em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-D6B72BC2'><div><p>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>read receipt</em> email.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the parties nor make any party the agent of another party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a party to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the parties out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each party who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the parties <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'> may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either party may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'> Until the parties have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither party shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either party may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause requires the parties to use reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No party may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a party may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other party&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. Each party acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b>Affiliate</b> in relation to that party&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that party itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This assignment clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>. A definition of Affiliate should be added to the definitions section of the agreement. See Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_188755'>Affiliate definition</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N66047'> and <em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'><em type='text'>insert name(s) of specific document(s)</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N66098'> or <em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'><em type='text'>insert name(s) of specific document(s)</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N66116'> or <em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'><em type='text'>insert name(s) of specified document(s)</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each party shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting party, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither party shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that party. The party affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other party in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>the party not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>either party</em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A8061E9-E900-4905-9AAA-893DAA4362D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>, the parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. The optional wording should be included where the agreement contains a dispute resolution clause preventing the parties from issuing court proceedings until the chosen form of dispute resolution procedure has been concluded without success. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:CF115CA5-5369-48B5-BE6F-B584256DD803'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>The <b>Supplier</b> shall comply with <b>Applicable Law</b> and shall maintain such licences, authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform its obligations under or in connection with the <b class='document-class'>Contract</b>. </p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on the supplier to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. Optional wording is included that is more favourable to the supplier so that the supplier is not liable if the breach arises because of something done by the customer. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:A65C0E8C-F095-4FD0-97BA-D72CBD41B18A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>The <b>Supplier</b> shall comply with <b>Applicable Law</b> and shall maintain such licences, authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform its obligations under or in connection with the <b>Contract</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on the supplier to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4B6AB514-4E2A-43F6-AC29-BB75F51DB12A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>The <b>Supplier</b> shall comply with <b>Applicable Law</b> and shall maintain such licences, authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform its obligations under or in connection with the <b class='document-class'>Contract</b>. </p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on the supplier to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. Optional wording is included that is more favourable to the supplier so that the supplier is not liable if the breach arises because of something done by the customer. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4B9636EC-D658-44D3-BA41-FF358FC5FF3E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D8E1865022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D8E1865022'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D8E1880023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D8E1880023'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D8E1891024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D8E1891024'><em type='text'>insert name of specified document</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4B9636EC-D658-44D3-BA41-FF358FC5FF3E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4B9636EC-D658-44D3-BA41-FF358FC5FF3E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4B9636EC-D658-44D3-BA41-FF358FC5FF3E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4B9636EC-D658-44D3-BA41-FF358FC5FF3E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4B9636EC-D658-44D3-BA41-FF358FC5FF3E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D8E20750020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D8E20750020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem22153a00-e1f0-4137-9c40-1df2fe099c85'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='name'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='name'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-4FA933AC'><div><p><em>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='name'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='name'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D8E21350021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D8E21350021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1559215484-27162225'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' type='clause'/></p><div><p>If this optional clause is retained then clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' type='clause'/> should be deleted.</p></div></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4B9636EC-D658-44D3-BA41-FF358FC5FF3E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem2c29fee2-ea8a-4736-8e6e-ee93175f28b0'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> includes its schedules;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemec826d64-c0e4-45a9-b25e-764c3ab52e86'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and the clause, paragraph, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on interpretation;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemebd8b96f-e391-4781-bc5e-ae3ca772ba78'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;<b>party</b>&#8217; includes that <b>party</b>&#8217;s successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem2cb88af1-44a0-4c13-a4db-c9a82447e9ef'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem3a2241aa-f9b2-46af-a640-b87e7f330e35'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemb2d605f7-a4b8-40c0-b68c-5f17a5db80eb'><div><p>a reference to &#8216;writing&#8217; or &#8216;written&#8217; includes any method of reproducing words in a legible and non-transitory form <em opt-key='opt-N66952'>(excluding email)</em>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e8725f3-ef2a-4deb-94cc-9e564309943d'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='0009'>in force at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='0009'>as amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em></em>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem537a2b6f-603f-4349-a9ff-0df6bd81c97f'><div><p>a reference to legislation includes all subordinate legislation made <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='0010'>as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='0010'>from time to time</em> under that legislation; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemb8def332-27af-47b5-8387-5e43d368c113'><div><p>a reference to any English action, remedy, method of judicial proceeding, court, official, legal document, legal status, legal doctrine, legal concept or thing shall, in respect of any jurisdiction other than England, be deemed to include a reference to that which most nearly approximates to the English equivalent in that jurisdiction.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/></p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4B9636EC-D658-44D3-BA41-FF358FC5FF3E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D8E22062345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D8E22062345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4B9636EC-D658-44D3-BA41-FF358FC5FF3E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4B9636EC-D658-44D3-BA41-FF358FC5FF3E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall at the request and cost of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and to transfer <b>Control</b> of the <b>Domain Name</b> to the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> and otherwise enable the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> to fully operate the <b>Domain Name</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges the seller at the request of the buyer to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:989DD307-7131-4D08-8610-D9CC9DF5D1FD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:989DD307-7131-4D08-8610-D9CC9DF5D1FD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:989DD307-7131-4D08-8610-D9CC9DF5D1FD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Transfer of rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No party may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a party may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> through any <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other party&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>. Each party acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b> in relation to that party&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that party itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Transfer of rights</p><div><p>This transfer of rights clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>. </p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:989DD307-7131-4D08-8610-D9CC9DF5D1FD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the parties out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each party who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the parties <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'> may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either party may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the parties have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither party shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either party may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause requires the parties to use reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:989DD307-7131-4D08-8610-D9CC9DF5D1FD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:989DD307-7131-4D08-8610-D9CC9DF5D1FD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's <em alt-key='alt-D13E10680020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D13E10680020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D13E11280021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D13E11280021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:989DD307-7131-4D08-8610-D9CC9DF5D1FD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;party&#8217; includes that party&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow 'include', 'includes', 'including', &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D13E4060009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D13E4060009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:989DD307-7131-4D08-8610-D9CC9DF5D1FD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:989DD307-7131-4D08-8610-D9CC9DF5D1FD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D13E1008022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D13E1008022'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D13E1023023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D13E1023023'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D13E1034024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D13E1034024'><em type='text'>insert name of specified document</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:989DD307-7131-4D08-8610-D9CC9DF5D1FD'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a party to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0658A44F-FFCD-49EF-92AD-D2F0BC1E8D04'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's <em alt-key='alt-D18E8490020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D18E8490020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b class='referring'>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D18E9090021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D18E9090021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0658A44F-FFCD-49EF-92AD-D2F0BC1E8D04'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a party to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0658A44F-FFCD-49EF-92AD-D2F0BC1E8D04'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D18E789022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D18E789022'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D18E804023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D18E804023'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D18E815024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D18E815024'><em type='text'>insert name of specified document</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.<!--Added Entire agreement--></p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0658A44F-FFCD-49EF-92AD-D2F0BC1E8D04'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0658A44F-FFCD-49EF-92AD-D2F0BC1E8D04'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;party&#8217; includes that party&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p> a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p> words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow 'include', 'includes', 'including', &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D18E3970009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D18E3970009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0658A44F-FFCD-49EF-92AD-D2F0BC1E8D04'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0658A44F-FFCD-49EF-92AD-D2F0BC1E8D04'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0658A44F-FFCD-49EF-92AD-D2F0BC1E8D04'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Transfer of rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No party may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a party may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other party&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>. Each party acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b> in relation to that party&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that party itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Transfer of rights</p><div><p>This transfer of rights clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>. </p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0658A44F-FFCD-49EF-92AD-D2F0BC1E8D04'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0658A44F-FFCD-49EF-92AD-D2F0BC1E8D04'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the parties out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each party who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the parties <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'> may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either party may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the parties have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither party shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either party may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause requires the parties to use reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0FF8D5AD-6C3B-46E1-826E-9B157AF607A5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> shall comply with <b>Applicable Law</b> and shall maintain such licences, authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform its obligations under or in connection with the <b class='document-class'>Contract</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on the customer to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>. Ensure that this clause is compatible with the data protection law compliance provisions.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:B16D5EFE-2EF1-4072-9876-24FFA0535105'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the assignment agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:B16D5EFE-2EF1-4072-9876-24FFA0535105'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='2345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='2345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the assignment agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='notfound'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting <b>party</b>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:334E4C21-70AF-4146-9E49-4E55FEBC76F7'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D64E33840020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E33840020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem63b756a3-539d-46ad-a1bb-e85f071e31fb'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-51DEDAD8'><div><p><em>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D64E34440021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E34440021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:334E4C21-70AF-4146-9E49-4E55FEBC76F7'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='notfound'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;<b>party</b>&#8217; includes that <b>party</b>&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-key='alt-D64E4770009' alt-connector='or'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b></em><em alt-key='alt-D64E4770009' alt-connector='or'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/></p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:334E4C21-70AF-4146-9E49-4E55FEBC76F7'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid if any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='notfound'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D64E37452345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E37452345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:334E4C21-70AF-4146-9E49-4E55FEBC76F7'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p><em alt-key='alt-D64E35650001' alt-connector='or'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, each</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E35650001' alt-connector='or'>Each</em> <b>party</b> shall pay all sums that it owes to the other <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:334E4C21-70AF-4146-9E49-4E55FEBC76F7'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the <b>parties</b> out of or in connection with this <b>Licence</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each <b>party</b> who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the <b>parties</b> <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either <b>party</b> may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the <b>parties</b> have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither <b>party</b> shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either <b>party</b> may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>The parties should decide how any disputes under the agreement should be dealt with.</p></div><div><p>It is usually appropriate to take a graduated approach&#8212;eg initially using reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation.</p></div><div><p>The parties should consider what their objectives are when agreeing a dispute resolution mechanism&#8212;eg arbitration might be appropriate if confidentiality is the key consideration, but court proceedings might prove less expensive and follow more familiar procedures.</p></div><div><p>For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>For more information about alternative dispute resolution, see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0ONJ_166446'>Types of dispute resolution</a>, <a normcite='0ONJ_173056'>IP and mediation</a> and <a normcite='0ONJ_3421594'>IP and arbitration</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:334E4C21-70AF-4146-9E49-4E55FEBC76F7'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b>. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D64E25500001'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E25500001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:334E4C21-70AF-4146-9E49-4E55FEBC76F7'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:334E4C21-70AF-4146-9E49-4E55FEBC76F7'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='notfound'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b><em opt-key='opt-N66047'> and <em alt-key='alt-D64E3324022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E3324022'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D64E3339023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E3339023'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D64E3350024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D64E3350024'><em type='text'>insert names of specified documents</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:334E4C21-70AF-4146-9E49-4E55FEBC76F7'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='notfound'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>,<em opt-key='opt-N65821'> their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting <b>party</b>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D69E37802345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E37802345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, <em opt-key='opt-N65821'>their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b><em opt-key='opt-N66047'> and <em alt-key='alt-D69E3358022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E3358022'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b><em opt-key='opt-N66098'> or <em alt-key='alt-D69E3373023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E3373023'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b><em opt-key='opt-N66116'> or <em alt-key='alt-D69E3384024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E3384024'><em type='text'>insert names of specified documents</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='notfound'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;<b>party</b>&#8217; includes that <b>party</b>&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-key='alt-D69E5050009' alt-connector='or'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b></em><em alt-key='alt-D69E5050009' alt-connector='or'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/></p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid if any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p><em alt-key='alt-D69E35990001' alt-connector='or'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, each</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E35990001' alt-connector='or'>Each</em> <b>party</b> shall pay all sums that it owes to the other <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the <b>parties</b> out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each <b>party</b> who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the <b>parties</b> <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either <b>party</b> may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the <b>parties</b> have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither <b>party</b> shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either <b>party</b> may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>The parties should decide how any disputes under the agreement should be dealt with.</p></div><div><p>It is usually appropriate to take a graduated approach&#8212;eg initially using reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation.</p></div><div><p>The parties should consider what their objectives are when agreeing a dispute resolution mechanism&#8212;eg arbitration might be appropriate if confidentiality is the key consideration, but court proceedings might prove less expensive and be follow more familiar procedures.</p></div><div><p>For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>For more information about alternative dispute resolution, see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0ONJ_166446'>Types of dispute resolution</a>, <a normcite='0ONJ_173056'>IP and mediation</a> and <a normcite='0ONJ_3421594'>IP and arbitration</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b>. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D69E25200001'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E25200001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:93229244-00EF-4FC3-BDDE-664DD106EC89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='alt-D69E34190020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E34190020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> (or to the fax number<em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'> or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemcf966a48-118d-47ea-86a7-0a6c940eef93'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D69E34790021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D69E34790021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Licence</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EBEA5DE2-9159-42F8-9BAA-A9EAED3786C8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;party&#8217; includes that party&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p> a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p> words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D73E13570009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D73E13570009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1515672880-110221141'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a' type='clause'/></p><div><p>The data protection schedule (<a id-ref='ukContentItem1511788371-22165' type='schedule'/>) is generally drafted on the basis that references to data protection laws means such laws as amended from to time (given that customers are placing increased emphasis on such provisions and since suppliers will usually needed to comply with similar basic obligations for all customers), and on the assumption that the option &#8216;as amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time&#8217; will be used (without any qualification such as &#8216;except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this Agreement&#8217;). However the supplier may wish to take a more restrictive approach. Adapt <a id-ref='ukContentItem1511788371-22165' type='schedule'/> and other provisions as appropriate to ensure the agreement clearly sets out how changes in legislation will apply for the purposes of data protection and other provisions of this agreement (eg if <a id-ref='ukContentItem1511788371-22165' type='schedule'/> will contain a different regime ensure this clause is flagged to be &#8216;Without prejudice to the provisions of <a id-ref='ukContentItem1511788371-22165' type='schedule'/>&#8217;). Assuming this clause states &#8216;a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time&#8217; the initial optional wording &#8216;Without prejudice to the provisions of Schedule [5]&#8217; would not be needed.</p></div></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EBEA5DE2-9159-42F8-9BAA-A9EAED3786C8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D73E4883022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D73E4883022'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D73E4898023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D73E4898023'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D73E4909024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D73E4909024'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specified document[s]</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each of the <b>parties</b> shall<em alt-key='000112'>, at its own cost and expense,</em><em alt-key='000112'>, at the request, cost and expense of the other <b>party</b>,</em><em opt-key='opt-N65626'> use its reasonable endeavours to</em> perform all acts, and sign, execute and deliver all deeds and documents, as may be <em opt-key='opt-N65630'>reasonably</em> required for the purpose of giving full effect to this agreement <em opt-key='opt-N65634'>and shall <em opt-key='opt-N65637'>use its reasonable endeavours to</em> procure that necessary third parties shall also do so</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='022'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='023'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='024'><em type='text'>insert names of specified documents</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements (such as those made during the course of negotiations, but which are not reflected in the final agreement) from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='2345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='2345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, <em opt-key='opt-N65821'>their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;<b>party</b>&#8217; includes that <b>party</b>&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender includes each other gender;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow &#8216;include&#8217;, &#8216;includes&#8217;, &#8216;including&#8217;, &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='0009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='0009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>For example boilerplate wording, see Precedents: <a normcite='0OKF_1481872'>Boilerplate set&#8212;short form</a> and <a normcite='0OKF_1481866'>Boilerplate set&#8212;long form</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No <b>party</b> may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a <b>party</b> may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other <b>party</b>&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. Each <b>party</b> acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b>Affiliate</b> in relation to that <b>party</b>&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that <b>party</b> itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party and precludes the parties from transferring or otherwise dealing with the rights and obligations under the agreement to another party without the other party&#8217;s express consent. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the <b>parties</b> out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each <b>party</b> who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem270c8d7f-8caf-4e3a-b9d1-8f0997a027a3' type='clause'/>, the <b>parties</b> <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either <b>party</b> may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the <b>parties</b> have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither <b>party</b> shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either <b>party</b> may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>The parties should decide how any disputes under the agreement should be dealt with.</p></div><div><p>It is usually appropriate to take a graduated approach&#8212;eg initially using reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation.</p></div><div><p>The parties should consider what their objectives are when agreeing a dispute resolution mechanism&#8212;eg arbitration might be appropriate if confidentiality is the key consideration, but court proceedings might prove less expensive and be follow more familiar procedures.</p></div><div><p>For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div><!--CM note to self: cross-refer to PN on IP arbitration, when it's ready.--></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability for any failure or delay in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> to the extent the same results from <em alt-key='alt-0D3DE2B1'><b>Force majeure</b></em><em alt-key='alt-0D3DE2B1'>any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b></em><em opt-key='opt-2C9F2521'> for as long as such event means that performance of the agreement is not possible or is delayed</em>. The <b>party</b> affected by such <em alt-key='alt-0D3E0061'><b>Force majeure</b></em><em alt-key='alt-0D3E0061'>event</em> shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such <em alt-key='alt-0D3E0BC5'><b>Force majeure</b></em><em alt-key='alt-0D3E0BC5'>event</em> causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such <em alt-key='alt-0D3E12E3'><b>Force majeure</b></em><em alt-key='alt-0D3E12E3'>event</em> continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation <em opt-key='opt-71C6861E'>(including non-contractual disputes or claims)</em> shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7338BB9B-41A1-44FD-BBC3-CC75747F5534'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='0020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='0020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ByFaxToNumberInTheCaseOfPartyAndNum-FEECC49A'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='0021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='0021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7CC738A7-7EB9-42E7-94CB-5322EC88CA3A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's address as set out on the first page of this <b>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc37bcf8b-3b40-4e89-9012-a45297ac6f61'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='0021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='0021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7CC738A7-7EB9-42E7-94CB-5322EC88CA3A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the parties out of or in connection with this <b>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to the <b>Authorised Contacts</b> of each party who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>, the parties may resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p>Either party may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause promotes initial attempts to resolve any dispute informally. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7CC738A7-7EB9-42E7-94CB-5322EC88CA3A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> shall not subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This assignment clause has a customer bias with optional wording to allay supplier concerns. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:9D2D1848-C55A-4016-A8F0-3882E49F9C10'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment and sub-contracting</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554' type='clause'/>, neither <b>party</b> may assign, sub-contract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other <b>party</b>&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>. This clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/> is subject to the additional requirements of clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItema1076363-48f3-4f54-ad2a-86d81c78871f' type='clause'/> to <a id-ref='ukContentItemd04ebbf6-f9d6-4e26-89f2-3c0ee0fbbc7b' type='clause'/> (inclusive).</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. The <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b>Affiliate</b> in relation to the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> itself.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem20596ff8-8b2e-4fcd-8e24-cf1071dfe09c'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> shall remain responsible for all acts and omissions of <b>Supplier Personnel</b> as if they were its own acts and omissions. Any obligation on the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> to do, or to refrain from doing, any act or thing under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or otherwise shall include an obligation upon the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> to procure that all <b>Supplier Personnel</b> also do, or refrain from doing, such act or thing.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1575293233-28347158'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem20596ff8-8b2e-4fcd-8e24-cf1071dfe09c' type='clause'/></p><div><p>While this clause reflects a generally accepted contracting approach, in the context of managed services the supplier should consider if any carve outs are required in respect of transferred contracts (since the relevant service providers and their staff will become supplier personnel).</p></div></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment and sub-contracting</p><div><p>This assignment clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:9D2D1848-C55A-4016-A8F0-3882E49F9C10'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute Resolution Process</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem4276d089-dfdb-4dd8-bd71-327fd971e7c2'><div><p>Any dispute arising between the <b>parties</b> out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be dealt with in accordance with the provisions of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc4dc0eb0-7e74-4a9f-ab75-0ca1b00ab398'><div><p>The <b>Dispute Resolution Process</b> may be initiated at any time by either <b>party</b> serving a notice in writing on the other <b>party</b> that a dispute has arisen. The notice must include reasonable information as to the nature of the dispute.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6b66c1f3-0e27-4b38-b567-5c52f64dae9e'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> shall use all reasonable endeavours to reach a negotiated resolution through the following procedures:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb455abb3-65f4-4d4a-ba6d-dd612fdcea5c'><div><p>Within <em type='text'>seven days</em> of service of the notice, the <em type='text'>Authorised Contacts</em> of the <b>parties</b> shall meet to discuss the dispute and attempt to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc5f47e05-572b-44a3-a974-da92d24063cd'><div><p>If the dispute has not been resolved within <em type='text'>seven days</em> of the first meeting of the <em type='text'>Authorised Contacts</em>, then the matter shall be referred to the <em type='text'>chief executives</em> (or persons of equivalent seniority). The <em type='text'>chief executives</em> (or equivalent) will meet within <em type='text'>seven days</em> to discuss the dispute and attempt to resolve it.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28af2d5f-053a-467d-8901-ceab4f9fc4e2'><div><p>The specific format for the resolution of the dispute under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemb455abb3-65f4-4d4a-ba6d-dd612fdcea5c' type='clause'/> and, if necessary, clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemc5f47e05-572b-44a3-a974-da92d24063cd' type='clause'/> will be left to the reasonable discretion of the <b>parties</b>, but may include the preparation and submission of statements of fact or of position.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1e581e57-78f7-4552-a0fd-7ab0641e6895'><div><p>If the dispute has not been resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the first meeting of the <em type='text'>chief executives</em> (or equivalent) under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemc5f47e05-572b-44a3-a974-da92d24063cd' type='clause'/>, then the matter <em alt-key='alt-AE12CA32'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE12CA32'>may</em> be referred to mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem3a2ac717-7df0-44ea-82bd-d3b4de0d1e51'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE131CF8'>Either <b>party</b> may issue formal legal proceedings at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem6b66c1f3-0e27-4b38-b567-5c52f64dae9e' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItem1e581e57-78f7-4552-a0fd-7ab0641e6895' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE131CF8'>Until the <b>parties</b> have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem6b66c1f3-0e27-4b38-b567-5c52f64dae9e' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItem1e581e57-78f7-4552-a0fd-7ab0641e6895' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither <b>party</b> shall commence formal legal proceedings except that either <b>party</b> may at any time seek urgent interim relief from the courts or emergency arbitrator relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73b20206-d224-44fc-8e3b-e77091dbd815'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute Resolution Process</p><div><p>For guidance, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:2A30565C-D4A0-466C-B5B1-922045989686'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the parties out of or in connection with this <b>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to the account managers of each party who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>10 Business Days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>, the parties may resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p>Either party may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause promotes initial attempts to resolve any dispute informally. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:2A30565C-D4A0-466C-B5B1-922045989686'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p>Each party must pay all sums that it owes to the other party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits either party from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. In practice this will favour the supplier. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:2A30565C-D4A0-466C-B5B1-922045989686'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div><p>No party may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This assignment clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:2A30565C-D4A0-466C-B5B1-922045989686'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:2A30565C-D4A0-466C-B5B1-922045989686'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's address as set out on the first page of this <b>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>five</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc37bcf8b-3b40-4e89-9012-a45297ac6f61'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D2E31220021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D2E31220021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:2A30565C-D4A0-466C-B5B1-922045989686'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither party shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b>Agreement</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that party. The party affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other party in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>3</em> months, either party may terminate this <b>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4F597581-212A-40C8-A5EA-FAF5B064B757'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s address as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc37bcf8b-3b40-4e89-9012-a45297ac6f61'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='0021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='0021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4F597581-212A-40C8-A5EA-FAF5B064B757'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='022'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='023'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='024'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specified document[s]</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;The customer should always consider whether, in fact, other documents or policies are relevant to the supplier&#8217;s performance of the contract and reference them clearly within the agreement if this clause is included. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4F597581-212A-40C8-A5EA-FAF5B064B757'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> shall not assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the prior written consent&#160;of the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This one-way assignment clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4F597581-212A-40C8-A5EA-FAF5B064B757'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force Majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b>. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, either <b>party</b> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. Customers should give the clause careful consideration as suppliers may seek to include many scenarios in the scope of force majeure so as to gain maximum protection from liability. It is also important to consider whether a party should have the right to terminate if the event of force majeure exceeds a certain period. When an event of force majeure has struck, it is at that point that the customer might most need to rely on the supplier, not receive a notice of termination. Equally, if such an event happens, it might be the customer that wants to issue a notice of termination so as to secure continuity of service with an alternative supplier. If the customer is being provided with disaster recovery services, consider if the force majeure clause should be removed.</p></div><div><p>For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4F597581-212A-40C8-A5EA-FAF5B064B757'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>party</b> without the prior written consent of the other <b>party</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:4F597581-212A-40C8-A5EA-FAF5B064B757'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:38DFC790-B156-403E-BD86-386288AE90D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='2345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='2345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='referring'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Paragraph <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:38DFC790-B156-403E-BD86-386288AE90D5'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='referring'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Paragraph <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EEF5CAF9-6D23-4AFE-AAA8-30AC3757BFDE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b>. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='0001'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='0001'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EEF5CAF9-6D23-4AFE-AAA8-30AC3757BFDE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Transfer of rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No <b>party</b> may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a <b>party</b> may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other <b>party</b>&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. Each <b>party</b> acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b>Affiliate</b> in relation to that <b>party</b>&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that <b>party</b> itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Transfer of rights</p><div><p>This transfer of rights clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. Note that this provision will need to be amended if the licence grant at clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemd51fa390-73ca-47ba-9840-6c5048948a42' type='clause'/> provides that the licence may be freely transferable and/or sublicenseable. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EEF5CAF9-6D23-4AFE-AAA8-30AC3757BFDE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EEF5CAF9-6D23-4AFE-AAA8-30AC3757BFDE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>party</b> without the prior written consent of the other <b>party</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EEF5CAF9-6D23-4AFE-AAA8-30AC3757BFDE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>'s <em alt-key='0020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='0020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number<em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'> or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> days after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> days after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;<em opt-key='opt-9B23287B'> and</em></p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; <em opt-key='opt-9B2323D3'>and</em></p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-4C4D4963'><div><p>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='0021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='0021'>read</em> return email.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed Drafting Notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EEF5CAF9-6D23-4AFE-AAA8-30AC3757BFDE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EEF5CAF9-6D23-4AFE-AAA8-30AC3757BFDE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N66047'> and <em alt-key='022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='022'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N66098'> or <em alt-key='023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='023'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N66116'> or <em alt-key='024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='024'><em type='text'>insert name of specified document</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EEF5CAF9-6D23-4AFE-AAA8-30AC3757BFDE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:EEF5CAF9-6D23-4AFE-AAA8-30AC3757BFDE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:28868B8C-76CC-41FF-856A-78B2765CAFA2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b>. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other party in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='00011'>the <b>party</b> not affected</em><em alt-key='00011'>either <b>party</b></em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability and gives them the right to terminate the agreement if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:28868B8C-76CC-41FF-856A-78B2765CAFA2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Transfer of rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-5B32A48C'>Except where expressly permitted in the <b>Agreement</b>,</em> <em alt-key='alt-91D630AA'>No</em><em alt-key='alt-91D630AA'>no</em> <b>party</b> may assign, subcontract, transfer, or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a <b>party</b> may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other <b>party</b>&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. <em opt-key='opt-5B33160A'>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b> <em opt-key='opt-5B331307'>or of any subcontractor to whom the licensee grants a sublicence pursuant to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>,</em> in relation to that <b>party</b>&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that <b>party</b> itself.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Transfer of rights</p><div><p>This transfer of rights clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. Note that optional text has been included which can be used where the licence grant at clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemd51fa390-73ca-47ba-9840-6c5048948a42' type='clause'/> provides that the licence may be freely transferable and/or sublicenseable. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:28868B8C-76CC-41FF-856A-78B2765CAFA2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:28868B8C-76CC-41FF-856A-78B2765CAFA2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:28868B8C-76CC-41FF-856A-78B2765CAFA2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='022'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='023'><em type='text'>insert name of specific document</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='024'><em type='text'>insert name of specified document</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:28868B8C-76CC-41FF-856A-78B2765CAFA2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees,</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This third party rights clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:28868B8C-76CC-41FF-856A-78B2765CAFA2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:28868B8C-76CC-41FF-856A-78B2765CAFA2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a <b>party</b> without the prior written consent of the other <b>party</b> (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:28868B8C-76CC-41FF-856A-78B2765CAFA2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s <em alt-key='0020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='0020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> days after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> days after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report<em opt-key='opt-91D5F95F'>; and</em></p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-4C4D4963'><div><p>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='0021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='0021'>read</em> return email.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:B60D7911-F3F1-412D-B372-3FED5C3B9DED'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem75435fe9-ac96-4bfc-bfc9-59395ec334e6'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply with all applicable laws and shall maintain such authorisations and approvals as required from time to time to perform their obligations under or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc7f471e2-6c8b-4f45-9013-c297d47f4525'><div><p>Without prejudice to the generality of clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem75435fe9-ac96-4bfc-bfc9-59395ec334e6' type='clause'/>, the <b>parties</b> shall comply with all applicable laws, rules, and regulations governing export of goods and information that apply to the <b>Software</b> and the <b>User Manual</b>, and shall not export or re-export, directly or indirectly, separately or as a part of a system, the <b>Software</b> or the <b>User Manual</b> to any country for which an export licence or other approval is required, without first obtaining such licence or other approval. The <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> shall be solely responsible for ensuring its access, importation or use of the <b>Software</b> or <b>User Manual</b> in or into any part of the <b>Territory</b> complies with all export laws.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, particularly those in relation to export restrictions. It is a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. Suppliers should be aware that customers may request a specific warranty that the installation and use of the software in accordance with the agreement will not put it in breach of any applicable export laws.</p></div><div><p>Export control regulations restrict the export of so-called &#8216;dual use&#8217; goods (which include software) that could have both a civilian and military use to certain blacklisted countries. One possible example involves the international licensing of any software containing encryption functionality. Whilst export control regulations are unlikely to be triggered by the majority of commercial software licences, suppliers and customers should be aware of these provisions and cater for them particularly when licensing software internationally. It should be noted that &#8216;export&#8217; includes both physical and electronic delivery of the software.</p></div><div><p>Suppliers exporting dual use goods will need to apply for licences from the relevant authorities. A failure to do so can result in criminal sanctions (including fines and imprisonment) with enforcement in the UK pursued under the Customs and Excise Management Act 1979 or the Export Control Order 2008.</p></div><div><p>Where the circumstances are such that compliance with export laws is a material risk (for example, if the software has a military application or if it contains encryption functionality) the supplier may want to consider including an additional right to discontinue the licence, either permanently or temporarily, to the extent necessary for either party to be able to comply with the law.</p></div><div><p>For more on export restrictions generally see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OK7_197822'>Export controls&#8212;requirement for an export licence</a>.</p></div><div><p>For alternative forms of general compliance with law wording and drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FF23518D-A184-406C-BA26-DA0823E16294'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentIteme3044c46-4f9a-44bf-a317-60755984b8c8'><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem971c5fe9-334f-471b-8bc8-964d71658ddf' type='clause'/>, each <b>party</b> shall comply with all laws, enactments, regulations, regulatory policies, guidelines and industry codes applicable to them and shall maintain such authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform their obligations under or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem971c5fe9-334f-471b-8bc8-964d71658ddf'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> warrants and represents that the access, use, import or download of the <b>Software</b> into the <b>Territory</b> by the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party>, any <b>Customer Affiliate</b> or any <b>Authorised Third Party</b> in accordance with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> will not breach any applicable laws, rules and regulations including any applicable export or import restrictions.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws and contains a warranty and representation by the supplier that the customer&#8217;s use of the software will not breach any such laws including, in particular, any export control regulations.</p></div><div><p>Export control regulations restrict the export of so-called 'dual use' goods (which include software) that could have both a civilian and military use to certain blacklisted countries. One possible example involves the international licensing of any software containing encryption functionality. Whilst export control regulations are unlikely to be triggered by the majority of commercial software licences, suppliers and customers should be aware of these provisions and cater for them particularly when licensing software internationally. It should be noted that &#8216;export&#8217; includes both physical and electronic delivery of the software.</p></div><div><p>For more on export restrictions generally see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OK7_197822'>Export controls&#8212;requirement for an export licence</a>.</p></div><div><p>For alternative forms of general compliance with law wording and drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:A2E7BC74-40A4-4B3D-9B8F-B545175BDBDC'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its <b>Representatives</b> will comply with all applicable <b>Law</b>, provided that neither <b>party</b> shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by the other <b>party</b> (or its <b>Representatives</b>).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. It is a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:96099CF0-AB33-4339-9AE9-6E14FC115E1F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this Agreement, its employees, agents and representatives will comply with all applicable laws and regulations, provided that neither <b>party</b> shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this Agreement by the other <b>party</b> (or its employees, agents and representatives).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws. It is a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:B422DACE-6503-4394-82DE-B453B6C77289'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem75435fe9-ac96-4bfc-bfc9-59395ec334e6'><div><p>Each party shall comply with all applicable laws and shall maintain such authorisations and approvals as required from time to time to perform their obligations under or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc7f471e2-6c8b-4f45-9013-c297d47f4525'><div><p>Without prejudice to the generality of clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem75435fe9-ac96-4bfc-bfc9-59395ec334e6' type='clause'/>, the parties shall comply with all applicable laws, rules, and regulations governing export of goods, software and information that apply to the <b>Software</b> and the <b>User Manual</b>, and shall not export or re-export, directly or indirectly, separately or as a part of a system, the <b>Software</b> or the <b>User Manual</b> to any country for which an export licence or other approval is required, without first obtaining such licence or other approval. The <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> shall be solely responsible for ensuring its access, importation or use of the <b>Software</b> or <b>User Manual</b> in or into any part of the <b>Territory</b> complies with all export laws.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, particularly those in relation to export restrictions. It is generally drafted as a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. Suppliers should be aware that customers may request a specific warranty that the installation and use of the software in accordance with the agreement will not put it in breach of any applicable export laws.</p></div><div><p>Export control regulations restrict the export of so-called 'dual use' goods (which include software) that could have both a civilian and military use to certain blacklisted countries. One possible example involves the international licensing of any software containing encryption functionality. Whilst export control regulations are unlikely to be triggered by the majority of commercial software licences, suppliers and customers should be aware of these provisions and cater for them particularly when licensing software internationally. It should be noted that &#8216;export&#8217; includes both physical and electronic delivery of the software. Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemc7f471e2-6c8b-4f45-9013-c297d47f4525' type='clause'/> may duplicate equivalent obligations in the licence agreement (see for example equivalent provisions in Precedent: <a normcite='0OKV_2355593'>Software licence&#8212;pro-supplier</a> ). However, the supplier is likely to wish to repeat any such obligation here for the avoidance of doubt and also so that any default in compliance with such a clause by the customer is a breach of both agreements, which may simplify the supplier&#8217;s ability to seek appropriate remedies. For further information see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKV_2355593'>Software licence&#8212;pro-supplier</a>.</p></div><div><p>For alternative forms of general compliance with law wording and drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:07E37F36-3B15-42C1-BC24-88F5EF12DE37'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the deed survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:07E37F36-3B15-42C1-BC24-88F5EF12DE37'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' opt-key='opt-BC793996'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the parties out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each party who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the parties <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either party may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the parties have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither party shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either party may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause requires the parties to use reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:07E37F36-3B15-42C1-BC24-88F5EF12DE37'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Transfer of rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No party may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a party may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> through any <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other party&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b>. Each party acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b class='referring'>Affiliate</b> in relation to that party&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that party itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Transfer of rights</p><div><p>This transfer of rights clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under a deed may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>. </p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:07E37F36-3B15-42C1-BC24-88F5EF12DE37'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a party to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the deed. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:07E37F36-3B15-42C1-BC24-88F5EF12DE37'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's <em alt-key='alt-D13E10680020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D13E10680020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery<em opt-key='opt-C96D141E'>; and</em></p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report<em opt-key='opt-C96D1017'>; and</em></p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-C96D0C12'><div><p>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D13E11280021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D13E11280021'>read</em> return email.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the deed and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:07E37F36-3B15-42C1-BC24-88F5EF12DE37'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the deed and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:07E37F36-3B15-42C1-BC24-88F5EF12DE37'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;party&#8217; includes that party&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender encompasses said gender as well as all genders;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow 'include', 'includes', 'including', &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D13E4060009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D13E4060009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the deed. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:07E37F36-3B15-42C1-BC24-88F5EF12DE37'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:07E37F36-3B15-42C1-BC24-88F5EF12DE37'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the deed. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D5F9C85-AB1E-4002-AD5F-5DF11C0C9F9A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966'><div><p>In this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem80c6df84-4f7d-4729-97a3-bf23e4a6a732'><div><p>a reference to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> includes its schedules, appendices and annexes (if any);</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem71a83988-4130-4afe-94f0-2ed9ca0ab274'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;party&#8217; includes that party&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6523c344-02a6-4bd2-a6aa-013cca0bac3c'><div><p>a reference to a &#8216;person&#8217; includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (in each case whether or not having separate legal personality) and that person&#8217;s personal representatives, successors and permitted assigns;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem16790808-24fb-4466-9a23-a0bcd8880d2e'><div><p>a reference to a gender encompasses said gender as well as all genders;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem9e86def6-3aeb-4e62-a605-383dbb32b401'><div><p>words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem82a6626d-b0f9-4606-ba62-d77a92d05848'><div><p>any words that follow 'include', 'includes', 'including', &#8216;in particular&#8217; or any similar words and expressions shall be construed as illustrative only and shall not limit the sense of any word, phrase, term, definition or description preceding those words;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7d571334-3825-4fd5-9070-2627e806bed7'><div><p>the table of contents, background section and any clause, schedule or other headings in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> are included for convenience only and shall have no effect on the interpretation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem86969d41-464d-4654-8645-34e59a7f175a'><div><p>a reference to legislation is a reference to that legislation as <em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D13E4060009'>in force as at the date of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D13E4060009'>amended, extended, re-enacted or consolidated from time to time <em opt-key='opt-N67007'>except to the extent that any such amendment, extension or re-enactment would increase or alter the liability of a party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b></em></em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem792220e8-a42a-4ba8-a8ea-3594bdd0ce67'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem42724442-7f8d-49fc-a36e-8d6994eb3966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Interpretation</p><div><p>This interpretation clause applies selected principles of interpretation to the Agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of interpretation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179780'>Definitions and interpretation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D5F9C85-AB1E-4002-AD5F-5DF11C0C9F9A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's <em alt-key='alt-D13E10680020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D13E10680020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D13E11280021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D13E11280021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D5F9C85-AB1E-4002-AD5F-5DF11C0C9F9A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D5F9C85-AB1E-4002-AD5F-5DF11C0C9F9A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D5F9C85-AB1E-4002-AD5F-5DF11C0C9F9A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' opt-key='opt-BC793996'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the parties out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each party who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the parties <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'> may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either party may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Until the parties have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither party shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either party may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause requires the parties to use reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D5F9C85-AB1E-4002-AD5F-5DF11C0C9F9A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D5F9C85-AB1E-4002-AD5F-5DF11C0C9F9A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "IPANDIT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D5F9C85-AB1E-4002-AD5F-5DF11C0C9F9A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a party to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34828125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:26961143-94A6-4376-915E-4A565C65428A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have exclusive jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem6a4733a3-5990-4eba-b100-19fe125ff259'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This clause provides that the courts of England and Wales shall have jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, the agreement. </p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217;.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Fiona Trust v Privalov and others [2007] All ER (D) 233 (Oct) </a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>UBS AG v HSH Nordbank AG [2009] EWCA Civ 585, para 82</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The inclusion of the wording 'arise out of, or in connection with' and similar terms in a jurisdiction clause used to cause difficulties as to exactly what type of disputes were brought within its scope. The House of Lords has, in an arbitration case, upheld a wide interpretation of these words. This was on the assumption that the parties, as rational businessmen, were likely to have intended <em class='it'>any</em> dispute arising out of their relationship to be decided by the tribunal referred to in the relevant clause. The wording was held to be so wide as to cover claims arising before inception of the relevant agreement, such as misrepresentation. This wide interpretation has subsequently been followed in a number of litigation cases.</p></div><div><p>The enforceability of a clause which confers jurisdiction on the courts of England and Wales may ultimately depend, post-Brexit, on the treaty arrangements which exist after the UK leaves the EU. It cannot be said with absolute certainty that the courts of an EU member state will respect such a clause, particularly if the clause confers non-exclusive jurisdiction on the courts of England and Wales. Consequently, if one of the parties to this agreement is domiciled in an EU member state and does not have sufficient assets within the jurisdiction to satisfy any potential judgment against it, practitioners may need to advise clients to seek a legal opinion from lawyers in the EU member state where enforcement is likely to be required confirming that the courts in that country will enforce an English judgment under their national rules. Alternatively, clients might consider making it a term of this agreement that sufficient assets are brought into the jurisdiction in order to satisfy any judgment obtained here.</p></div><div><p>See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLB_3122262'>Brexit&#8212;jurisdiction [Archived]</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34327125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:26961143-94A6-4376-915E-4A565C65428A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1490085952-34560125'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause provides that the agreement and certain disputes and claims shall governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217;.</p></div><div><p>A choice of law clause which makes English law the law of this agreement should not be affected by Brexit, regardless of whether this agreement is entered into before or after the UK leaves the EU. This is because EU law (in the form of &#160;Regulation (EC) 593/2008 (&#8216;Rome I&#8217;) and Regulation (EC) 864/2007 (&#8216;Rome II&#8217;)) requires member states to uphold choice of law clauses regardless of whether the law chosen is the law of a member state. A party who is domiciled in an EU member state should not be in a position to argue that English law should not apply to any dispute arising out of this agreement even though the court of an EU member state has jurisdiction over it.</p></div><div><p>See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLB_3122566'>Brexit&#8212;applicable law [Archived]</a>.</p></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34097125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:26961143-94A6-4376-915E-4A565C65428A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125'><p class='main_heading'>Joint and several liability</p><div><p>Where the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> is more than one person, the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may release or compromise the liability of any of those persons under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or grant time or other indulgence without affecting the liability of any other of them.</p></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:26961143-94A6-4376-915E-4A565C65428A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' opt-key='opt-N70787'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p> No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party<em opt-key='opt-D733AC17'>, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any securities exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem52b8262f-83f4-481e-a3e0-95e8d8a98954'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This is a short form announcements provision. For a longer form see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>This clause is drafted on the basis that:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>it binds all of the parties to the Agreement</p></div></li><li><div><p>the general prohibition on announcements and other public disclosures relates to the existence of the contract itself and any of the matters contained in it</p></div></li><li><div><p>the parties will remain bound for the duration of the Agreement (if the clause is intended to survive termination of the agreement, this may be stated in the clause itself or elsewhere in the Agreement, eg in the termination or survival clause)</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made with the prior written consent of the other party, with no express process being set out to obtain such consent, although it must not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made as required by law, a court or any other authority, without any prior written consent from the other party or any consultation with them being required.</p></div><div><p>The announcements clause normally forms part of the main agreement relating to a transaction or arrangement and, as such, will take effect on the signing of the agreement. Prior to signing, any announcement relating to the proposed transaction or arrangement will normally be restricted by the terms of a confidentiality agreement entered into between the parties. The terms of such a confidentiality agreement should be considered in drafting an announcements clause; it would be usual for the announcements clause (along with any confidentiality clause) to replace this initial confidentiality agreement.</p></div><div><p>It is necessary to consider an announcements clause in an agreement in conjunction with any confidentiality clause, to ensure that the two work effectively together</p></div></li></ul></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1561132277-50196260", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:26961143-94A6-4376-915E-4A565C65428A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' opt-key='opt-590EB33F'><p class='main_heading'>Undertaking</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-42027560'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall procure that, by the time of <b>Completion</b>, the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of an undertaking (&#8216;the Undertaking&#8217;) given by the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> (whether by the adoption of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion by Post (2019) (&#8216;the Code&#8217;) or otherwise) that the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on <b>Completion</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50459160'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall not be obliged to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> unless and until the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of the Undertaking. If the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> is ready, able and willing to complete but the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> do not have the benefit of the Undertaking, the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall be treated as in default and not being ready, able and willing to complete and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be entitled to give the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> a notice to complete.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-41490460'><div><p>In this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/>, the term &#8216;Seller&#8217; has the same meaning as in the Code and the phrase &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitors&#8217; has the same meaning as is given to the term &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitor&#8217; in the Code.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1561132277-41509560'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> &#8212; Undertaking</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Dreamvar (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin LLP and another; Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya (a firm) and another (Law Society intervening) [2018] EWCA Civ 1082</a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.propertyprotocols.co.uk/_uploads/downloads/LPSLG-protocol-on-client-identity---final-version-20-May-2019.pdf'>LPSLG protocol on client identity</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The London Property Support Lawyers Group (&#8216;LPSLG&#8217;) released a protocol (&#8216;the Protocol&#8217;) in May 2019 to address the risk of identity fraud, in the light of the Court of Appeal&#8217;s decision in <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> (see <a normcite='0S4D_2878129'>Court of Appeal gives judgment in property fraud cases&#8212;bad news for vendors&#8217; solicitors (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin, Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya)</a>). The provisions set out in this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are those suggested by the LPSLG in order to implement its Protocol. </p></div><div><p><em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> concerned the undertakings given by the seller&#8217;s solicitor as a result of using the 2011 version of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion (&#8216;the Code&#8217;). The 2011 version of the Code contains an undertaking by the seller&#8217;s solicitor that it has the seller&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on completion (and the same undertaking is re-stated in the 2019 version of the Code). The Court of Appeal interpreted &#8216;completion&#8217; to mean a real completion in which real money is exchanged for the title to the land and on that basis a completion with a fraudster is no completion at all. </p></div><div><p>Accordingly, by using the Code, the seller&#8217;s solicitor gives an undertaking that it has the authority of the real owner of the property to complete the transaction. The seller&#8217;s solicitor breaches that undertaking when they purport to complete on behalf of a fraudster impersonating the real owner. </p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.lawsociety.org.uk/support-services/documents/code-for-completion-by-post-2019/'>Law Society Code for Completion by Post 2019</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> case prompted the Law Society to release an updated version of the Code in May 2019. The obligations in the 2019 Code are unchanged from those in the 2011 version, although the numbering has changed. The majority of the changes are to reinforce that the effect of the use of the Code is that the seller&#8217;s solicitor undertakes that the seller is the person genuinely entitled to sell the land. (See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM9_45869'>How does completion happen?</a>.)</p></div><div><p>The Protocol states:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>&#8216;When acting for a buyer, we will not normally request confirmation of identity, or assurances as to the carrying out of AML checks or similar, from the seller&#8217;s solicitors. Our AML responsibilities are not there to create a cause of action between law firms.</p></div></li><li><div><p>Instead we will rely on the seller&#8217;s solicitors&#8217; undertaking that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf (as the Court of Appeal held in Dreamvar that this meant the true owner). Accordingly where the Code is not being adopted, the seller&#8217;s solicitors should be prepared to undertake that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf. No well advised real estate lawyer acting for a buyer would complete without such an undertaking anyway and if completion is to be dealt with via solicitors, no seller&#8217;s solicitor could avoid giving such an undertaking in order for the completion process to proceed with confidence.</p></div></li><li><div><p>We recognise that to be sure that such an undertaking will be given before completion it will be necessary to add a contractual obligation on the seller to procure that their solicitor will provide such an undertaking (whether as part of using the Code or as a stand-alone undertaking) as a pre-condition to completion.&#8217;</p></div></li></ul><div><p>Our view is that the Protocol and LPSLG&#8217;s suggested clauses set out here as clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are a sensible approach to address the risk of identity fraud following <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em>. If using these clauses, the Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should note that they will entitle the Buyer to serve a notice to complete if the Undertaking is not forthcoming. The Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should also be mindful that they will be committed to providing an undertaking on Completion and therefore the firm&#8217;s internal policy regarding giving undertakings will need to be complied with.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:26961143-94A6-4376-915E-4A565C65428A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' opt-key='opt-N68621'><p class='main_heading'>Capital allowances</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d'><div><p>In this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/> the following definitions apply:</p></div><div><lnb-prec:definition><b>CAA&#160;2001</b><div><p>Capital Allowances Act 2001;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Election</b><div><p>an election in respect of the <b>Fixtures</b> under section 198 of <b>CAA 2001</b>in the form annexed to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> as <a id-ref='ukContentItem1526996978-504428464' type='schedule'/>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem7ffa5e9f-e1cc-4d3e-a8e7-2a787fd78282'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Election</p><div><p>For details of elections in real estate transactions, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Fixtures</b><div><p>all plant and machinery which is installed or otherwise fixed in or to the <b>Property</b> so as to become (in law) part of the <b>Property</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem047859c8-e9af-4c86-a104-979d3ffe03cc'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Fixtures</p><div><p>Fixtures are plant or machinery installed or fixed so that they become, in law, part of a building or land. Examples include boilers, alarm systems and fitted kitchen units. There are special rules to determine whether a taxpayer is eligible to claim allowances for expenditure on a fixture. In order to claim allowances, the taxpayer must have an interest in the land or building of which the fixture is part. Further rules determine who may claim allowances where more than one person might have a claim, for instance where a person constructs a building, installs fixtures, then leases the building to another person for a capital sum that includes a payment for those fixtures. For new fixtures, the capital allowances claim is based on the actual expenditure. For more information see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>HMRC</b><div><p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Main Pool Plant</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> included by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in the main pool under section 54 of <b>CAA 2001</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1508418030-2811139'><p class='main_heading'>Main Pool Plant</p><div><p>This definition catches most fixtures that are not within the definition of Special Rate Pool Plant.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Prior Right</b><div><p>has the meaning of prior right for the purposes of section 181(2) of <b>CAA 2001</b>;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Special Rate Pool Plant</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> included by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in a special rate pool under section 104C of <b>CAA 2001</b>.</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1508418030-5461139'><p class='main_heading'>Special Rate Pool Plant</p><div><p>This definition catches <a normcite='0OLV_161955'>integral features</a>, thermal insulation, <a citeref='CITEID_127779' normcite='0OLV_162011'>long-life assets</a> and solar panels. These generally qualify for a lower rate of capital allowances than other fixtures.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition></div></div><div id='ukContentItem501d9779-1046-4b61-8f0d-f5f5c15d812a'><div><p>On <b>Completion</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall make the <b>Election</b> and shall each, within <em type='number'>insert number</em> working days of <b>Completion</b>, deliver the Election to their respective tax inspectors at <b>HMRC</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Special Rate Pool Plant</b> shall be &#163; <em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7d07a11-1d76-48f8-9e04-c9c4b70af874'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/>&#8212;Integral and non-integral Features</p><div><p>Dividing the fixtures into those that attract allowances at a special rate (most commonly, integral features) and those that do not is the absolute minimum HMRC will accept. Depending upon which fixtures exist in the property, it may be necessary to subdivide them further and provide more details, such as 'electrical systems' or 'cold water systems'. In this case it may be better to delete clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650' type='clause'/> and to rely upon on a more detailed breakdown in the proforma election in <a id-ref='ukContentItem1526996978-504428464' type='schedule'/>. See Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_163854'>Election&#8212;capital allowances apportionment on sale of land&#8212;CAA 2001, s 198</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Main Pool Plant</b> shall be <em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem319cec81-cb14-4d36-926e-ce949f567f03'><div><p>Each of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemc5df0ee3-08eb-4925-a8e3-33f52238585a'><div><p>provide all necessary information to each other and take all reasonable steps required to validly make the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem144eeb00-b956-485c-a895-427af7748ae9'><div><p>submit a copy of the Election to <b>HMRC</b> with their tax return for the first period affected by the Election;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItema8e4c85b-ffc7-4568-ace2-7967853612d1'><div><p>take all reasonable steps to ensure that the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> are accepted by <b>HMRC</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdce79faf-9fbc-4a52-afbb-21adf5a4abdf'><div><p>reflect the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> in their respective tax computations and returns.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemacc4de87-96b3-4966-a239-c45bb9bfa360'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that no person has a <b>Prior Right</b> in relation to any of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemabc048f4-b70e-400c-bccd-ec560520ed1a'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that the total and individual figures in the Election are no greater than the amounts incurred by it in accordance with <b>CAA 2001</b> for the provision of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema8c561ba-3721-4e44-b601-b05c3c8c5a73'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/>&#8212;Capital allowances</p><div><p>It is important on any sale of property to consider the position in relation to capital allowances. In order to qualify for plant and machinery allowances, expenditure must be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>capital</p></div></li><li><div><p>on plant and machinery, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>wholly or partly for the purposes of a qualifying activity</p></div></li></ul><div><p>In addition, the person incurring the expenditure must own the plant and machinery as a result of that expenditure. See <a normcite='0OLU_123942'>Captial allowances&#8212;overview Document</a> for further information on the qualification criteria.</p></div><div><p>Properties often have substantial plant and machinery. This may be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>fixtures, and/or</p></div></li><li><div><p>integral features</p></div></li></ul><div><p>For information on the practicalities of capital allowance-related warranties and pre-contract enquiries on a property transfer, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185796'>Plant and machinery allowances on property acquisitions and disposals (including pre-contract enquiries)</a>.</p></div><div><p>The drafting in this clause is for use where the Seller has claimed allowances and the parties will enter into a section 198 election on Completion. For alternative drafting clauses where the <b>Seller</b>:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>has claimed allowances and the parties will apply to the First-tier Tax Tribunal for a just and reasonable allocation of allowances; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has claimed allowances but the information is not available on completion to enable a section 198 election to be entered into at completion; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has not claimed capital allowances, and was not entitled to do so; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>was entitled to claim capital allowances but has not done so</p></div></li></ul><div><p>see the drafting alternatives and notes in Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>.</p></div><div><p>The purpose of a section 198 election is to determine, for capital allowances purposes, the amount of the price for the property that should be attributed to fixtures on which the Seller has claimed allowances.</p></div><div><p>For more information see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a> and <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div><div><p>These clauses are about plant and machinery allowances for fixtures. In some circumstances, the seller of a property will have been claiming structures and buildings allowances (SBAs), which are another type of capital allowance available for (broadly) capital expenditure incurred since 29 October 2018 on the construction, conversion or renovation of a building or structure. If this applies, the buyer of the property would normally inherit the ability to claim SBAs. For wording to address this, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>. For more information, see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0OLV_3243499'>Structures and buildings allowances</a> and <a citeref='CITEID_687537' normcite='0OLV_185796'>Capital allowances on property sales&#8212;pre-contract enquiries&#8212;Structures and buildings allowance</a>.</p></div></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:26961143-94A6-4376-915E-4A565C65428A'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' opt-key='opt-N69736'><p class='main_heading'><lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party></p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1494506087-33817162'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Guarantor</p><div><p>This guarantee clause is suitable for use where the Seller requires some security that the Buyer will observe its obligations in the Agreement. The guarantee clause provides that if the Buyer defaults the guarantor will perform those obligations (and this will include the obligation to pay the purchase price to the Seller). The guarantor also indemnifies the Seller against any losses or liability incurred because of the Buyer&#8217;s default. Delete if no guarantor is being provided.</p></div></div></lnb-prec:title><div><p>In consideration of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> entering into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> at the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>'s request the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> agrees with the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> as a primary obligation as follows:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem6ee7430d-2436-4cbd-a424-5998ea800fc6'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> must perform and observe all of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem10d54eae-693d-4a1f-b86a-88d839de7f41'><div><p>if the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> defaults in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will perform them;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItembb7685cb-daff-41b1-b57c-8b7c6326d0f8'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will indemnify the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> against all claims, demands, damages, losses, liability, costs, fees and expenses sustained by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> by reason of, or arising in any way directly or indirectly out of, the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e'><div><p>if this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> has been disclaimed following the insolvency of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may serve notice in writing on the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> (the &#8216;<b>Guarantor Notice</b>&#8217;) requiring the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> in accordance with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> with the following modifications:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemd421ca62-727b-49e6-9240-91993f13ced3'><div><p>all obligations of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be deemed to have been entered into by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> as though it were named as <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in place of the party defined as the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem816b7794-9d86-4cb3-84fa-81079304136a'><div><p>if a notice to complete served by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> on the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> has expired at the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b> the <b>Completion Date</b> shall be <em type='number'>5</em> working days after the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem545c300a-9165-4d26-9d02-5ef27f83db51'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> is to pay:</p></div><div number-type='loweralpha'><div id='ukContentItemaacf6481-adc4-4d44-9044-072c062496b1'><div><p><b>Interest</b> on the balance of the <b>Price</b> from the contractual <b>Completion Date</b> until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdbf94e06-289b-4a0a-bce1-84e84f47f6ec'><div><p>all money expended by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in consequence of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default from the date of expenditure until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days;</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7203eb7e-1bf8-472d-bd14-67e4f0494902'><div><p>for the avoidance of doubt no further deposit shall be payable by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem64b572ca-3e0c-48bf-9c51-f30482836137'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Disclaimer</p><div><p>This gives the Seller the ability to require the Guarantor to take a transfer of the Property in the event that the Agreement is disclaimed. See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM3_149095'>The process of disclaimer by a liquidator or trustee in bankruptcy under sections 178 or 315 of the Insolvency Act 1986</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1'><div><p>the liability of the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> shall not be affected reduced or extinguished by:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb2b70c21-0e1a-4ca0-a124-6ad25dd6e5f4'><div><p>any time or indulgence granted by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> to the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemfb07de4a-86ee-446c-b76f-346d6ca05a86'><div><p>any neglect or forbearance of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in enforcing its rights under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemaa2a78f2-df61-4f7b-8af6-482506233419'><div><p>any variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> agreed between the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>; or</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89'><div><p>the fact that any other person or entity comprising the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> or intended to comprise the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> has not executed this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or is not bound by the guarantee in this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>;</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem94e8ddef-544f-4d85-bd54-629d58779cbf'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89' type='clause'/>&#8212;Signatories</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Harvey v Dunbar Assets [2013] All ER (D) 400 (Jul)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>In <em class='it'>Harvey</em> the court decided a bank guarantee was subject to a condition that it would be signed by all the other intended guarantors named in the deed, and so liability as a &#8216;Guarantor&#8217; was only imposed on an individual signatory to the document in circumstances where all the named individuals did indeed sign the guarantee. This meant the individual being sued was never on the hook as guarantor because one of the intended guarantors had not signed the document (his signature had been forged). The guarantee was a single composite document, which sought to impose joint and several liability on four individuals together defined as &#8216;the Guarantor&#8217; and envisaged it would be signed by all four individuals. There was nothing in the wording excluding the result that all intended guarantors had to sign for an individual guarantor to be liable. It is assumed that the contract into which this clause is inserted provides for joint and several liability where obligations are owed by more than one party. This sub-clause is an attempt to avoid the problem in <em class='it'>Harvey</em> as, whilst the case relates to a bank guarantee it could, of course, be of wider application in the context of guarantees. It has not been tested in court.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf2e07994-da50-4aed-8b93-04436780dc3b'><div><p>anything else by which apart from this clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1' type='clause'/> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> would be released other than a release under seal.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:35E66E21-09A6-4CEC-95DE-90A96ACCB70B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' opt-key='opt-N73574'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p> No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party <em type='text'>such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any securities exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem52b8262f-83f4-481e-a3e0-95e8d8a98954'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This is a short form announcements provision. For a longer form clause see: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>This clause is drafted on the basis that:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>it binds all of the parties to the Agreement</p></div></li><li><div><p>the general prohibition on announcements and other public disclosures relates to the existence of the Agreement itself and any of the matters contained in it</p></div></li><li><div><p>the parties will remain binding for the duration of the Agreement (if the clause is intended to survive termination of the Agreement, this may be stated in the clause itself or elsewhere in the Agreement, eg in the termination or survival clause)</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made with the prior written consent of the other party, with no express process being set out to obtain such consent, although it must not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made as required by law, a court or any other authority, without any prior written consent from the other party or any consultation with them being required.</p></div><div><p>The announcements clause normally forms part of the main contract relating to a transaction or arrangement and, as such, will take effect on the signing of the contract. Prior to signing, any announcement relating to the proposed transaction or arrangement will normally be restricted by the terms of a confidentiality agreement entered into between the parties. The terms of such a confidentiality agreement should be considered in drafting an announcements clause; it would be usual for the announcements clause (along with any confidentiality clause) to replace this initial confidentiality agreement.</p></div><div><p>It is necessary to consider an announcements clause in the Agreement in conjunction with any confidentiality clause, to ensure that the two work effectively together.</p></div></li></ul></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:35E66E21-09A6-4CEC-95DE-90A96ACCB70B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' opt-key='opt-N72516'><p class='main_heading'>Guarantor</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1494500282-101398358'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Guarantor</p><div><p>This guarantee clause is suitable for use where the Seller requires some security that the Buyer will observe its obligations in the Agreement. The guarantee clause provides that if the Buyer defaults the guarantor will perform those obligations (and this will include the obligation to pay the Price (and the Chattels Price, if included) to the Seller). The guarantor also indemnifies the Seller against any losses or liability incurred because of the Buyer&#8217;s default. Delete if no guarantor is being provided.</p></div><div><p>Where the agreed heads of terms incorporate a rental guarantee by the Seller for void occupational rents post-Completion, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OL6_245546'>Rental guarantee schedule</a>.</p></div></div></lnb-prec:title><div><p>In consideration of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> entering into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> at the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor's</lnb-prec:party> request the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> agrees with the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> as a primary obligation as follows:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem6ee7430d-2436-4cbd-a424-5998ea800fc6'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> must perform and observe all of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem10d54eae-693d-4a1f-b86a-88d839de7f41'><div><p>if the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> defaults in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will perform them;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItembb7685cb-daff-41b1-b57c-8b7c6326d0f8'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will indemnify the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> against all claims, demands, damages, losses, liability, costs, fees and expenses sustained by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> by reason of, or arising in any way directly or indirectly out of, the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e'><div><p>if this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> has been disclaimed following the insolvency of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may serve notice in writing on the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> (the &#8216;<b>Guarantor Notice</b>&#8217;) requiring the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> in accordance with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> with the following modifications:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemd421ca62-727b-49e6-9240-91993f13ced3'><div><p>all obligations of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be deemed to have been entered into by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> as though it were named as <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in place of the party defined as the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem816b7794-9d86-4cb3-84fa-81079304136a'><div><p>if a notice to complete served by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> on the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> has expired at the date of service of the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> Notice the <b>Completion Date</b> shall be <em type='number'>5</em> working days after the date of service of the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> Notice;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem545c300a-9165-4d26-9d02-5ef27f83db51'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> is to pay:</p></div><div number-type='loweralpha'><div id='ukContentItemaacf6481-adc4-4d44-9044-072c062496b1'><div><p><b>Interest</b> on the balance of the <b>Price</b> from the contractual <b>Completion Date</b> until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdbf94e06-289b-4a0a-bce1-84e84f47f6ec'><div><p>all money expended by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in consequence of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default from the date of expenditure until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days;</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7203eb7e-1bf8-472d-bd14-67e4f0494902'><div><p>for the avoidance of doubt no further deposit shall be payable by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem64b572ca-3e0c-48bf-9c51-f30482836137'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Disclaimer</p><div><p>This gives the Seller the ability to require the Guarantor to take a transfer of the Property in the event that the Agreement is disclaimed. See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM3_149095'>The process of disclaimer by a liquidator or trustee in bankruptcy under sections 178 or 315 of the Insolvency Act 1986</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1'><div><p>the liability of the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> shall not be affected reduced or extinguished by:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb2b70c21-0e1a-4ca0-a124-6ad25dd6e5f4'><div><p>any time or indulgence granted by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> to the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemfb07de4a-86ee-446c-b76f-346d6ca05a86'><div><p>any neglect or forbearance of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in enforcing its rights under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemaa2a78f2-df61-4f7b-8af6-482506233419'><div><p>any variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> agreed between the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>; or</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89'><div><p>the fact that any other person or entity comprising the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> or intended to comprise the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> has not executed this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or is not bound by the guarantee in this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>;</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem94e8ddef-544f-4d85-bd54-629d58779cbf'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89' type='clause'/>&#8212;Signatories</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Harvey v Dunbar Assets plc [2013] All ER (D) 400 (Jul)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>In <em class='it'>Harvey</em> the court decided a bank guarantee was subject to a condition that it would be signed by all the other intended guarantors named in the deed, and, so, liability as a &#8216;Guarantor&#8217; was only imposed on an individual signatory to the document in circumstances where all the named individuals did indeed sign the guarantee. This meant the individual being sued was never on the hook as guarantor because one of the intended guarantors had not signed the document (his signature had been forged). The guarantee was a single composite document, which sought to impose joint and several liability on four individuals together defined as &#8216;the Guarantor&#8217; and envisaged it would be signed by all four individuals. There was nothing in the wording excluding the result that all intended guarantors had to sign for an individual guarantor to be liable. This Agreement provides for joint and several liability where obligations are owed by more than one party (see clause 2.1.6). This sub-clause is an attempt to avoid the problem in <em class='it'>Harvey</em> as whilst the case relates to a bank guarantee it could, of course, be of wider application in the context of guarantees. It has not been tested in court.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf2e07994-da50-4aed-8b93-04436780dc3b'><div><p>anything else by which apart from this clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1' type='clause'/> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> would be released other than a release under seal.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:35E66E21-09A6-4CEC-95DE-90A96ACCB70B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' opt-key='opt-N70726'><p class='main_heading'>Capital allowances</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d'><div><p>In this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/> the following definitions apply:</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema8c561ba-3721-4e44-b601-b05c3c8c5a73'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/>&#8212;Capital allowances</p><div><p>It is important on any sale of property to consider the position in relation to capital allowances. In order to qualify for plant and machinery allowances, expenditure must be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>capital</p></div></li><li><div><p>on plant and machinery, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>wholly or partly for the purposes of a qualifying activity</p></div></li></ul><div><p>In addition, the person incurring the expenditure must own the plant and machinery as a result of that expenditure. See: <a normcite='0OLU_123942'>Capital allowances&#8212;overview</a> for further information on the qualification criteria.</p></div><div><p>Properties often have substantial plant and machinery. This may be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>fixtures, and/or</p></div></li><li><div><p>integral features</p></div></li></ul><div><p>For information on the practicalities of capital allowance-related warranties and pre-contract enquiries on a property transfer, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185796'>Plant and machinery allowances on property acquisitions and disposals (including pre-contract enquiries)</a>.</p></div><div><p>The drafting in this clause is for use where the Seller has claimed allowances and the parties will enter into a s 198 election on Completion. For alternative drafting clauses where the Seller:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>has claimed allowances and the parties will apply to the First-tier Tax Tribunal for a just and reasonable allocation of allowances; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has claimed allowances but the information is not available on completion to enable a s198 election to be entered into at completion; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has not claimed capital allowances, and was not entitled to do so; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>was entitled to claim capital allowances but has not done so</p></div></li></ul><div><p>see the drafting alternatives and notes in Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>.</p></div><div><p>The purpose of a section 198 election is to determine, for capital allowances purposes, the amount of the price for the Property that should be attributed to fixtures on which the Seller has claimed allowances.</p></div><div><p>For more information see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a> and <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div><div><p>These clauses are about plant and machinery allowances for fixtures. In some circumstances, the seller of a property will have been claiming structures and buildings allowances (SBAs), which are another type of capital allowance available for (broadly) capital expenditure incurred since 29 October 2018 on the construction, conversion or renovation of a building or structure. If this applies, the buyer of the property would normally inherit the ability to claim SBAs. For drafting to address this situation, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>. For more information, see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0OLV_3243499'>Structures and buildings allowances</a> and <a citeref='CITEID_687537' normcite='0OLV_185796'>Capital allowances on property sales&#8212;pre-contract enquiries&#8212;Structures and buildings allowance</a>.</p></div></div></div><div><lnb-prec:definition><b>CAA&#160;2001</b><div><p>Capital Allowances Act 2001;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Election</b><div><p>an election in respect of the <b>Fixtures</b> under section 198 of <b>CAA 2001</b>, in the form annexed as <a id-ref='ukContentItem1526894273-794091583' type='schedule'/>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem7ffa5e9f-e1cc-4d3e-a8e7-2a787fd78282'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Election</p><div><p>For details of elections in real estate transactions, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Fixtures</b><div><p>all plant and machinery which is installed or otherwise fixed in or to the <b>Property</b> so as to become (in law) part of the <b>Property</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem047859c8-e9af-4c86-a104-979d3ffe03cc'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Fixtures</p><div><p>Fixtures are plant or machinery that is installed or fixed so that they become, in law, part of a building or land. Examples include boilers, alarm systems and fitted kitchen units. There are special rules to determine whether a taxpayer is eligible to claim allowances for expenditure on a fixture. In order to claim allowances, the taxpayer must have an interest in the land or building of which the fixture is part. Further rules determine who may claim allowances where more than one person might have a claim, for instance where a person constructs a building, installs fixtures, then leases the building to another person for a capital sum that includes a payment for those fixtures. For new fixtures, the capital allowances claim is based on the actual expenditure. For more information see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Main Pool Plant</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> included by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in the main pool under section 54 of <b>CAA 2001</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1508418030-2811139'><p class='main_heading'>Main Pool Plant</p><div><p>This definition catches most fixtures that are not within the definition of Special Rate Pool Plant.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Prior Right</b><div><p>has the meaning of &#8216;prior right&#8217; for the purposes of section 181(2) of CAA 2001;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Special Rate Pool Plant</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> included by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in a special rate pool under section 104C of <b>CAA 2001</b>.</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1508418030-5461139'><p class='main_heading'>Special Rate Pool Plant</p><div><p>This definition catches <a normcite='0OLV_161955'>integral features</a>, thermal insulation, <a citeref='CITEID_127779' normcite='0OLV_162011'>long-life assets</a> and solar panels. These generally qualify for a lower rate of capital allowances than other fixtures.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition></div></div><div id='ukContentItem501d9779-1046-4b61-8f0d-f5f5c15d812a'><div><p>On <b>Completion</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall make the <b>Election</b> and shall each, within <em type='number'>insert number</em> working days of <b>Completion</b>, deliver the <b>Election</b> to their respective tax inspectors at <b>HMRC</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Special Rate Pool Plant</b> shall be &#163; <em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7d07a11-1d76-48f8-9e04-c9c4b70af874'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/>&#8212;Integral and Non-integral Features</p><div><p>Dividing the fixtures into those that attract allowances at a special rate (most commonly, integral features) and those that do not is the absolute minimum HMRC will accept. Depending on which fixtures exist in the Property, it may be necessary to subdivide them further and provide more details, such as 'electrical systems' or 'cold water systems'. In this case it may be better to delete clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650' type='clause'/> rely on a more detailed breakdown in the pro forma election in <a id-ref='ukContentItem1526894273-794091583' type='schedule'/>. See Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_163854'>Election&#8212;capital allowances apportionment on sale of land&#8212;CAA 2001, s 198</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Main Pool Plant</b> shall be <em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem319cec81-cb14-4d36-926e-ce949f567f03'><div><p>Each of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemc5df0ee3-08eb-4925-a8e3-33f52238585a'><div><p>provide all necessary information to each other and take all reasonable steps required to validly make the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem144eeb00-b956-485c-a895-427af7748ae9'><div><p>submit a copy of the <b>Election</b> to <b>HMRC</b> with their tax return for the first period affected by the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItema8e4c85b-ffc7-4568-ace2-7967853612d1'><div><p>take all reasonable steps to ensure that the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> are accepted by <b>HMRC</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdce79faf-9fbc-4a52-afbb-21adf5a4abdf'><div><p>reflect the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> in their respective tax computations and returns.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemacc4de87-96b3-4966-a239-c45bb9bfa360'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that no person has a <b>Prior Right</b> in relation to any of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemabc048f4-b70e-400c-bccd-ec560520ed1a'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that the total and individual figures in the <b>Election</b> are no greater than the amounts incurred by it in accordance with <b>CAA 2001</b> for the provision of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1561132277-50196260", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:35E66E21-09A6-4CEC-95DE-90A96ACCB70B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' opt-key='opt-590EB33F'><p class='main_heading'>Undertaking</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-42027560'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall procure that, by the time of <b>Completion</b>, the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of an undertaking (&#8216;the Undertaking&#8217;) given by the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> (whether by the adoption of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion by Post (2019) (&#8216;the Code&#8217;) or otherwise) that the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on <b>Completion</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50459160'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall not be obliged to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> unless and until the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of the Undertaking. If the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> is ready, able and willing to complete but the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> do not have the benefit of the Undertaking, the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall be treated as in default and not being ready, able and willing to complete and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be entitled to give the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> a notice to complete.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-41490460'><div><p>In this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/>, the term &#8216;Seller&#8217; has the same meaning as in the Code and the phrase &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitors&#8217; has the same meaning as is given to the term &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitor&#8217; in the Code.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1561132277-41509560'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> &#8212; Undertaking</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Dreamvar (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin LLP and another; Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya (a firm) and another (Law Society intervening) [2018] EWCA Civ 1082</a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.propertyprotocols.co.uk/_uploads/downloads/LPSLG-protocol-on-client-identity---final-version-20-May-2019.pdf'>LPSLG protocol on client identity</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The London Property Support Lawyers Group (&#8216;LPSLG&#8217;) released a protocol (&#8216;the Protocol&#8217;) in May 2019 to address the risk of identity fraud, in the light of the Court of Appeal&#8217;s decision in <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> (see <a normcite='0S4D_2878129'>Court of Appeal gives judgment in property fraud cases&#8212;bad news for vendors&#8217; solicitors (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin, Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya)</a>). The provisions set out in this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are those suggested by the LPSLG in order to implement its Protocol. </p></div><div><p><em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> concerned the undertakings given by the seller&#8217;s solicitor as a result of using the 2011 version of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion (&#8216;the Code&#8217;). The 2011 version of the Code contains an undertaking by the seller&#8217;s solicitor that it has the seller&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on completion (and the same undertaking is re-stated in the 2019 version of the Code). The Court of Appeal interpreted &#8216;completion&#8217; to mean a real completion in which real money is exchanged for the title to the land and on that basis a completion with a fraudster is no completion at all. </p></div><div><p>Accordingly, by using the Code, the seller&#8217;s solicitor gives an undertaking that it has the authority of the real owner of the property to complete the transaction. The seller&#8217;s solicitor breaches that undertaking when they purport to complete on behalf of a fraudster impersonating the real owner. </p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.lawsociety.org.uk/support-services/documents/code-for-completion-by-post-2019/'>Law Society Code for Completion by Post 2019</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> case prompted the Law Society to release an updated version of the Code in May 2019. The obligations in the 2019 Code are unchanged from those in the 2011 version, although the numbering has changed. The majority of the changes are to reinforce that the effect of the use of the Code is that the seller&#8217;s solicitor undertakes that the seller is the person genuinely entitled to sell the land. (See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM9_45869'>How does completion happen?</a>.)</p></div><div><p>The Protocol states:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>&#8216;When acting for a buyer, we will not normally request confirmation of identity, or assurances as to the carrying out of AML checks or similar, from the seller&#8217;s solicitors. Our AML responsibilities are not there to create a cause of action between law firms.</p></div></li><li><div><p>Instead we will rely on the seller&#8217;s solicitors&#8217; undertaking that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf (as the Court of Appeal held in Dreamvar that this meant the true owner). Accordingly where the Code is not being adopted, the seller&#8217;s solicitors should be prepared to undertake that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf. No well advised real estate lawyer acting for a buyer would complete without such an undertaking anyway and if completion is to be dealt with via solicitors, no seller&#8217;s solicitor could avoid giving such an undertaking in order for the completion process to proceed with confidence.</p></div></li><li><div><p>We recognise that to be sure that such an undertaking will be given before completion it will be necessary to add a contractual obligation on the seller to procure that their solicitor will provide such an undertaking (whether as part of using the Code or as a stand-alone undertaking) as a pre-condition to completion.&#8217;</p></div></li></ul><div><p>Our view is that the Protocol and LPSLG&#8217;s suggested clauses set out here as clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are a sensible approach to address the risk of identity fraud following <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em>. If using these clauses, the Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should note that they will entitle the Buyer to serve a notice to complete if the Undertaking is not forthcoming. The Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should also be mindful that they will be committed to providing an undertaking on Completion and therefore the firm&#8217;s internal policy regarding giving undertakings will need to be complied with.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1561132277-50196260", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:011FFCF6-2EB3-4D9E-8D55-11F905FFC400'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' opt-key='opt-590EB33F'><p class='main_heading'>Undertaking</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-42027560'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall procure that, by the time of <b>Completion</b>, the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of an undertaking (&#8216;the Undertaking&#8217;) given by the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> (whether by the adoption of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion by Post (2019) (&#8216;the Code&#8217;) or otherwise) that the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on <b>Completion</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50459160'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall not be obliged to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> unless and until the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of the Undertaking. If the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> is ready, able and willing to complete but the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> do not have the benefit of the Undertaking, the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall be treated as in default and not being ready, able and willing to complete and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be entitled to give the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> a notice to complete.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-41490460'><div><p>In this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/>, the term &#8216;Seller&#8217; has the same meaning as in the Code and the phrase &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitors&#8217; has the same meaning as is given to the term &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitor&#8217; in the Code.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1561132277-41509560'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> &#8212; Undertaking</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Dreamvar (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin LLP and another; Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya (a firm) and another (Law Society intervening) [2018] EWCA Civ 1082</a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.propertyprotocols.co.uk/_uploads/downloads/LPSLG-protocol-on-client-identity---final-version-20-May-2019.pdf'>LPSLG protocol on client identity</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The London Property Support Lawyers Group (&#8216;LPSLG&#8217;) released a protocol (&#8216;the Protocol&#8217;) in May 2019 to address the risk of identity fraud, in the light of the Court of Appeal&#8217;s decision in <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> (see <a normcite='0S4D_2878129'>Court of Appeal gives judgment in property fraud cases&#8212;bad news for vendors&#8217; solicitors (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin, Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya)</a>). The provisions set out in this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are those suggested by the LPSLG in order to implement its Protocol. </p></div><div><p><em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> concerned the undertakings given by the seller&#8217;s solicitor as a result of using the 2011 version of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion (&#8216;the Code&#8217;). The 2011 version of the Code contains an undertaking by the seller&#8217;s solicitor that it has the seller&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on completion (and the same undertaking is re-stated in the 2019 version of the Code). The Court of Appeal interpreted &#8216;completion&#8217; to mean a real completion in which real money is exchanged for the title to the land and on that basis a completion with a fraudster is no completion at all. </p></div><div><p>Accordingly, by using the Code, the seller&#8217;s solicitor gives an undertaking that it has the authority of the real owner of the property to complete the transaction. The seller&#8217;s solicitor breaches that undertaking when they purport to complete on behalf of a fraudster impersonating the real owner. </p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.lawsociety.org.uk/support-services/documents/code-for-completion-by-post-2019/'>Law Society Code for Completion by Post 2019</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> case prompted the Law Society to release an updated version of the Code in May 2019. The obligations in the 2019 Code are unchanged from those in the 2011 version, although the numbering has changed. The majority of the changes are to reinforce that the effect of the use of the Code is that the seller&#8217;s solicitor undertakes that the seller is the person genuinely entitled to sell the land. (See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM9_45869'>How does completion happen?</a>.)</p></div><div><p>The Protocol states:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>&#8216;When acting for a buyer, we will not normally request confirmation of identity, or assurances as to the carrying out of AML checks or similar, from the seller&#8217;s solicitors. Our AML responsibilities are not there to create a cause of action between law firms.</p></div></li><li><div><p>Instead we will rely on the seller&#8217;s solicitors&#8217; undertaking that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf (as the Court of Appeal held in Dreamvar that this meant the true owner). Accordingly where the Code is not being adopted, the seller&#8217;s solicitors should be prepared to undertake that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf. No well advised real estate lawyer acting for a buyer would complete without such an undertaking anyway and if completion is to be dealt with via solicitors, no seller&#8217;s solicitor could avoid giving such an undertaking in order for the completion process to proceed with confidence.</p></div></li><li><div><p>We recognise that to be sure that such an undertaking will be given before completion it will be necessary to add a contractual obligation on the seller to procure that their solicitor will provide such an undertaking (whether as part of using the Code or as a stand-alone undertaking) as a pre-condition to completion.&#8217;</p></div></li></ul><div><p>Our view is that the Protocol and LPSLG&#8217;s suggested clauses set out here as clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are a sensible approach to address the risk of identity fraud following <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em>. If using these clauses, the Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should note that they will entitle the Buyer to serve a notice to complete if the Undertaking is not forthcoming. The Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should also be mindful that they will be committed to providing an undertaking on Completion and therefore the firm&#8217;s internal policy regarding giving undertakings will need to be complied with.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:011FFCF6-2EB3-4D9E-8D55-11F905FFC400'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' opt-key='opt-N70787'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p> No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party <em type='text'>such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any securities exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem52b8262f-83f4-481e-a3e0-95e8d8a98954'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This is a short form announcements provision. For a longer form see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>This clause is drafted on the basis that:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>it binds all of the parties to the Agreement</p></div></li><li><div><p>the general prohibition on announcements and other public disclosures relates to the existence of the contract itself and any of the matters contained in it</p></div></li><li><div><p>the parties will remain bound for the duration of the Agreement (if the clause is intended to survive termination of the agreement, this may be stated in the clause itself or elsewhere in the Agreement, eg in the termination or survival clause)</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made with the prior written consent of the other party, with no express process being set out to obtain such consent, although it must not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made as required by law, a court or any other authority, without any prior written consent from the other party or any consultation with them being required.</p></div><div><p>The announcements clause normally forms part of the main agreement relating to a transaction or arrangement and, as such, will take effect on the signing of the agreement. Prior to signing, any announcement relating to the proposed transaction or arrangement will normally be restricted by the terms of a confidentiality agreement entered into between the parties. The terms of such a confidentiality agreement should be considered in drafting an announcements clause; it would be usual for the announcements clause (along with any confidentiality clause) to replace this initial confidentiality agreement.</p></div><div><p>It is necessary to consider an announcements clause in an agreement in conjunction with any confidentiality clause, to ensure that the two work effectively together</p></div></li></ul></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:011FFCF6-2EB3-4D9E-8D55-11F905FFC400'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' opt-key='opt-N69736'><p class='main_heading'><lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party></p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1494506087-33817162'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Guarantor</p><div><p>This guarantee clause is suitable for use where the Seller requires some security that the Buyer will observe its obligations in the Agreement. The guarantee clause provides that if the Buyer defaults the Guarantor will perform those obligations (and this will include the obligation to pay the purchase price to the Seller). The Guarantor also indemnifies the Seller against any losses or liability incurred because of the Buyer&#8217;s default. Delete if no guarantor is being provided.</p></div></div></lnb-prec:title><div><p>In consideration of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> entering into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> at the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s request the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> agrees with the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> as a primary obligation as follows:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem6ee7430d-2436-4cbd-a424-5998ea800fc6'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> must perform and observe all of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem10d54eae-693d-4a1f-b86a-88d839de7f41'><div><p>if the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> defaults in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will perform them;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItembb7685cb-daff-41b1-b57c-8b7c6326d0f8'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will indemnify the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> against all claims, demands, damages, losses, liability, costs, fees and expenses sustained by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> by reason of, or arising in any way directly or indirectly out of, the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s default in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e'><div><p>if this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> has been disclaimed following the insolvency of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may serve notice in writing on the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> (the &#8216;<b>Guarantor Notice</b>&#8217;) requiring the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> in accordance with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> with the following modifications:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemd421ca62-727b-49e6-9240-91993f13ced3'><div><p>all obligations of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be deemed to have been entered into by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> as though it were named as <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in place of the party defined as the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem816b7794-9d86-4cb3-84fa-81079304136a'><div><p>if a notice to complete served by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> on the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> has expired at the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b> the <b>Completion Date</b> shall be <em type='number'>5</em> working days after the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem545c300a-9165-4d26-9d02-5ef27f83db51'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> is to pay:</p></div><div number-type='loweralpha'><div id='ukContentItemaacf6481-adc4-4d44-9044-072c062496b1'><div><p><b>Interest</b> on the balance of the <b>Price</b> from the contractual <b>Completion Date</b> until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdbf94e06-289b-4a0a-bce1-84e84f47f6ec'><div><p>all money expended by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in consequence of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s default from the date of expenditure until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days;</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7203eb7e-1bf8-472d-bd14-67e4f0494902'><div><p>for the avoidance of doubt no further deposit shall be payable by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem64b572ca-3e0c-48bf-9c51-f30482836137'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Disclaimer</p><div><p>This gives the Seller the ability to require the Guarantor to take a transfer of the Property in the event that the Agreement is disclaimed. See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM3_149095'>The process of disclaimer by a liquidator or trustee in bankruptcy under sections 178 or 315 of the Insolvency Act 1986</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1'><div><p>the liability of the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> shall not be affected reduced or extinguished by:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb2b70c21-0e1a-4ca0-a124-6ad25dd6e5f4'><div><p>any time or indulgence granted by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> to the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemfb07de4a-86ee-446c-b76f-346d6ca05a86'><div><p>any neglect or forbearance of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in enforcing its rights under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemaa2a78f2-df61-4f7b-8af6-482506233419'><div><p>any variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> agreed between the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>; or</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89'><div><p>the fact that any other person or entity comprising the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> or intended to comprise the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> has not executed this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or is not bound by the guarantee in this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>;</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem94e8ddef-544f-4d85-bd54-629d58779cbf'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89' type='clause'/>&#8212;Signatories</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Harvey v Dunbar Assets [2013] All ER (D) 400 (Jul)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>In <em class='it'>Harvey</em> the court decided a bank guarantee was subject to a condition that it would be signed by all the other intended guarantors named in the deed, and so liability as a &#8216;Guarantor&#8217; was only imposed on an individual signatory to the document in circumstances where all the named individuals did indeed sign the guarantee. This meant the individual being sued was never on the hook as guarantor because one of the intended guarantors had not signed the document (his signature had been forged). The guarantee was a single composite document, which sought to impose joint and several liability on four individuals together defined as &#8216;the Guarantor&#8217; and envisaged it would be signed by all four individuals. There was nothing in the wording excluding the result that all intended guarantors had to sign for an individual guarantor to be liable. It is assumed that the contract into which this clause is inserted provides for joint and several liability where obligations are owed by more than one party. This sub-clause is an attempt to avoid the problem in <em class='it'>Harvey</em> as, whilst the case relates to a bank guarantee it could, of course, be of wider application in the context of guarantees. It has not been tested in court.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf2e07994-da50-4aed-8b93-04436780dc3b'><div><p>anything else by which apart from this clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1' type='clause'/> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> would be released other than a release under seal.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PLANNING::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem1561132277-50196260", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FA34D42B-A159-4A0F-A9A2-3D91AA24C4C3'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' opt-key='opt-590EB33F'><p class='main_heading'>Undertaking</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-42027560'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall procure that, by the time of <b>Completion</b>, the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of an undertaking (&#8216;the Undertaking&#8217;) given by the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> (whether by the adoption of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion by Post (2019) (&#8216;the Code&#8217;) or otherwise) that the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on <b>Completion</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50459160'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall not be obliged to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> unless and until the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of the Undertaking. If the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> is ready, able and willing to complete but the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> do not have the benefit of the Undertaking, the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall be treated as in default and not being ready, able and willing to complete and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be entitled to give the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> a notice to complete.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-41490460'><div><p>In this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/>, the term &#8216;Seller&#8217; has the same meaning as in the Code and the phrase &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitors&#8217; has the same meaning as is given to the term &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitor&#8217; in the Code.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1561132277-41509560'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> &#8212; Undertaking</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Dreamvar (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin LLP and another; Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya (a firm) and another (Law Society intervening) [2018] EWCA Civ 1082</a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.propertyprotocols.co.uk/_uploads/downloads/LPSLG-protocol-on-client-identity---final-version-20-May-2019.pdf'>LPSLG protocol on client identity</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The London Property Support Lawyers Group (&#8216;LPSLG&#8217;) released a protocol (&#8216;the Protocol&#8217;) in May 2019 to address the risk of identity fraud, in the light of the Court of Appeal&#8217;s decision in <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> (see <a normcite='0S4D_2878129'>Court of Appeal gives judgment in property fraud cases&#8212;bad news for vendors&#8217; solicitors (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin, Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya)</a>). The provisions set out in this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are those suggested by the LPSLG in order to implement its Protocol. </p></div><div><p><em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> concerned the undertakings given by the seller&#8217;s solicitor as a result of using the 2011 version of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion (&#8216;the Code&#8217;). The 2011 version of the Code contains an undertaking by the seller&#8217;s solicitor that it has the seller&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on completion (and the same undertaking is re-stated in the 2019 version of the Code). The Court of Appeal interpreted &#8216;completion&#8217; to mean a real completion in which real money is exchanged for the title to the land and on that basis a completion with a fraudster is no completion at all. </p></div><div><p>Accordingly, by using the Code, the seller&#8217;s solicitor gives an undertaking that it has the authority of the real owner of the property to complete the transaction. The seller&#8217;s solicitor breaches that undertaking when they purport to complete on behalf of a fraudster impersonating the real owner. </p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.lawsociety.org.uk/support-services/documents/code-for-completion-by-post-2019/'>Law Society Code for Completion by Post 2019</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> case prompted the Law Society to release an updated version of the Code in May 2019. The obligations in the 2019 Code are unchanged from those in the 2011 version, although the numbering has changed. The majority of the changes are to reinforce that the effect of the use of the Code is that the seller&#8217;s solicitor undertakes that the seller is the person genuinely entitled to sell the land. (See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM9_45869'>How does completion happen?</a>.)</p></div><div><p>The Protocol states:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>&#8216;When acting for a buyer, we will not normally request confirmation of identity, or assurances as to the carrying out of AML checks or similar, from the seller&#8217;s solicitors. Our AML responsibilities are not there to create a cause of action between law firms.</p></div></li><li><div><p>Instead we will rely on the seller&#8217;s solicitors&#8217; undertaking that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf (as the Court of Appeal held in Dreamvar that this meant the true owner). Accordingly where the Code is not being adopted, the seller&#8217;s solicitors should be prepared to undertake that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf. No well advised real estate lawyer acting for a buyer would complete without such an undertaking anyway and if completion is to be dealt with via solicitors, no seller&#8217;s solicitor could avoid giving such an undertaking in order for the completion process to proceed with confidence.</p></div></li><li><div><p>We recognise that to be sure that such an undertaking will be given before completion it will be necessary to add a contractual obligation on the seller to procure that their solicitor will provide such an undertaking (whether as part of using the Code or as a stand-alone undertaking) as a pre-condition to completion.&#8217;</p></div></li></ul><div><p>Our view is that the Protocol and LPSLG&#8217;s suggested clauses set out here as clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are a sensible approach to address the risk of identity fraud following <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em>. If using these clauses, the Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should note that they will entitle the Buyer to serve a notice to complete if the Undertaking is not forthcoming. The Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should also be mindful that they will be committed to providing an undertaking on Completion and therefore the firm&#8217;s internal policy regarding giving undertakings will need to be complied with.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A6711E0-BD8A-4AD3-8E95-C97CC10C5975'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' opt-key='opt-N72516'><p class='main_heading'>Guarantor</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1494500282-101398358'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Guarantor</p><div><p>This guarantee clause is suitable for use where the Seller requires some security that the Buyer will observe its obligations in the contract. The guarantee clause provides that if the Buyer defaults the guarantor will perform those obligations (and this will include the obligation to pay the purchase price to the Seller). The guarantor also indemnifies the Seller against any losses or liability incurred because of the Buyer&#8217;s default. Delete if no guarantor is being provided.</p></div><div><p>Where the agreed heads of terms incorporate a rental guarantee by the Seller for void occupational rents post-Completion, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OL6_245546'>Rental guarantee schedule</a>.</p></div></div></lnb-prec:title><div><p>In consideration of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> entering into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> at the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor's</lnb-prec:party> request the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> agrees with the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> as a primary obligation as follows:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem6ee7430d-2436-4cbd-a424-5998ea800fc6'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> must perform and observe all of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem10d54eae-693d-4a1f-b86a-88d839de7f41'><div><p>if the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> defaults in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will perform them;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItembb7685cb-daff-41b1-b57c-8b7c6326d0f8'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will indemnify the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> against all claims, demands, damages, losses, liability, costs, fees and expenses sustained by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> by reason of, or arising in any way directly or indirectly out of, the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e'><div><p>if this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> has been disclaimed following the insolvency of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may serve notice in writing on the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> (the &#8216;<b>Guarantor Notice</b>&#8217;) requiring the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> in accordance with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> with the following modifications:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemd421ca62-727b-49e6-9240-91993f13ced3'><div><p>all obligations of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be deemed to have been entered into by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> as though it were named as <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in place of the party defined as the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem816b7794-9d86-4cb3-84fa-81079304136a'><div><p>if a notice to complete served by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> on the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> has expired at the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b> the <b>Completion Date</b> shall be <em type='number'>5</em> working days after the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem545c300a-9165-4d26-9d02-5ef27f83db51'><div><p>the <b>Guarantor</b> is to pay:</p></div><div number-type='loweralpha'><div id='ukContentItemaacf6481-adc4-4d44-9044-072c062496b1'><div><p><b>Interest</b> on the balance of the <b>Price</b> from the contractual <b>Completion Date</b> until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdbf94e06-289b-4a0a-bce1-84e84f47f6ec'><div><p>all money expended by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in consequence of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default from the date of expenditure until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days;</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7203eb7e-1bf8-472d-bd14-67e4f0494902'><div><p>for the avoidance of doubt no further deposit shall be payable by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem64b572ca-3e0c-48bf-9c51-f30482836137'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Disclaimer</p><div><p>This gives the Seller the ability to require the Guarantor to take a transfer of the Property in the event that the contract is disclaimed. See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM3_149095'>The process of disclaimer by a liquidator or trustee in bankruptcy under sections 178 or 315 of the Insolvency Act 1986</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1'><div><p>the liability of the Guarantor shall not be affected reduced or extinguished by:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb2b70c21-0e1a-4ca0-a124-6ad25dd6e5f4'><div><p>any time or indulgence granted by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> to the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemfb07de4a-86ee-446c-b76f-346d6ca05a86'><div><p>any neglect or forbearance of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in enforcing its rights under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemaa2a78f2-df61-4f7b-8af6-482506233419'><div><p>any variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> agreed between the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>; or</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89'><div><p>the fact that any other person or entity comprising the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> or intended to comprise the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> has not executed this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or is not bound by the guarantee in clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>;</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem94e8ddef-544f-4d85-bd54-629d58779cbf'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89' type='clause'/>&#8212;Signatories</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Harvey v Dunbar Assets plc [2013] All ER (D) 400 (Jul)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>In <em class='it'>Harvey</em> the court decided a bank guarantee was subject to a condition that it would be signed by all the other intended guarantors named in the deed, and, so, liability as a &#8216;Guarantor&#8217; was only imposed on an individual signatory to the document in circumstances where all the named individuals did indeed sign the guarantee. This meant the individual being sued was never on the hook as guarantor because one of the intended guarantors had not signed the document (his signature had been forged). The guarantee was a single composite document, which sought to impose joint and several liability on four individuals together defined as &#8216;the Guarantor&#8217; and envisaged it would be signed by all four individuals. There was nothing in the wording excluding the result that all intended guarantors had to sign for an individual guarantor to be liable. It is assumed that the contract into which this clause is inserted provides for joint and several liability where obligations are owed by more than one party. This sub-clause is an attempt to avoid the problem in <em class='it'>Harvey</em> as whilst the case relates to a bank guarantee it could, of course, be of wider application in the context of guarantees. It has not been tested in court.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf2e07994-da50-4aed-8b93-04436780dc3b'><div><p>anything else by which apart from clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1' type='clause'/> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> would be released other than a release under seal.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A6711E0-BD8A-4AD3-8E95-C97CC10C5975'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' opt-key='opt-N70726'><p class='main_heading'>Capital allowances</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d'><div><p>In clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/> the following definitions apply:</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema8c561ba-3721-4e44-b601-b05c3c8c5a73'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/>&#8212;Capital allowances</p><div><p>It is important on any sale of property to consider the position in relation to capital allowances. In order to qualify for plant and machinery allowances, expenditure must be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>capital</p></div></li><li><div><p>on plant and machinery, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>wholly or partly for the purposes of a qualifying activity</p></div></li></ul><div><p>In addition, the person incurring the expenditure must own the plant and machinery as a result of that expenditure. See: <a normcite='0OLU_123942'>Capital allowances&#8212;overview</a> for further information on the qualification criteria.</p></div><div><p>Properties often have substantial plant and machinery. This may be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>fixtures, and/or</p></div></li><li><div><p>integral features</p></div></li></ul><div><p>For information on the practicalities of capital allowance-related warranties and pre-contract enquiries on a property transfer, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185796'>Plant and machinery allowances on property acquisitions and disposals (including pre-contract enquiries)</a>.</p></div><div><p>The drafting in this clause is for use where the Seller has claimed allowances and the parties will enter into a s 198 election on Completion. For alternative drafting clauses where the Seller:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>has claimed allowances and the parties will apply to the First-tier Tax Tribunal for a just and reasonable allocation of allowances; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has claimed allowances but the information is not available on completion to enable a s198 election to be entered into at completion; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has not claimed capital allowances, and was not entitled to do so; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>was entitled to claim capital allowances but has not done so</p></div></li></ul><div><p>see the drafting alternatives and notes in Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>.</p></div><div><p>The purpose of a section 198 election is to determine, for capital allowances purposes, the amount of the price for the Property that should be attributed to fixtures on which the Seller has claimed allowances.</p></div><div><p>For more information see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a> and <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div><div><p>These clauses are about plant and machinery allowances for fixtures. In some circumstances, the seller of a property will have been claiming structures and buildings allowances (SBAs), which are another type of capital allowance available for (broadly) capital expenditure incurred since 29 October 2018 on the construction, conversion or renovation of a building or structure. If this applies, the buyer of the property would normally inherit the ability to claim SBAs. For drafting to address this situation, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a> and, for more information, see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0OLV_3243499'>Structures and buildings allowances</a> and <a citeref='CITEID_687537' normcite='0OLV_185796'>Capital allowances on property sales&#8212;pre-contract enquiries&#8212;Structures and buildings allowance</a>.</p></div></div></div><div><lnb-prec:definition><b>CAA&#160;2001</b><div><p>Capital Allowances Act 2001;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Election</b><div><p>an election in respect of the <b>Fixtures</b> under section 198 of <b>CAA 2001</b> in the form annexed in to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> in<a id-ref='ukContentItem1527671250-839993120' type='schedule'/>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem7ffa5e9f-e1cc-4d3e-a8e7-2a787fd78282'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Election</p><div><p>For details of elections in real estate transactions, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Fixtures</b><div><p>all plant and machinery which is installed or otherwise fixed in or to the <b>Property</b> so as to become (in law) part of the <b>Property</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem047859c8-e9af-4c86-a104-979d3ffe03cc'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Fixtures</p><div><p>Fixtures are plant or machinery that is installed or fixed so that they become, in law, part of a building or land. Examples include boilers, alarm systems and fitted kitchen units. There are special rules to determine whether a taxpayer is eligible to claim allowances for expenditure on a fixture. In order to claim allowances, the taxpayer must have an interest in the land or building of which the fixture is part. Further rules determine who may claim allowances where more than one person might have a claim, for instance where a person constructs a building, installs fixtures, then leases the building to another person for a capital sum that includes a payment for those fixtures. For new fixtures, the capital allowances claim is based on the actual expenditure. For more information see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Main Pool Plant</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> included by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in the main pool under section 54 of <b>CAA 2001</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1508418030-2811139'><p class='main_heading'>Main Pool Plant</p><div><p>This definition catches most fixtures that are not within the definition of Special Rate Pool Plant.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Prior Right</b><div><p>has the meaning of &#8216;prior right&#8217; for the purposes of section 181(2) of CAA 2001;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Special Rate Pool Plant</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> included by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in a special rate pool under section 104C of <b>CAA 2001</b>.</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1508418030-5461139'><p class='main_heading'>Special Rate Pool Plant</p><div><p>This definition catches <a normcite='0OLV_161955'>integral features</a>, thermal insulation, <a citeref='CITEID_127779' normcite='0OLV_162011'>long-life assets</a> and solar panels. These generally qualify for a lower rate of capital allowances than other fixtures.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition></div></div><div id='ukContentItem501d9779-1046-4b61-8f0d-f5f5c15d812a'><div><p>On <b>Completion</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall make the <b>Election</b> and shall each, within <em type='number'>insert number</em> working days of <b>Completion</b>, deliver the <b>Election</b> to their respective tax inspectors at <b>HMRC</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Special Rate Pool Plant</b> shall be &#163;<em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7d07a11-1d76-48f8-9e04-c9c4b70af874'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/>&#8212;Integral and Non-integral Features</p><div><p>Dividing the fixtures into those that attract allowances at a special rate (most commonly, integral features) and those that do not is the absolute minimum HMRC will accept. Depending on which fixtures exist in the Property, it may be necessary to subdivide them further and provide more details, such as 'electrical systems' or 'cold water systems'. In this case it may be better to delete clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650' type='clause'/> rely on a more detailed breakdown in the proforma election in <a id-ref='ukContentItem1527671250-839993120' type='schedule'/>. See Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_163854'>Election&#8212;capital allowances apportionment on sale of land&#8212;CAA 2001, s 198</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Main Pool Plant</b> shall be <em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem319cec81-cb14-4d36-926e-ce949f567f03'><div><p>Each of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemc5df0ee3-08eb-4925-a8e3-33f52238585a'><div><p>provide all necessary information to each other and take all reasonable steps required to validly make the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem144eeb00-b956-485c-a895-427af7748ae9'><div><p>submit a copy of the <b>Election</b> to <b>HMRC</b> with their tax return for the first period affected by the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItema8e4c85b-ffc7-4568-ace2-7967853612d1'><div><p>take all reasonable steps to ensure that the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> are accepted by <b>HMRC</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdce79faf-9fbc-4a52-afbb-21adf5a4abdf'><div><p>reflect the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> in their respective tax computations and returns.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemacc4de87-96b3-4966-a239-c45bb9bfa360'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that no person has a <b>Prior Right</b> in relation to any of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemabc048f4-b70e-400c-bccd-ec560520ed1a'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that the total and individual figures in the <b>Election</b> are no greater than the amounts incurred by it in accordance with <b>CAA 2001</b> for the provision of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1561132277-50196260", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A6711E0-BD8A-4AD3-8E95-C97CC10C5975'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' opt-key='opt-590EB33F'><p class='main_heading'>Undertaking</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-42027560'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall procure that, by the time of <b>Completion</b>, the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of an undertaking (&#8216;the Undertaking&#8217;) given by the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> (whether by the adoption of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion by Post (2019) (&#8216;the Code&#8217;) or otherwise) that the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on <b>Completion</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50459160'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall not be obliged to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> unless and until the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of the Undertaking. If the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> is ready, able and willing to complete but the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> do not have the benefit of the Undertaking, the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall be treated as in default and not being ready, able and willing to complete and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be entitled to give the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> a notice to complete.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-41490460'><div><p>In this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/>, the term &#8216;Seller&#8217; has the same meaning as in the Code and the phrase &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitors&#8217; has the same meaning as is given to the term &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitor&#8217; in the Code.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1561132277-41509560'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> &#8212; Undertaking</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Dreamvar (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin LLP and another; Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya (a firm) and another (Law Society intervening) [2018] EWCA Civ 1082</a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.propertyprotocols.co.uk/_uploads/downloads/LPSLG-protocol-on-client-identity---final-version-20-May-2019.pdf'>LPSLG protocol on client identity</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The London Property Support Lawyers Group (&#8216;LPSLG&#8217;) released a protocol (&#8216;the Protocol&#8217;) in May 2019 to address the risk of identity fraud, in the light of the Court of Appeal&#8217;s decision in <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> (see <a normcite='0S4D_2878129'>Court of Appeal gives judgment in property fraud cases&#8212;bad news for vendors&#8217; solicitors (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin, Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya)</a>). The provisions set out in this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are those suggested by the LPSLG in order to implement its Protocol. </p></div><div><p><em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> concerned the undertakings given by the seller&#8217;s solicitor as a result of using the 2011 version of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion (&#8216;the Code&#8217;). The 2011 version of the Code contains an undertaking by the seller&#8217;s solicitor that it has the seller&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on completion (and the same undertaking is re-stated in the 2019 version of the Code). The Court of Appeal interpreted &#8216;completion&#8217; to mean a real completion in which real money is exchanged for the title to the land and on that basis a completion with a fraudster is no completion at all. </p></div><div><p>Accordingly, by using the Code, the seller&#8217;s solicitor gives an undertaking that it has the authority of the real owner of the property to complete the transaction. The seller&#8217;s solicitor breaches that undertaking when they purport to complete on behalf of a fraudster impersonating the real owner. </p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.lawsociety.org.uk/support-services/documents/code-for-completion-by-post-2019/'>Law Society Code for Completion by Post 2019</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> case prompted the Law Society to release an updated version of the Code in May 2019. The obligations in the 2019 Code are unchanged from those in the 2011 version, although the numbering has changed. The majority of the changes are to reinforce that the effect of the use of the Code is that the seller&#8217;s solicitor undertakes that the seller is the person genuinely entitled to sell the land. (See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM9_45869'>How does completion happen?</a>.)</p></div><div><p>The Protocol states:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>&#8216;When acting for a buyer, we will not normally request confirmation of identity, or assurances as to the carrying out of AML checks or similar, from the seller&#8217;s solicitors. Our AML responsibilities are not there to create a cause of action between law firms.</p></div></li><li><div><p>Instead we will rely on the seller&#8217;s solicitors&#8217; undertaking that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf (as the Court of Appeal held in Dreamvar that this meant the true owner). Accordingly where the Code is not being adopted, the seller&#8217;s solicitors should be prepared to undertake that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf. No well advised real estate lawyer acting for a buyer would complete without such an undertaking anyway and if completion is to be dealt with via solicitors, no seller&#8217;s solicitor could avoid giving such an undertaking in order for the completion process to proceed with confidence.</p></div></li><li><div><p>We recognise that to be sure that such an undertaking will be given before completion it will be necessary to add a contractual obligation on the seller to procure that their solicitor will provide such an undertaking (whether as part of using the Code or as a stand-alone undertaking) as a pre-condition to completion.&#8217;</p></div></li></ul><div><p>Our view is that the Protocol and LPSLG&#8217;s suggested clauses set out here as clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are a sensible approach to address the risk of identity fraud following <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em>. If using these clauses, the Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should note that they will entitle the Buyer to serve a notice to complete if the Undertaking is not forthcoming. The Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should also be mindful that they will be committed to providing an undertaking on Completion and therefore the firm&#8217;s internal policy regarding giving undertakings will need to be complied with.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8A6711E0-BD8A-4AD3-8E95-C97CC10C5975'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' opt-key='opt-N73574'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p> No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party <em type='text'>such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any securities exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem52b8262f-83f4-481e-a3e0-95e8d8a98954'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This is a short form announcements provision. For a longer form clause see: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>This clause is drafted on the basis that:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>it binds all of the parties to the contract</p></div></li><li><div><p>the general prohibition on announcements and other public disclosures relates to the existence of the contract itself and any of the matters contained in it</p></div></li><li><div><p>the parties will remain binding for the duration of the contract (if the clause is intended to survive termination of the contract, this may be stated in the clause itself or elsewhere in the contract, eg in the termination or survival clause)</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made with the prior written consent of the other party, with no express process being set out to obtain such consent, although it must not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made as required by law, a court or any other authority, without any prior written consent from the other party or any consultation with them being required.</p></div><div><p>The announcements clause normally forms part of the main contract relating to a transaction or arrangement and, as such, will take effect on the signing of the contract. Prior to signing, any announcement relating to the proposed transaction or arrangement will normally be restricted by the terms of a confidentiality agreement entered into between the parties. The terms of such a confidentiality agreement should be considered in drafting an announcements clause; it would be usual for the announcements clause (along with any confidentiality clause) to replace this initial confidentiality agreement.</p></div><div><p>It is necessary to consider an announcements clause in the contract in conjunction with any confidentiality clause, to ensure that the two work effectively together.</p></div></li></ul></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:C5651668-F4DB-4D37-BA91-B9C936E855C8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' opt-key='opt-N69736'><p class='main_heading'><lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party></p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1494506087-33817162'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Guarantor</p><div><p>This guarantee clause is suitable for use where the Seller requires some security that the Buyer will observe its obligations in the Agreement. The guarantee clause provides that if the Buyer defaults the Guarantor will perform those obligations (and this will include the obligation to pay the purchase price to the Seller). The Guarantor also indemnifies the Seller against any losses or liability incurred because of the Buyer&#8217;s default. Delete if no guarantor is being provided.</p></div></div></lnb-prec:title><div><p>In consideration of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> entering into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> at the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s request the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> agrees with the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> as a primary obligation as follows:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem6ee7430d-2436-4cbd-a424-5998ea800fc6'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> must perform and observe all of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem10d54eae-693d-4a1f-b86a-88d839de7f41'><div><p>if the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> defaults in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will perform them;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItembb7685cb-daff-41b1-b57c-8b7c6326d0f8'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will indemnify the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> against all claims, demands, damages, losses, liability, costs, fees and expenses sustained by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> by reason of, or arising in any way directly or indirectly out of, the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s default in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e'><div><p>if this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> has been disclaimed following the insolvency of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may serve notice in writing on the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> (the &#8216;<b>Guarantor Notice</b>&#8217;) requiring the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> in accordance with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> with the following modifications:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemd421ca62-727b-49e6-9240-91993f13ced3'><div><p>all obligations of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be deemed to have been entered into by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> as though it were named as <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in place of the party defined as the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem816b7794-9d86-4cb3-84fa-81079304136a'><div><p>if a notice to complete served by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> on the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> has expired at the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b> the <b>Completion Date</b> shall be <em type='number'>5</em> working days after the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem545c300a-9165-4d26-9d02-5ef27f83db51'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> is to pay:</p></div><div number-type='loweralpha'><div id='ukContentItemaacf6481-adc4-4d44-9044-072c062496b1'><div><p><b>Interest</b> on the balance of the <b>Price</b> from the contractual <b>Completion Date</b> until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdbf94e06-289b-4a0a-bce1-84e84f47f6ec'><div><p>all money expended by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in consequence of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s default from the date of expenditure until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days;</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7203eb7e-1bf8-472d-bd14-67e4f0494902'><div><p>for the avoidance of doubt no further deposit shall be payable by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem64b572ca-3e0c-48bf-9c51-f30482836137'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Disclaimer</p><div><p>This gives the Seller the ability to require the Guarantor to take a transfer of the Property in the event that the Agreement is disclaimed. See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM3_149095'>The process of disclaimer by a liquidator or trustee in bankruptcy under sections 178 or 315 of the Insolvency Act 1986</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1'><div><p>the liability of the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> shall not be affected reduced or extinguished by:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb2b70c21-0e1a-4ca0-a124-6ad25dd6e5f4'><div><p>any time or indulgence granted by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> to the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemfb07de4a-86ee-446c-b76f-346d6ca05a86'><div><p>any neglect or forbearance of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in enforcing its rights under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemaa2a78f2-df61-4f7b-8af6-482506233419'><div><p>any variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> agreed between the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>; or</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89'><div><p>the fact that any other person or entity comprising the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> or intended to comprise the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> has not executed this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or is not bound by the guarantee in this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>;</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem94e8ddef-544f-4d85-bd54-629d58779cbf'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89' type='clause'/>&#8212;Signatories</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Harvey v Dunbar Assets [2013] All ER (D) 400 (Jul)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>In <em class='it'>Harvey</em> the court decided a bank guarantee was subject to a condition that it would be signed by all the other intended guarantors named in the deed, and so liability as a &#8216;Guarantor&#8217; was only imposed on an individual signatory to the document in circumstances where all the named individuals did indeed sign the guarantee. This meant the individual being sued was never on the hook as guarantor because one of the intended guarantors had not signed the document (his signature had been forged). The guarantee was a single composite document, which sought to impose joint and several liability on four individuals together defined as &#8216;the Guarantor&#8217; and envisaged it would be signed by all four individuals. There was nothing in the wording excluding the result that all intended guarantors had to sign for an individual guarantor to be liable. It is assumed that the contract into which this clause is inserted provides for joint and several liability where obligations are owed by more than one party. This sub-clause is an attempt to avoid the problem in <em class='it'>Harvey</em> as, whilst the case relates to a bank guarantee it could, of course, be of wider application in the context of guarantees. It has not been tested in court.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf2e07994-da50-4aed-8b93-04436780dc3b'><div><p>anything else by which apart from this clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1' type='clause'/> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> would be released other than a release under seal.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1561132277-50196260", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:C5651668-F4DB-4D37-BA91-B9C936E855C8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' opt-key='opt-590EB33F'><p class='main_heading'>Undertaking</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-42027560'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall procure that, by the time of <b>Completion</b>, the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of an undertaking (&#8216;the Undertaking&#8217;) given by the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> (whether by the adoption of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion by Post (2019) (&#8216;the Code&#8217;) or otherwise) that the <b>Seller&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on <b>Completion</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-50459160'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall not be obliged to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> unless and until the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> have the benefit of the Undertaking. If the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> is ready, able and willing to complete but the <b>Buyer&#8217;s Solicitors</b> do not have the benefit of the Undertaking, the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall be treated as in default and not being ready, able and willing to complete and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be entitled to give the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> a notice to complete.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1561132277-41490460'><div><p>In this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/>, the term &#8216;Seller&#8217; has the same meaning as in the Code and the phrase &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitors&#8217; has the same meaning as is given to the term &#8216;Seller&#8217;s Solicitor&#8217; in the Code.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1561132277-41509560'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> &#8212; Undertaking</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Dreamvar (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin LLP and another; Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya (a firm) and another (Law Society intervening) [2018] EWCA Civ 1082</a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.propertyprotocols.co.uk/_uploads/downloads/LPSLG-protocol-on-client-identity---final-version-20-May-2019.pdf'>LPSLG protocol on client identity</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The London Property Support Lawyers Group (&#8216;LPSLG&#8217;) released a protocol (&#8216;the Protocol&#8217;) in May 2019 to address the risk of identity fraud, in the light of the Court of Appeal&#8217;s decision in <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> (see <a normcite='0S4D_2878129'>Court of Appeal gives judgment in property fraud cases&#8212;bad news for vendors&#8217; solicitors (P&amp;P Property Ltd v Owen White &amp; Catlin, Dreamvar (UK) Ltd v Mishcon De Reya)</a>). The provisions set out in this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are those suggested by the LPSLG in order to implement its Protocol. </p></div><div><p><em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> concerned the undertakings given by the seller&#8217;s solicitor as a result of using the 2011 version of the Law Society&#8217;s Code for Completion (&#8216;the Code&#8217;). The 2011 version of the Code contains an undertaking by the seller&#8217;s solicitor that it has the seller&#8217;s authority to receive the purchase money on completion (and the same undertaking is re-stated in the 2019 version of the Code). The Court of Appeal interpreted &#8216;completion&#8217; to mean a real completion in which real money is exchanged for the title to the land and on that basis a completion with a fraudster is no completion at all. </p></div><div><p>Accordingly, by using the Code, the seller&#8217;s solicitor gives an undertaking that it has the authority of the real owner of the property to complete the transaction. The seller&#8217;s solicitor breaches that undertaking when they purport to complete on behalf of a fraudster impersonating the real owner. </p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a class='https' href='www.lawsociety.org.uk/support-services/documents/code-for-completion-by-post-2019/'>Law Society Code for Completion by Post 2019</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em> case prompted the Law Society to release an updated version of the Code in May 2019. The obligations in the 2019 Code are unchanged from those in the 2011 version, although the numbering has changed. The majority of the changes are to reinforce that the effect of the use of the Code is that the seller&#8217;s solicitor undertakes that the seller is the person genuinely entitled to sell the land. (See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM9_45869'>How does completion happen?</a>.)</p></div><div><p>The Protocol states:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>&#8216;When acting for a buyer, we will not normally request confirmation of identity, or assurances as to the carrying out of AML checks or similar, from the seller&#8217;s solicitors. Our AML responsibilities are not there to create a cause of action between law firms.</p></div></li><li><div><p>Instead we will rely on the seller&#8217;s solicitors&#8217; undertaking that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf (as the Court of Appeal held in Dreamvar that this meant the true owner). Accordingly where the Code is not being adopted, the seller&#8217;s solicitors should be prepared to undertake that they are authorised to receive the completion funds on the seller&#8217;s behalf. No well advised real estate lawyer acting for a buyer would complete without such an undertaking anyway and if completion is to be dealt with via solicitors, no seller&#8217;s solicitor could avoid giving such an undertaking in order for the completion process to proceed with confidence.</p></div></li><li><div><p>We recognise that to be sure that such an undertaking will be given before completion it will be necessary to add a contractual obligation on the seller to procure that their solicitor will provide such an undertaking (whether as part of using the Code or as a stand-alone undertaking) as a pre-condition to completion.&#8217;</p></div></li></ul><div><p>Our view is that the Protocol and LPSLG&#8217;s suggested clauses set out here as clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1561132277-50196260' type='clause'/> are a sensible approach to address the risk of identity fraud following <em class='it'>Dreamvar</em>. If using these clauses, the Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should note that they will entitle the Buyer to serve a notice to complete if the Undertaking is not forthcoming. The Seller&#8217;s Solicitor should also be mindful that they will be committed to providing an undertaking on Completion and therefore the firm&#8217;s internal policy regarding giving undertakings will need to be complied with.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:C5651668-F4DB-4D37-BA91-B9C936E855C8'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' opt-key='opt-N70787'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p> No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party <em type='text'>such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any securities exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem52b8262f-83f4-481e-a3e0-95e8d8a98954'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This is a short form announcements provision. For a longer form see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>This clause is drafted on the basis that:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>it binds all of the parties to the Agreement</p></div></li><li><div><p>the general prohibition on announcements and other public disclosures relates to the existence of the contract itself and any of the matters contained in it</p></div></li><li><div><p>the parties will remain bound for the duration of the Agreement (if the clause is intended to survive termination of the agreement, this may be stated in the clause itself or elsewhere in the Agreement, eg in the termination or survival clause)</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made with the prior written consent of the other party, with no express process being set out to obtain such consent, although it must not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made as required by law, a court or any other authority, without any prior written consent from the other party or any consultation with them being required.</p></div><div><p>The announcements clause normally forms part of the main agreement relating to a transaction or arrangement and, as such, will take effect on the signing of the agreement. Prior to signing, any announcement relating to the proposed transaction or arrangement will normally be restricted by the terms of a confidentiality agreement entered into between the parties. The terms of such a confidentiality agreement should be considered in drafting an announcements clause; it would be usual for the announcements clause (along with any confidentiality clause) to replace this initial confidentiality agreement.</p></div><div><p>It is necessary to consider an announcements clause in an agreement in conjunction with any confidentiality clause, to ensure that the two work effectively together</p></div></li></ul></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:BD21B7AA-7240-4D40-8FB0-73D4F29E4CE2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Transferor</lnb-prec:party> shall at the request <em opt-key='opt-E74FA4C4'>and cost</em> of the <lnb-prec:party>Transferee</lnb-prec:party>, do or procure to be done all acts and execute and deliver, or procure the execution and delivery of, all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and to transfer <b>Control</b> of the <b>Domain Name</b> to the <lnb-prec:party>Transferee</lnb-prec:party> <em opt-key='opt-E74FBF45'>and otherwise enable the <lnb-prec:party>Transferee</lnb-prec:party> to fully operate the <b>Domain Name</b></em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges the transferor at the request of the transferee to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:BD21B7AA-7240-4D40-8FB0-73D4F29E4CE2'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D8E22062345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D8E22062345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0C215E70-FAE0-4700-B25B-A9086AF4A428'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' opt-key='opt-N69736'><p class='main_heading'><lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party></p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1494506087-33817162'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Guarantor</p><div><p>This guarantee clause is suitable for use where the Seller requires some security that the Buyer will observe its obligations in the Agreement. The guarantee clause provides that if the Buyer defaults the guarantor will perform those obligations (and this will include the obligation to pay the purchase price to the Seller). The guarantor also indemnifies the Seller against any losses or liability incurred because of the Buyer&#8217;s default. Delete if no guarantor is being provided.</p></div></div></lnb-prec:title><div><p>In consideration of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> entering into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> at the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>'s request the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> agrees with the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> as a primary obligation as follows:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem6ee7430d-2436-4cbd-a424-5998ea800fc6'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> must perform and observe all of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem10d54eae-693d-4a1f-b86a-88d839de7f41'><div><p>if the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> defaults in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will perform them;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItembb7685cb-daff-41b1-b57c-8b7c6326d0f8'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will indemnify the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> against all claims, demands, damages, losses, liability, costs, fees and expenses sustained by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> by reason of, or arising in any way directly or indirectly out of, the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e'><div><p>if this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> has been disclaimed following the insolvency of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may serve notice in writing on the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> (the &#8216;<b>Guarantor Notice</b>&#8217;) requiring the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> to complete the purchase of the <b>Property</b> in accordance with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> with the following modifications:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemd421ca62-727b-49e6-9240-91993f13ced3'><div><p>all obligations of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be deemed to have been entered into by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> as though it were named as <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in place of the party defined as the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem816b7794-9d86-4cb3-84fa-81079304136a'><div><p>if a notice to complete served by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> on the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> has expired at the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b> the <b>Completion Date</b> shall be <em type='number'>5</em> working days after the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem545c300a-9165-4d26-9d02-5ef27f83db51'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> is to pay:</p></div><div number-type='loweralpha'><div id='ukContentItemaacf6481-adc4-4d44-9044-072c062496b1'><div><p><b>Interest</b> on the balance of the <b>Price</b> from the contractual <b>Completion Date</b> until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdbf94e06-289b-4a0a-bce1-84e84f47f6ec'><div><p>all money expended by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in consequence of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>'s default from the date of expenditure until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days;</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7203eb7e-1bf8-472d-bd14-67e4f0494902'><div><p>no further deposit shall be payable by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem64b572ca-3e0c-48bf-9c51-f30482836137'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Disclaimer</p><div><p>This gives the Seller the ability to require the Guarantor to take a transfer of the Property in the event that the Agreement is disclaimed. See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM3_149095'>The process of disclaimer by a liquidator or trustee in bankruptcy under sections 178 or 315 of the Insolvency Act 1986</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1'><div><p>the liability of the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> shall not be affected reduced or extinguished by:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb2b70c21-0e1a-4ca0-a124-6ad25dd6e5f4'><div><p>any time or indulgence granted by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> to the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemfb07de4a-86ee-446c-b76f-346d6ca05a86'><div><p>any neglect or forbearance of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in enforcing its rights under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemaa2a78f2-df61-4f7b-8af6-482506233419'><div><p>any variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> agreed between the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>; or</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89'><div><p>the fact that any other person or entity comprising the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> or intended to comprise the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> has not executed this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or is not bound by the guarantee in this clause;</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem94e8ddef-544f-4d85-bd54-629d58779cbf'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89' type='clause'/>&#8212;Signatories</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Harvey v Dunbar Assets [2013] All ER (D) 400 (Jul)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>In <em class='it'>Harvey</em> the court decided a bank guarantee was subject to a condition that it would be signed by all the other intended guarantors named in the deed, and so liability as a &#8216;Guarantor&#8217; was only imposed on an individual signatory to the document in circumstances where all the named individuals did indeed sign the guarantee. This meant the individual being sued was never on the hook as guarantor because one of the intended guarantors had not signed the document (his signature had been forged). The guarantee was a single composite document, which sought to impose joint and several liability on four individuals together defined as &#8216;the Guarantor&#8217; and envisaged it would be signed by all four individuals. There was nothing in the wording excluding the result that all intended guarantors had to sign for an individual guarantor to be liable. It is assumed that the contract into which this clause is inserted provides for joint and several liability where obligations are owed by more than one party. This sub-clause is an attempt to avoid the problem in <em class='it'>Harvey</em> as, while the case relates to a bank guarantee it could, of course, be of wider application in the context of guarantees. It has not been tested in court.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf2e07994-da50-4aed-8b93-04436780dc3b'><div><p>anything else by which apart from this clause the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> would be released other than a release under seal.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0C215E70-FAE0-4700-B25B-A9086AF4A428'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' opt-key='opt-N68621'><p class='main_heading'>Capital allowances</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d'><div><p>In this clause the following definitions apply:</p></div><div><lnb-prec:definition><b>CAA&#160;2001</b><div><p>Capital Allowances Act 2001;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Election</b><div><p>an election in respect of the <b>Fixtures</b> under section 198 of <b>CAA 2001</b> in the form annexed in to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> as <a id-ref='ukContentItem1528449960-532921241' type='schedule'/>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem7ffa5e9f-e1cc-4d3e-a8e7-2a787fd78282'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Election</p><div><p>For details of elections in real estate transactions, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Fixtures</b><div><p>means all plant and machinery which is installed or otherwise fixed in or to the <b>Property</b> so as to become (in law) part of the <b>Property</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem047859c8-e9af-4c86-a104-979d3ffe03cc'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemebd1b413-4c26-4c47-876d-9d7166eb7d8d' type='clause'/>&#8212;Fixtures</p><div><p>Fixtures are plant or machinery installed or fixed so that they become, in law, part of a building or land. Examples include boilers, alarm systems and fitted kitchen units. There are special rules to determine whether a taxpayer is eligible to claim allowances for expenditure on a fixture. In order to claim allowances, the taxpayer must have an interest in the land or building of which the fixture is part. Further rules determine who may claim allowances where more than one person might have a claim, for instance where a person constructs a building, installs fixtures, then leases the building to another person for a capital sum that includes a payment for those fixtures. For new fixtures, the capital allowances claim is based on the actual expenditure. For more information see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a>.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>HMRC</b><div><p>means HM Revenue &amp; Customs;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Main Pool Plant</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> included by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in the main pool under section 54 of <b>CAA 2001</b>;</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1508418030-2811139'><p class='main_heading'>Main Pool Plant</p><div><p>This definition catches most fixtures that are not within the definition of Special Rate Pool Plant.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Prior Right</b><div><p>has the meaning of prior right for the purposes of section 181(2) of <b>CAA 2001</b>;</p></div></lnb-prec:definition><lnb-prec:definition><b>Special Rate Pool Plant</b><div><p>those <b>Fixtures</b> included by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in a special rate pool under section 104C of <b>CAA 2001</b>.</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1508418030-5461139'><p class='main_heading'>Special Rate Pool Plant</p><div><p>This definition catches <a normcite='0OLV_161955'>integral features</a>, thermal insulation, <a citeref='CITEID_127779' normcite='0OLV_162011'>long-life assets</a> and solar panels. These generally qualify for a lower rate of capital allowances than other fixtures.</p></div></div></div></lnb-prec:definition></div></div><div id='ukContentItem501d9779-1046-4b61-8f0d-f5f5c15d812a'><div><p>On <b>Completion</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall make the <b>Election</b> and shall each, within <em type='number'>insert number</em> working days of <b>Completion</b>, deliver the <b>Election</b> to their respective tax inspectors at <b>HMRC</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Special Rate Pool Plant</b> shall be &#163;<em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7d07a11-1d76-48f8-9e04-c9c4b70af874'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/>&#8212;Integral and Non-integral Features</p><div><p>Dividing the fixtures into those that attract allowances at a special rate (most commonly, integral features) and those that do not is the absolute minimum HMRC will accept. Depending upon which fixtures exist in the property, it may be necessary to subdivide them further and provide more details, such as 'electrical systems' or 'cold water systems'. In this case it may be better to delete clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem734da9de-2044-442e-840c-1b26d3b5408a' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650' type='clause'/> and rely upon on a more detailed breakdown in the proforma election annexed as <a id-ref='ukContentItem1528449960-532921241' type='schedule'/>. See Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_163854'>Election&#8212;capital allowances apportionment on sale of land&#8212;CAA 2001, s 198</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc956be45-980b-4cf5-bbf3-000560762650'><div><p>The amount to be fixed in respect of the <b>Main Pool Plant</b> shall be &#163;<em type='number'>insert amount</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem319cec81-cb14-4d36-926e-ce949f567f03'><div><p>Each of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> shall:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemc5df0ee3-08eb-4925-a8e3-33f52238585a'><div><p>provide all necessary information to each other and take all reasonable steps required to validly make the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem144eeb00-b956-485c-a895-427af7748ae9'><div><p>submit a copy of the <b>Election</b> to <b>HMRC</b> with their tax return for the first period affected by the <b>Election</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItema8e4c85b-ffc7-4568-ace2-7967853612d1'><div><p>take all reasonable steps to ensure that the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> are accepted by <b>HMRC</b>; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdce79faf-9fbc-4a52-afbb-21adf5a4abdf'><div><p>reflect the amounts fixed by the <b>Election</b> in their respective tax computations and returns.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemacc4de87-96b3-4966-a239-c45bb9bfa360'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that no person has a <b>Prior Right</b> in relation to any of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemabc048f4-b70e-400c-bccd-ec560520ed1a'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> warrants that the total and individual figures in the <b>Election</b> are no greater than the amounts incurred by it in accordance with <b>CAA 2001</b> for the provision of the <b>Fixtures</b>.</p></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema8c561ba-3721-4e44-b601-b05c3c8c5a73'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem247936ef-500d-40a2-8f77-744bae30bded' type='clause'/>&#8212;Capital allowances</p><div><p>It is important on any sale of property to consider the position in relation to capital allowances. In order to qualify for plant and machinery allowances, expenditure must be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>capital</p></div></li><li><div><p>on plant and machinery, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>wholly or partly for the purposes of a qualifying activity</p></div></li></ul><div><p>In addition, the person incurring the expenditure must own the plant and machinery as a result of that expenditure. See <a normcite='0OLU_123942'>Captial allowances&#8212;overview Document</a> for further information on the qualification criteria.</p></div><div><p>Properties often have substantial plant and machinery. This may be:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>fixtures, and/or</p></div></li><li><div><p>integral features</p></div></li></ul><div><p>For information on the practicalities of capital allowance-related warranties and pre-contract enquiries on a property transfer, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLV_185796'>Plant and machinery allowances on property acquisitions and disposals (including pre-contract enquiries)</a>.</p></div><div><p>The drafting in this clause is for use where the Seller has claimed allowances and the parties will enter into a section 198 election on Completion. For alternative drafting clauses where the Seller:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>has claimed allowances and the parties will apply to the First-tier Tax Tribunal for a just and reasonable allocation of allowances; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has claimed allowances but the information is not available on completion to enable a section 198 election to be entered into at completion; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>has not claimed capital allowances, and was not entitled to do so; or</p></div></li><li><div><p>was entitled to claim capital allowances but has not done so</p></div></li></ul><div><p>see the drafting alternatives and notes in Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a>.</p></div><div><p>The purpose of a section 198 election is to determine, for capital allowances purposes, the amount of the price for the property that should be attributed to fixtures on which the Seller has claimed allowances.</p></div><div><p>For more information see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0OLV_185795'>Plant and machinery allowances&#8212;fixtures</a> and <a normcite='0OLV_185798'>Section 198 and 199 elections on transactions involving real estate property</a>.</p></div><div><p>These clauses are about plant and machinery allowances for fixtures. In some circumstances, the seller of a property will have been claiming structures and buildings allowances (SBAs), which are another type of capital allowance available for (broadly) capital expenditure incurred since 29 October 2018 on the construction, conversion or renovation of a building or structure. If this applies, the buyer of the property would normally inherit the ability to claim SBAs. For drafting to address this, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OL9_255172'>Capital allowances clauses&#8212;property sale contract</a> and, for more information, see Practice Notes: <a normcite='0OLV_3243499'>Structures and buildings allowances</a> and <a citeref='CITEID_687537' normcite='0OLV_185796'>Capital allowances on property sales&#8212;pre-contract enquiries&#8212;Structures and buildings allowance</a>.</p></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0C215E70-FAE0-4700-B25B-A9086AF4A428'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' opt-key='opt-N70787'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party<em opt-key='opt-D733AC17'>, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any securities exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem52b8262f-83f4-481e-a3e0-95e8d8a98954'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This is a short form announcements provision. For a longer form see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>This clause is drafted on the basis that:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>it binds all of the parties to the Agreement</p></div></li><li><div><p>the general prohibition on announcements and other public disclosures relates to the existence of the contract itself and any of the matters contained in it</p></div></li><li><div><p>the parties will remain bound for the duration of the Agreement (if the clause is intended to survive termination of the agreement, this may be stated in the clause itself or elsewhere in the Agreement, eg in the termination or survival clause)</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made with the prior written consent of the other party, with no express process being set out to obtain such consent, although it must not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made as required by law, a court or any other authority, without any prior written consent from the other party or any consultation with them being required.</p></div><div><p>The announcements clause normally forms part of the main agreement relating to a transaction or arrangement and, as such, will take effect on the signing of the agreement. Prior to signing, any announcement relating to the proposed transaction or arrangement will normally be restricted by the terms of a confidentiality agreement entered into between the parties. The terms of such a confidentiality agreement should be considered in drafting an announcements clause; it would be usual for the announcements clause (along with any confidentiality clause) to replace this initial confidentiality agreement.</p></div><div><p>It is necessary to consider an announcements clause in an agreement in conjunction with any confidentiality clause, to ensure that the two work effectively together</p></div></li></ul></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34828125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0C215E70-FAE0-4700-B25B-A9086AF4A428'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have exclusive jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem6a4733a3-5990-4eba-b100-19fe125ff259'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This clause provides that the courts of England and Wales shall have jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, the agreement. </p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217;.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Fiona Trust v Privalov and others [2007] All ER (D) 233 (Oct) </a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>UBS AG v HSH Nordbank AG [2009] EWCA Civ 585, para 82</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The inclusion of the wording 'arise out of, or in connection with' and similar terms in a jurisdiction clause used to cause difficulties as to exactly what type of disputes were brought within its scope. The House of Lords has, in an arbitration case, upheld a wide interpretation of these words. This was on the assumption that the parties, as rational businessmen, were likely to have intended <em class='it'>any</em> dispute arising out of their relationship to be decided by the tribunal referred to in the relevant clause. The wording was held to be so wide as to cover claims arising before inception of the relevant agreement, such as misrepresentation. This wide interpretation has subsequently been followed in a number of litigation cases.</p></div><div><p>The enforceability of a clause which confers jurisdiction on the courts of England and Wales may ultimately depend, post-Brexit, on the treaty arrangements which exist after the UK leaves the EU. It cannot be said with absolute certainty that the courts of an EU member state will respect such a clause, particularly if the clause confers non-exclusive jurisdiction on the courts of England and Wales. Consequently, if one of the parties to this agreement is domiciled in an EU member state and does not have sufficient assets within the jurisdiction to satisfy any potential judgment against it, practitioners may need to advise clients to seek a legal opinion from lawyers in the EU member state where enforcement is likely to be required confirming that the courts in that country will enforce an English judgment under their national rules. Alternatively, clients might consider making it a term of this agreement that sufficient assets are brought into the jurisdiction in order to satisfy any judgment obtained here.</p></div><div><p>See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLB_3122262'>Brexit&#8212;jurisdiction [Archived]</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34327125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0C215E70-FAE0-4700-B25B-A9086AF4A428'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1490085952-34560125'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause provides that the agreement and certain disputes and claims shall governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217;.</p></div><div><p>A choice of law clause which makes English law the law of this agreement should not be affected by Brexit, regardless of whether this agreement is entered into before or after the UK leaves the EU. This is because EU law (in the form of Regulation (EC) 593/2008 (&#8216;Rome I&#8217;) and Regulation (EC) 864/2007 (&#8216;Rome II&#8217;)) requires member states to uphold choice of law clauses regardless of whether the law chosen is the law of a member state. A party who is domiciled in an EU member state should not be in a position to argue that English law should not apply to any dispute arising out of this agreement even though the court of an EU member state has jurisdiction over it.</p></div><div><p>See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLB_3122566'>Brexit&#8212;applicable law [Archived]</a>.</p></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34097125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0C215E70-FAE0-4700-B25B-A9086AF4A428'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125'><p class='main_heading'>Joint and several liability</p><div><p>Where the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> is more than one person, the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may release or compromise the liability of any of those persons under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or grant time or other indulgence without affecting the liability of any other of them.</p></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:92CD348C-BEFB-47B1-BE40-B3FAFD285DDE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' opt-key='opt-N68721'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p> No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party <em opt-key='opt-N68735'>such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any securities exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem52b8262f-83f4-481e-a3e0-95e8d8a98954'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This is a short form announcements provision. For a longer form see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>This clause is drafted on the basis that:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>it binds all of the parties to the agreement</p></div></li><li><div><p>the general prohibition on announcements and other public disclosures relates to the existence of the agreement itself and any of the matters contained in it</p></div></li><li><div><p>the parties will remain bound for the duration of the agreement (if the clause is intended to survive termination of the agreement, this may be stated in the clause itself or elsewhere in the agreement, eg in the termination or survival clause)</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made with the prior written consent of the other party, with no express process being set out to obtain such consent, although it must not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made as required by law, a court or any other authority, without any prior written consent from the other party or any consultation with them being required.</p></div><div><p>The announcements clause normally forms part of the main agreement relating to a transaction or arrangement and, as such, will take effect on the signing of the agreement. Prior to signing, any announcement relating to the proposed transaction or arrangement will normally be restricted by the terms of a confidentiality agreement entered into between the parties. The terms of such a confidentiality agreement should be considered in drafting an announcements clause; it would be usual for the announcements clause (along with any confidentiality clause) to replace this initial confidentiality agreement.</p></div><div><p>It is necessary to consider an announcements clause in an agreement in conjunction with any confidentiality clause, to ensure that the two work effectively together.</p></div></li></ul></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:F3229CA6-6B43-4C70-8FDE-FD8C46EBDF9F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each party shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this Agreement, its employees, agents and representatives will comply with all applicable laws and regulations, provided that neither party shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this Agreement by the other party (or its employees, agents and representatives).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws. It is a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:BECB573B-4357-4A79-BBD0-F55F6A12DCD0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each party shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this Agreement, its employees, agents and representatives will comply with all applicable laws and regulations, provided that neither party shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this Agreement by the other party (or its employees, agents and representatives).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. It is a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:D0D3C1AB-DC00-4DD8-B982-068F2E9ED407'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its employees, agents and representatives will comply with all applicable laws and regulations, provided that neither <b>party</b> shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by the other <b>party</b> (or its employees, agents and representatives).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "INFORMATIONLAW", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:ABC82775-CDFB-4D24-BA50-D36C4A3657CE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply with all laws, enactments, regulations, regulatory policies, guidelines and industry codes applicable to them and shall maintain such authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform their obligations under or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PLANNING::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34097125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:614AC72C-58AA-4FB8-BDAE-FE78031592CF'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34097125'><p class='main_heading'>Joint and several liability</p><div><p>Where the <lnb-prec:party>Tenant</lnb-prec:party> is more than one person, the <lnb-prec:party>Landlord</lnb-prec:party> may release or compromise the liability of any of those persons under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or grant time or other indulgence without affecting the liability of any other of them.</p></div></div>"}, {PA: "PLANNING::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34327125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:614AC72C-58AA-4FB8-BDAE-FE78031592CF'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1490085952-34560125'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34327125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause provides that the agreement and certain disputes and claims shall governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217;.</p></div><div><p>A choice of law clause which makes English law the law of this agreement should not be affected by Brexit, regardless of whether this agreement is entered into before or after the UK leaves the EU. This is because EU law (in the form of Regulation (EC) 593/2008 (&#8216;Rome I&#8217;) and Regulation (EC) 864/2007 (&#8216;Rome II&#8217;)) requires member states to uphold choice of law clauses regardless of whether the law chosen is the law of a member state. A party who is domiciled in an EU member state should not be in a position to argue that English law should not apply to any dispute arising out of this agreement even though the court of an EU member state has jurisdiction over it.</p></div><div><p>See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLB_3122566'>Brexit&#8212;applicable law [Archived]</a>.</p></div></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PLANNING::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem1490085952-34828125", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:614AC72C-58AA-4FB8-BDAE-FE78031592CF'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have exclusive jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem6a4733a3-5990-4eba-b100-19fe125ff259'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem1490085952-34828125' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This clause provides that the courts of England and Wales shall have jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, the agreement. </p></div><div><p>The wording as to the types of dispute and claim to be covered is deliberately wide in its reference to any &#8216;dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation&#8217;.</p></div><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Fiona Trust v Privalov and others [2007] All ER (D) 233 (Oct) </a></lnb-prec:margin-note><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>UBS AG v HSH Nordbank AG [2009] EWCA Civ 585, para 82</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>The inclusion of the wording 'arise out of, or in connection with' and similar terms in a jurisdiction clause used to cause difficulties as to exactly what type of disputes were brought within its scope. The House of Lords has, in an arbitration case, upheld a wide interpretation of these words. This was on the assumption that the parties, as rational businessmen, were likely to have intended <em class='it'>any</em> dispute arising out of their relationship to be decided by the tribunal referred to in the relevant clause. The wording was held to be so wide as to cover claims arising before inception of the relevant agreement, such as misrepresentation. This wide interpretation has subsequently been followed in a number of litigation cases.</p></div><div><p>The enforceability of a clause which confers jurisdiction on the courts of England and Wales may ultimately depend, post-Brexit, on the treaty arrangements which exist after the UK leaves the EU. It cannot be said with absolute certainty that the courts of an EU member state will respect such a clause, particularly if the clause confers non-exclusive jurisdiction on the courts of England and Wales. Consequently, if one of the parties to this agreement is domiciled in an EU member state and does not have sufficient assets within the jurisdiction to satisfy any potential judgment against it, practitioners may need to advise clients to seek a legal opinion from lawyers in the EU member state where enforcement is likely to be required confirming that the courts in that country will enforce an English judgment under their national rules. Alternatively, clients might consider making it a term of this agreement that sufficient assets are brought into the jurisdiction in order to satisfy any judgment obtained here.</p></div><div><p>See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OLB_3122262'>Brexit&#8212;jurisdiction [Archived]</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:C8B27994-C96D-407D-8F6C-4385B9138002'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a <b>party</b>&#8217;s address as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-E4B4FC0C'>(or to the email address set out below)</em>. <b>Notice</b>s may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'><b>party</b></em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='0021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='0021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:C8B27994-C96D-407D-8F6C-4385B9138002'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> may set off any amount the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> owes it under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or otherwise against any amount that it owes to the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or otherwise, whether such debt is owed now or at any time in the future, whether it is liquidated or not and whether it is actual or contingent. Any exercise by the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> of its rights under this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/> will not prejudice any other right or remedy available to it, whether under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or otherwise.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>As this is a pro-customer precedent the set-off provisions have been drafted to permit set-off by the customer. A supplier is likely to prefer a clause which prohibits set-off. This will be a point for negotiation as set-off can offer a useful remedy for a customer. For alternative wording and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:C8B27994-C96D-407D-8F6C-4385B9138002'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> shall not a assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s prior written consent.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This assignment clause prohibits the assignment by the supplier of its rights and obligations under the agreement to a third party without the prior consent of the customer. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:C8B27994-C96D-407D-8F6C-4385B9138002'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force Majeure</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1543334969-83488625'><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b> the effects of which could not have been avoided by a <b>party</b> by compliance with its obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and which could not otherwise reasonably have been anticipated and avoided.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1543334969-82455325'><div><p> For the purposes of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>, an &#8216;event beyond the reasonable control&#8217; of a <b>party</b> shall not include <em>insert eg any industrial dispute or any duty to comply with <b>Applicable Law</b></em>. </p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem1543335423-84003325'><div><p>The <b>party</b> affected by a <b>Force Majeure Event</b> shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when the <b>Force Majeure Event</b> causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If the <b>Force Majeure Event</b> continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. As this is a pro-customer precedent the clause has been drafted narrowly. Force majeure is most likely to be relied on by the supplier. In the cloud environment it is not unreasonable to expect that the supplier should have built enough resilience into its system to provide for most potential force majeure events. It is in the customer&#8217;s interests that the supplier should take as much responsibility as possible for ensuring that its operations can continue without interruption (eg having suitable backup facilities and ensuring it does not use data centres in floodplains etc). The supplier is likely to seek to expand the scope of this provision during negotiation. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a> and for guidance in relation to force majeure provisions generally, see Checklist: <a normcite='0OJE_1344687'>Drafting and negotiating a force majeure clause&#8212;checklist</a>.</p></div><div><p>Care should be taken to ensure that any provisions which relieve the supplier of its responsibilities in the event of force majeure do not inadvertently have the effect of also relieving the supplier of its disaster recovery obligations. As far as possible, the customer should seek to retain a link to the supplier obligation to comply with obligations under the agreement, particularly obligations around disaster recovery planning.</p></div><div><p>Note also that certain events which commonly feature in long form definitions of force majeure may not be appropriate in relation to cloud contracts depending on how the definition is applied. For example:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>interruption or failure of power supply</p></div></li><li><div><p>industrial action by workers</p></div></li><li><div><p>equipment failure</p></div></li></ul><div><p>If specific example events are included within the concept of agreed force majeure events the customer should consider the appropriateness of each in the context of the cloud.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:C8B27994-C96D-407D-8F6C-4385B9138002'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either <b>party</b> in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT::Essentials", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:C8B27994-C96D-407D-8F6C-4385B9138002'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The <b>parties</b> agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='022'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each <b>party</b> acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='023'><em type='text'>insert names of specific documents</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='024'><em type='text'>insert names of specified documents</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No <b>party</b> shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:FC0B93DC-C846-4BF9-A4AA-B8B3F4E697B0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentIteme3044c46-4f9a-44bf-a317-60755984b8c8'><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem971c5fe9-334f-471b-8bc8-964d71658ddf' type='clause'/>, each party shall comply with all laws, enactments, regulations, regulatory policies, guidelines and industry codes applicable to them and shall maintain such authorisations and all other approvals, permits and authorities as are required from time to time to perform their obligations under or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem971c5fe9-334f-471b-8bc8-964d71658ddf'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> warrants and represents that the access, use, import or download of the <b>Software</b> into the <b>Territory</b> by any <b>Customer Entity</b> in accordance with this <b>Agreement</b> shall not breach any applicable laws, rules and regulations including any applicable export or import restrictions.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws and contains a warranty and representation by the supplier that the customer&#8217;s use of the software will not breach any such laws including, in particular, any export control regulations.</p></div><div><p>Export control regulations restrict the export of so-called &#8216;dual use&#8217; goods (which include software) that could have both a civilian and military use to certain blacklisted countries. One possible example involves the international licensing of any software containing encryption functionality. While export control regulations are unlikely to be triggered by the majority of commercial software licences, suppliers and customers should be aware of these provisions and cater for them particularly when licensing software internationally. It should be noted that &#8216;export&#8217; includes both physical and electronic delivery of the software.</p></div><div><p>For more on export restrictions generally see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OK7_197822'>Export controls&#8212;requirement for an export licence</a>.</p></div><div><p>For alternative forms of general compliance with law wording and drafting notes see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:387C9B1E-93CB-4DF2-8416-84A43B4AF9D7'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each party shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its employees, agents and representatives will comply with all applicable laws and regulations, provided that neither party shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by the other party (or its employees, agents and representatives).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. It is a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "INFORMATIONLAW", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:0AD631A1-3DAC-4F6C-B0D8-979652F2184F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the <b>parties</b> nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D11E46262345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E46262345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> without the prior written consent of the <lnb-prec:party>Hirer</lnb-prec:party> <em opt-key='opt-F31C87E8'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure by the supplier of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>The <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> may not assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the <lnb-prec:party>Hirer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-F31CC27F'>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the <lnb-prec:party>Hirer</lnb-prec:party>&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. The <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b>Affiliate</b> in relation to its rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of the <lnb-prec:party>Supplier</lnb-prec:party> itself.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This assignment clause governs the extent to which the supplier&#8217;s rights and obligations may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the parties, nor make any party the agent of another party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' opt-key='opt-F31CD58D'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D11E44640001'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, each</em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D11E44640001'>Each</em> party must pay all sums that it owes to the other party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's <em alt-key='alt-D11E41900020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E41900020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850ccc'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D11E42500021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E42500021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each party shall, at the request of the other and at the cost of the requesting party, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D11E4131022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E4131022'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral, in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D11E4146023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E4146023'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D11E4157024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D11E4157024'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specified document[s]</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb0431571-62fe-48ab-a86f-c3db99f9056d'><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem6f56f675-e0c8-4b54-a48a-3f81d5f80a31' type='clause'/>, no one other than a party to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>,<em opt-key='opt-N65821'> their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6f56f675-e0c8-4b54-a48a-3f81d5f80a31'><div><p>The Affiliates of the <lnb-prec:party>Hirer</lnb-prec:party> shall have the right to enforce the provisions of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:465EF26D-CA60-4BDA-B66A-F9B48484396B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:9885D3E1-8BAC-48D3-9B69-B274FC42DE2E'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its <b>Representatives</b> will comply with all applicable <b>Law</b>, provided that neither <b>party</b> shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by the other <b>party</b> (or its <b>Representatives</b>).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. It is a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:013D58F2-7A04-4FFD-9C3E-CAFA74692F51'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' opt-key='opt-N72516'><p class='main_heading'>Guarantor</p><div><p>In consideration of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> entering into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> at the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor&#8217;s</lnb-prec:party> request the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> agrees with the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> as a primary obligation as follows:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem6ee7430d-2436-4cbd-a424-5998ea800fc6'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> must perform and observe all of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem10d54eae-693d-4a1f-b86a-88d839de7f41'><div><p>if the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> defaults in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will perform them;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItembb7685cb-daff-41b1-b57c-8b7c6326d0f8'><div><p>the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> will indemnify the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> against all claims, demands, damages, losses, liability, costs, fees and expenses sustained by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> by reason of, or arising in any way directly or indirectly out of, the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s default in performing its obligations in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e'><div><p>if this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> has been disclaimed following the insolvency of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> may serve notice (or a series of notices) in writing on the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> (each &#8216;<b>Guarantor Notice</b>&#8217;) requiring the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> to complete the purchase of some or all of the <b>Properties</b> (at the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s discretion) in accordance with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> with the following modifications:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemd421ca62-727b-49e6-9240-91993f13ced3'><div><p>all obligations of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> shall be deemed to have been entered into by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> as though it were named as <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> of the <b>Property</b> or Properties the subject of the relevant <b>Guarantor Notice</b> in place of the party defined as the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem816b7794-9d86-4cb3-84fa-81079304136a'><div><p>if a notice to complete served by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> on the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party> has expired at the date of service of a <b>Guarantor Notice</b> the <b>Completion Date</b> for the relevant <b>Property</b> or <b>Properties</b> shall be <em type='number'>5</em> working days after the date of service of the <b>Guarantor Notice</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem545c300a-9165-4d26-9d02-5ef27f83db51'><div><p>the <b>Guarantor</b> is to pay:</p></div><div number-type='loweralpha'><div id='ukContentItemaacf6481-adc4-4d44-9044-072c062496b1'><div><p><b>Interest</b> on the balance of the <b>Price</b> from the contractual <b>Completion Date</b> until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemdbf94e06-289b-4a0a-bce1-84e84f47f6ec'><div><p>all money expended by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in consequence of the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>&#8217;s default from the date of expenditure until <b>Completion</b> inclusive of both days;</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7203eb7e-1bf8-472d-bd14-67e4f0494902'><div><p>for the avoidance of doubt no further deposit shall be payable by the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem64b572ca-3e0c-48bf-9c51-f30482836137'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem228e2ec8-9b74-44c3-884c-4dd4ff16972e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Disclaimer</p><div><p>This gives the Seller the ability to require the Guarantor to take a transfer of some or all of the Properties in the event that the contract is disclaimed. See Practice Note: <a normcite='0OM3_149095'>The process of disclaimer by a liquidator or trustee in bankruptcy under sections 178 or 315 of the Insolvency Act 1986</a>.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1'><div><p>the liability of the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> shall not be affected reduced or extinguished by:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb2b70c21-0e1a-4ca0-a124-6ad25dd6e5f4'><div><p>any time or indulgence granted by the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> to the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemfb07de4a-86ee-446c-b76f-346d6ca05a86'><div><p>any neglect or forbearance of the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> in enforcing its rights under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemaa2a78f2-df61-4f7b-8af6-482506233419'><div><p>any variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> agreed between the <lnb-prec:party>Seller</lnb-prec:party> and the <lnb-prec:party>Buyer</lnb-prec:party>; or</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89'><div><p>the fact that any other person or entity comprising the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> or intended to comprise the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> has not executed this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or is not bound by the guarantee in clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>;</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem94e8ddef-544f-4d85-bd54-629d58779cbf'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem46cb3e01-9e25-4553-86e8-d0f8cbd27c89' type='clause'/>&#8212;Signatories</p><div><p><lnb-prec:margin-note><a>Harvey v Dunbar Assets plc [2013] All ER (D) 400 (Jul)</a></lnb-prec:margin-note>In <em class='it'>Harvey</em> the court decided a bank guarantee was subject to a condition that it would be signed by all the other intended guarantors named in the deed, and, so, liability as a &#8216;Guarantor&#8217; was only imposed on an individual signatory to the document in circumstances where all the named individuals did indeed sign the guarantee. This meant the individual being sued was never on the hook as guarantor because one of the intended guarantors had not signed the document (his signature had been forged). The guarantee was a single composite document, which sought to impose joint and several liability on four individuals together defined as &#8216;the Guarantor&#8217; and envisaged it would be signed by all four individuals. There was nothing in the wording excluding the result that all intended guarantors had to sign for an individual guarantor to be liable. It is assumed that the contract into which this clause is inserted provides for joint and several liability where obligations are owed by more than one party. This sub-clause is an attempt to avoid the problem in <em class='it'>Harvey</em> as whilst the case relates to a bank guarantee it could, of course, be of wider application in the context of guarantees. It has not been tested in court.</p></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf2e07994-da50-4aed-8b93-04436780dc3b'><div><p>anything else by which apart from clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme591eb93-580d-4af0-9e3e-80124c61d0d1' type='clause'/> the <lnb-prec:party>Guarantor</lnb-prec:party> would be released other than a release under seal.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1494500282-101398358'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem66331d38-037d-4dde-b923-d862eec970bb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Guarantor</p><div><p>This guarantee clause is suitable for use where the Seller requires some security that the Buyer will observe its obligations in the contract. The guarantee clause provides that if the Buyer defaults the guarantor will perform those obligations (and this will include the obligation to pay the purchase price to the Seller). The guarantor also indemnifies the Seller against any losses or liability incurred because of the Buyer&#8217;s default. Delete if no guarantor is being provided.</p></div><div><p>Where the agreed heads of terms incorporate a rental guarantee by the Seller for void occupational rents post-Completion, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OL6_245546'>Rental guarantee schedule</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "PROPERTY", id: "ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:013D58F2-7A04-4FFD-9C3E-CAFA74692F51'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' opt-key='opt-N73574'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party <em type='text'>such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed</em>, except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including, without limitation, any securities exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem52b8262f-83f4-481e-a3e0-95e8d8a98954'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem271cc1a3-b050-4fd4-9ed3-9a89ef678695' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This is a short form announcements provision. For a longer form clause, see: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div><div><p>This clause is drafted on the basis that:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>it binds all of the parties to the contract</p></div></li><li><div><p>the general prohibition on announcements and other public disclosures relates to the existence of the contract itself and any of the matters contained in it</p></div></li><li><div><p>the parties will remain binding for the duration of the contract (if the clause is intended to survive termination of the contract, this may be stated in the clause itself or elsewhere in the contract, eg in the termination or survival clause)</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made with the prior written consent of the other party, with no express process being set out to obtain such consent, although it must not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>an announcement or other public disclosure may be made as required by law, a court or any other authority, without any prior written consent from the other party or any consultation with them being required.</p></div><div><p>The announcements clause normally forms part of the main contract relating to a transaction or arrangement and, as such, will take effect on the signing of the contract. Prior to signing, any announcement relating to the proposed transaction or arrangement will normally be restricted by the terms of a confidentiality agreement entered into between the parties. The terms of such a confidentiality agreement should be considered in drafting an announcements clause; it would be usual for the announcements clause (along with any confidentiality clause) to replace this initial confidentiality agreement.</p></div><div><p>It is necessary to consider an announcements clause in the contract in conjunction with any confidentiality clause, to ensure that the two work effectively together.</p></div></li></ul></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:34B1395F-9EFA-4595-8B0E-D1E6DFDA0CDF'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its employees, agents and representatives will comply with all applicable laws and regulations, provided that neither <b>party</b> shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by the other <b>party</b> (or its employees, agents and representatives).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws. It is a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:8816313F-7464-4854-B7C6-C98427B9C326'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its <b>Representatives</b> will comply with all applicable <b>Law</b>, provided that neither <b>party</b> shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by the other <b>party</b> (or its <b>Representatives</b>).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, regulations and guidelines. It is a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:494C3D43-7126-402A-A1C6-8AF519F1B4F0'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply and shall (at its own expense unless expressly agreed otherwise) ensure that in the performance of its duties under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its employees, agents and representatives will comply with all applicable laws and regulations, provided that neither <b>party</b> shall be liable for any breach of this clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/> to the extent that such breach is directly caused or contributed to by any breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by the other <b>party</b> (or its employees, agents and representatives).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws. It is a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. For alternative forms of wording and drafting note, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E709A261-5E6E-4D3B-A4D1-1F9DCD644D89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D3E8042345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D3E8042345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the novation agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:E709A261-5E6E-4D3B-A4D1-1F9DCD644D89'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the novation agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:72BC93E9-3F5C-49AD-82C1-B229691DBA3B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>The <b>parties</b> irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D3E8042345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D3E8042345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the deed of novation. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "COMMERCIAL", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:72BC93E9-3F5C-49AD-82C1-B229691DBA3B'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the deed of novation and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc'><p class='main_heading'>Force majeure</p><div><p>Neither <b>party</b> shall have any liability under or be deemed to be in breach of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> for any delays or failures in performance of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> which result from any event beyond the reasonable control of that <b>party</b>. The <b>party</b> affected by such an event shall promptly notify the other <b>party</b> in writing when such an event causes a delay or failure in performance and when it ceases to do so. If such an event continues for a continuous period of more than <em type='number'>three</em> months, <em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>the party not affected</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E3620001'>either party</em> may terminate this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> by written notice to the other <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem29ab3120-63f4-4090-9fca-c2caff8d49f5'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem64508a02-66e8-4fe4-aaa7-732c516bd2bc' type='clause'/>&#8212;Force majeure</p><div><p>This force majeure clause exempts the parties from liability, and gives them the right to terminate the agreement, if events occur that are beyond their reasonable control. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of force majeure provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_122582'>Force majeure clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No <b>party</b> may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a <b>party</b> may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other <b>party</b>&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. Each <b>party</b> acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b>Affiliate</b> in relation to that <b>party</b>&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that <b>party</b> itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This assignment clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>. A definition of Affiliate should be added to the definitions section of the agreement. See Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_188755'>Affiliate definition</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the parties out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each party who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the parties <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'> may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either party may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed.</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'> Until the parties have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither party shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either party may at any time seek urgent interim relief.</em></p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause requires the parties to use reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E5020001'>Except as expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, each</em><em alt-connector='or' alt-key='alt-D15E5020001'>Each</em> <b>party</b> shall pay all sums that it owes to the other <b>party</b> under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the parties nor make any <b>party</b> the agent of another <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's <em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>two</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>seven</em> <b>Business Day</b>s after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report; and</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961' opt-key='opt-5B975C38'><div><p>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>read</em> return email.</p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or <b>Work Order</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each <b>party</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting <b>party</b>, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specific document[s]</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'><em type='text'>insert name[s] of specified document[s]</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div><p>No one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b><em opt-key='opt-N65821'>, their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>, the parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. The optional wording should be included where the agreement contains a dispute resolution clause preventing the parties from issuing court proceedings until the chosen form of dispute resolution procedure has been concluded without success. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "LIFESCIENCES", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:5D89943E-9675-480A-9DE9-48D2973CE39F'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "BANKINGANDFINANCE", id: "ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:054810E4-2CBB-4B14-8D96-5F1289A0FEFE'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6'><p class='main_heading'>Counterparts</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemcace7bfe-e8c6-4fb8-aa54-a0afc1f84b7a'><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> may be executed in any number of separate counterparts and this has the same effect as if the signatures on those counterparts were on a single copy of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemf7d32354-9a69-4d8c-8ea1-8c8f8589cc98' opt-key='opt-N81044'><div><p>Each Party may evidence their execution of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> <em opt-key='opt-N81055'>by faxing or</em> by emailing an executed signature page of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> in PDF format together with the final version of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b> in PDF or Word format, which shall constitute an original executed counterpart of this <b class='document-class'>Deed</b>. Each Party adopting this method of execution will, following circulation <em opt-key='opt-N81071'>by fax or</em> by email, provide the original, hard copy executed signature page to the other Party as soon as reasonably practicable.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem20a31ffd-8952-4d76-a285-b6bbd82da4c2'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem5f569e16-4888-4fb7-a6d2-909b1f8635e6' type='clause'/>&#8212;Counterparts</p><div><p>A counterparts clause is a common boilerplate clause which provides that the parties to an agreement may execute separate copies of it, rather than all parties having to sign the same copy of the agreement. It is common practice to sign an agreement in counterparts, and this mechanism can be particularly useful where there are a large number of parties, or where the parties are located in different regions or countries and will be unable to hold a physical completion meeting.</p></div><div><p>If an agreement does not contain a counterparts clause, the parties will not be prevented from executing a document in counterpart. However, using a counterparts clause is advisable for certainty, and to prevent any argument that the agreement is not binding because it has not been properly executed.</p></div><div><p>The counterparts clause commonly consists of:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>a statement that the document may be executed in counterparts, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>a sub-clause dealing with virtual signing (ie circulating the signature pages by email)</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The difference between original counterparts and original duplicates should be noted here. If all the parties sign a number of copies of the agreement, each copy is an original duplicate rather than a counterpart, and the counterparts clause will not be applicable.</p></div><div><p>The <em class='it'>Mercury Tax</em> case considered the effectiveness of pre-signed signature pages and virtual signings and closings where signature pages are exchanged by email (<em class='it'>Re Mercury Tax</em> [2008] All ER (D) 129 (Nov)). Following this case, the Law Society issued guidance on good practice for virtual signings (<a class='http' href='www.lawsociety.org.uk/support-services/advice/practice-notes/execution-of-documents-by-virtual-means/'>Law Society Guidance: Execution of documents by virtual means</a>).</p></div><div><p>The Law Society guidance sets out three options for the virtual signing of an agreement or deed. Agreements that are to be executed as a deed should follow option 1 of the guidance.</p></div><div><p>The Law Society recommends that all parties&#8217; lawyers agree to the proposed arrangements for the virtual signing/closing well in advance of execution. For this reason, it has become common practice to include specific drafting on virtual signings in the counterparts clause (see Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf7d32354-9a69-4d8c-8ea1-8c8f8589cc98' type='clause'/>).</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 1</em> gives guidance on circulating the entire document and the signed signature page by email. This method is suitable for both deeds and simple contracts. The detailed requirements for option 1 are as follows:</p></div><ul number-type='disc'><li><div><p>execution copies of the documents are emailed as PDF or Word attachments to all parties that will be absent and/or their lawyers (as agreed); the signature page may be emailed as a separate PDF or Word document, for convenience</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent signatory then prints and signs the signature page only (there is no need to print off the full document)</p></div></li><li><div><p>each absent party then returns a single email to their lawyer or to the lawyers coordinating signing/closing as agreed and attaches <em class='it'>both</em> the final version of the PDF or Word agreement and a PDF copy of the signed signature page, and</p></div></li><li><div><p>at or shortly after signing/closing, the parties may wish to evidence the execution by one of the law firms circulating a final version of the document together with copies of executed signature pages</p></div></li></ul><div><p>The Law Society guidance confirms that, for option 1, the PDF or Word final version of the document and the PDF of the signed signature page will constitute an original signed document and each counterpart taken together will equate to the same physical document.</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 2</em> allows the parties to circulate the signature page by email, without a copy of the final agreement (so is slightly less burdensome than option 1). This method is only suitable for simple contracts (not deeds).</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Option 3</em> allows the parties to sign and circulate the signature pages in advance of finalising a document. This method is only suitable for simple contracts (not deeds).</p></div><div><p>For further information on signing see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OJE_145100'>Virtual execution of documents</a>.</p></div><div><p><em class='bf'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf7d32354-9a69-4d8c-8ea1-8c8f8589cc98' type='clause'/></em></p></div><div><p>It has become common practice to have a sub-clause within the counterparts clause which deals with virtual signing (ie the circulation of signature pages by email or fax) following the Mercury Tax case and subsequent Law Society guidance. The entire sub-clause can be deleted if the parties are not intending to circulate signature pages electronically.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:7797644F-6DCB-457E-839C-4954D5E85B34'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e'><p class='main_heading'>Compliance with law</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem75435fe9-ac96-4bfc-bfc9-59395ec334e6'><div><p><em>Insert details of any specific export restrictions which apply to the <b>Software</b></em>.</p></div><div><p>Each <b>party</b> shall comply with all applicable laws and shall maintain such authorisations and approvals as required from time to time to perform their obligations under or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemc7f471e2-6c8b-4f45-9013-c297d47f4525'><div><p>Without prejudice to the generality of clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem75435fe9-ac96-4bfc-bfc9-59395ec334e6' type='clause'/>, the <b>parties</b> shall comply with all applicable laws, rules, and regulations governing export of goods and information that apply to the <b>Software</b> and the <b>User Manual</b>, and shall not export or re-export, directly or indirectly, separately or as a part of a system, the <b>Software</b> or the <b>User Manual</b> to any country for which an export licence or other approval is required, without first obtaining such licence or other approval. The <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> shall be solely responsible for ensuring its access, importation or use of the <b>Software</b> or the <b>User Manual</b> in or into any part of the <b>Territory</b> complies with all export laws.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem3dba997b-120c-4340-bf2d-70bc8bebe557'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem53660225-a9fd-45f8-a7e6-0c6b2158df4e' type='clause'/>&#8212;Compliance with law</p><div><p>This clause places a contractual obligation on both parties to comply with applicable laws, particularly those in relation to export restrictions. It is a mutual obligation on the basis that it may be hard for the supplier to justify imposing such an obligation on the customer without agreeing to it itself. Suppliers should be aware that customers may request a specific warranty that the installation and use of the software in accordance with the agreement will not put it in breach of any applicable export laws.</p></div><div><p>Export control regulations restrict the export of so-called &#8216;dual use&#8217; goods (which include software) that could have both a civilian and military use to certain blacklisted countries. One possible example involves the international licensing of any software containing encryption functionality. While export control regulations are unlikely to be triggered by the majority of commercial software licences, suppliers and customers should be aware of these provisions and cater for them particularly when licensing software internationally. It should be noted that &#8216;export&#8217; includes both physical and electronic delivery of the software.</p></div><div><p>Suppliers exporting dual use goods will need to apply for licences from the relevant authorities.</p></div><div><p>Where the circumstances are such that compliance with export laws is a material risk (for example, if the software has a military application or if it contains encryption functionality) the supplier may want to consider including an additional right to discontinue the licence, either permanently or temporarily, to the extent necessary for either party to be able to comply with the law.</p></div><div><p>For more on export restrictions generally, see Practice Note: <a normcite='0OK7_197822'>Export controls&#8212;requirement for an export licence</a>.</p></div><div><p>For alternative forms of general compliance with law wording and drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1465005'>Compliance with law and regulation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92'><p class='main_heading'>Waiver</p><div><p>No failure, delay or omission by either party in exercising any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall operate as a waiver of that right, power or remedy, nor shall it preclude or restrict any future exercise of that or any other right or remedy. No single or partial exercise of any right, power or remedy provided by law or under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall prevent any future exercise of it or the exercise of any other right, power or remedy.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemd845f169-5bce-4479-9dfb-0ce06fbb4107'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem938717f9-b71b-450e-ba97-5709a96f8c92' type='clause'/>&#8212;Waiver</p><div><p>This waiver clause seeks to prevent inadvertent waivers of legal rights. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of waiver clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_180404'>Waiver clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95'><p class='main_heading'>Assignment</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c'><div><p>No party may assign, subcontract or encumber any right or obligation under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, in whole or in part, without the other&#8217;s prior written consent&#160;<em opt-key='opt-A3E879F9'>(such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed)</em>.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem09dfb0d4-9b33-4035-8633-a3e51a057554'><div><p>Notwithstanding clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem59e96927-0e9a-43b9-8263-676fc6be976c' type='clause'/>, a party may perform any of its obligations and exercise any of its rights granted under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> through any <b>Affiliate</b>, provided that it gives the other party&#160;prior&#160;written notice including the identity of the relevant <b>Affiliate</b>. Each party acknowledges and agrees that any act or omission of its <b>Affiliate</b> in relation to that party&#8217;s rights or obligations under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be deemed to be an act or omission of that party itself.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme0b3ce23-2bd3-455c-903a-f1b96ceb4e77'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8dabc94d-ac15-4f02-b7c0-d40242fcca95' type='clause'/>&#8212;Assignment</p><div><p>This assignment clause governs the extent to which a party&#8217;s rights and obligations under an agreement may be transferred to a third party. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of assignment provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_179778'>Assignment clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3'><p class='main_heading'>Dispute resolution</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709'><div><p>If any dispute arises between the parties out of or in connection with this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, the matter shall be referred to senior representatives of each party who shall use their reasonable endeavours to resolve it.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d'><div><p>If the dispute is not resolved within <em type='text'>insert, eg 14 days</em> of the referral being made under clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/>, the parties <em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>shall</em><em alt-key='alt-AE11E615'>may</em> resolve the matter through mediation in accordance with the London Court of International Arbitration Mediation Rules.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem207d5243-cdd6-4a85-9a2c-f370d05f0d79'><div><p><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'>Either party may issue formal legal proceedings or commence arbitration at any time whether or not the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/> have been completed</em><em alt-key='alt-AE121D41'> Until the parties have completed the steps referred to in clauses <a id-ref='ukContentItem287676d9-64ed-4be7-9b51-850e2b367709' type='clause'/> and <a id-ref='ukContentItemd67baec7-3fca-401d-aded-11516d5a471d' type='clause'/>, and have failed to resolve the dispute, neither party shall commence formal legal proceedings or arbitration except that either party may at any time seek urgent interim relief</em>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemc7529c4a-efda-4fa4-9813-59759d53f266'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>&#8212;Dispute resolution</p><div><p>This dispute resolution clause requires the parties to use reasonable endeavours to resolve disputes internally before referring the matter to mediation. For alternative forms of wording and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_1462243'>Dispute resolution clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b'><p class='main_heading'>Set off</p><div><p>Each party shall pay all sums that it owes to the other party under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> without any set-off, counterclaim, deduction or withholding of any kind, save as may be required by law.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem73d7a6e5-543c-47a8-b9c4-9935df69a21a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem28512f0b-78f5-494a-b0dd-bc874e473a3b' type='clause'/>&#8212;Set off</p><div><p>This set off clause prohibits the parties from deducting sums owed to them from amounts they owe under the agreement. For alternative wording (including clauses that permit set off in certain circumstances) and analysis of the operation of set off clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_224362'>Set-off clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11'><p class='main_heading'>No partnership or agency</p><div><p>Nothing in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> constitutes, or shall be deemed to constitute, a partnership between the parties nor make any party the agent of another party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItemf62d7755-9e8c-430a-a06e-d7f12aacfde9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemaba8c02e-6c0b-4151-923b-05b297a85a11' type='clause'/>&#8212;No partnership or agency</p><div><p>This no partnership or agency clause seeks to avoid an agreement inadvertently creating an unintended legal relationship between the parties, such as one of partnership or agency. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of no partnership or agency clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_216648'>No partnership or agency</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb'><p class='main_heading'>Severance</p><div><p>If any provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or part of any provision) is or becomes illegal, invalid or unenforceable, the legality, validity and enforceability of any other provision of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall not be affected.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4659e787-1724-4de5-9ebf-98870014e54a'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemfa80d880-d84c-4e3d-ace8-ee0792ea54eb' type='clause'/>&#8212;Severance</p><div><p>This severance clause seeks to ensure that the agreement survives and continues to be valid in the event that any provision (or any part of a provision) is found to be illegal, invalid or unenforceable. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of severance clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177488'>Severance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4'><p class='main_heading'>Notices</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem1d062585-3a99-4d10-afc5-abbd060364f6'><div><p>Notices under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be in writing and sent to a party's <em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>registered office</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2310020'>address</em> as set out on the first page of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> (or to the fax number <em opt-key='opt-AFBC6EBC'>or email address</em> set out below). Notices may be given, and shall be deemed received:</p></div><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItem15522d47-7d6b-4996-9a1c-749502f514b0'><div><p>by first-class post: <em type='number'>insert, eg two</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem18ab7033-8ddb-40da-9a6c-7ffc6bdac959'><div><p>by airmail: <em type='number'>insert, eg seven</em> <b>Business Days</b> after posting;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cc'><div><p>by hand: on delivery;</p></div></div><div id='ukContentIteme3f8e767-307d-41bd-b06e-f4e1abb850cd'><div><p>by fax to <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='number'>number</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a successful transmission report<em alt-key='alt-D8D3FE50'>; and</em><em alt-key='alt-D8D3FE50'>.</em></p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem28333aef-71f4-46e4-988b-dc2e25206961'><div><p><em opt-key='opt-AB97CA98'>by email to <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em> and <em type='address'>address</em> in the case of <em type='text'>party</em>: on receipt of a <em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>delivery</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E2910021'>read</em> return email.</em></p></div></div></div></div><div id='ukContentItem7094cf10-7583-4859-8424-7db5752db994'><div><p>This clause does not apply to notices given in legal proceedings or arbitration.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem983b9cce-f1c9-497d-a80e-d580c36192c4' opt-key='opt-N66450'><div><p>A notice given under this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> is not validly served if sent by email.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem024cb088-d100-49ec-9649-d85be792d599'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem8feaf598-1dd4-456b-8dff-0ef1686156c4' type='clause'/>&#8212;Notices</p><div><p>This notices clause describes how the parties must serve notices under the agreement and when the notices are deemed to be received. For alternative clauses and detailed drafting notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177482'>Notices clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c'><p class='main_heading'>Variation</p><div><p>No variation of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> shall be valid or effective unless it is in writing, refers to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and is duly signed or executed by, or on behalf of, each party.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItema2f416fa-e0da-46bd-8262-41406ab4225b'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembde5c411-c98f-4348-a593-05ab24ca194c' type='clause'/>&#8212;Variation</p><div><p>This variation clause aims to exclude any oral variations to the agreement and to ensure that any variation agreed by the parties is clearly documented and authorised. For examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of variation provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177485'>Variation clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1'><p class='main_heading'>Further assurance</p><div><p>Each party shall at the request of the other, and at the cost of the requesting party, do all acts and execute all documents which are necessary to give full effect to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem1e7a154e-641b-4061-afa6-d5de9db6eb57'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItemf1ca0aff-4fde-4e67-9d4e-8ad9580febd1' type='clause'/>&#8212;Further assurance</p><div><p>This further assurance clause obliges a party, at the request of the other, to carry out all actions and execute all documents required to give full effect to the agreement. For Drafting Notes, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177481'>Further assurance clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad'><p class='main_heading'>Entire agreement</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemedafd15a-94f5-46e8-90bb-ef46a2c6ff63'><div><p>The parties agree that this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66047'>and <em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E172022'><em type='text'>insert name(s) of specific document(s)</em></em></em> constitutes the entire agreement between them and supersedes all previous agreements, understandings and arrangements between them, whether in writing or oral in respect of its subject matter.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem52019a26-6cfb-4b34-a07e-0c27a157c86b'><div><p>Each party acknowledges that it has not entered into this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66098'>or <em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E187023'><em type='text'>insert name(s) of specific document(s)</em></em></em> in reliance on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any representation or warranty that is not expressly set out in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> <em opt-key='opt-N66116'>or <em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'>any documents entered into pursuant to it</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E198024'><em type='text'>insert name(s) of specified document(s)</em></em></em><em opt-key='opt-N66133'>, except in the case of fraudulent misrepresentation</em>. No party shall have any claim for innocent or negligent misrepresentation on the basis of any statement in this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4b4cbc0f-e165-4e65-bc0a-fd353dbbd1df'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItembafac083-19be-4212-aaeb-14c4ac2143ad' type='clause'/>&#8212;Entire agreement</p><div><p>This entire agreement clause aims to exclude other documents or statements from forming part of the contract.&#160;For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of entire agreement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177480'>Entire agreement clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82'><p class='main_heading'>Third party rights</p><div number-type='number'><div id='ukContentItemb0431571-62fe-48ab-a86f-c3db99f9056d'><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem6f56f675-e0c8-4b54-a48a-3f81d5f80a31' type='clause'/>, no one other than a <b>party</b> to this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>,<em opt-key='opt-N65821'> their successors and permitted assignees</em> shall have any right to enforce any of its provisions.</p></div></div><div id='ukContentItem6f56f675-e0c8-4b54-a48a-3f81d5f80a31'><div><p>The <b>Affiliate</b>s of the <lnb-prec:party>Customer</lnb-prec:party> shall have the right to enforce the provisions of this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>.</p></div></div></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem8881abd3-fadb-45b5-bc63-55b35223f2c9'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem9f658ca2-4e38-48e7-89e0-7c4015274d82' type='clause'/>&#8212;Third party rights</p><div><p>This rights of third parties clause governs the enforceability by third parties of rights arising under the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of third party rights clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177484'>Rights of third parties clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5'><p class='main_heading'>Jurisdiction</p><div><p>Subject to clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem0c4ee201-76ae-4075-9ccb-7ed84bffedb3' type='clause'/>, the parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have <em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>exclusive</em><em alt-key='alt-D15E6562345'>non-exclusive</em> jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b>, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims).</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem5fceb874-fdf2-461b-82b6-dccbb645e360'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentIteme2ecbab4-e486-4b68-b19a-74013805d2d5' type='clause'/>&#8212;Jurisdiction</p><div><p>This jurisdiction clause specifies the courts that are to have jurisdiction to hear disputes that arise in relation to the agreement. For a long form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of jurisdiction clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181753'>Jurisdiction clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de'><p class='main_heading'>Governing law</p><div><p>This <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> and any dispute or claim arising out of, or in connection with, it, its subject matter or formation (including non-contractual disputes or claims) shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of England and Wales.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentItem4321f6ef-2ddf-491d-a9ce-883987f057e7'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItem7ffe2a15-0caa-44f5-a5de-4ccfd45d43de' type='clause'/>&#8212;Governing law</p><div><p>This governing law clause specifies the substantive law to be applied in interpretation of the agreement and any dispute in relation to it. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of governing law clauses, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_181565'>Governing law clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}, {PA: "TMT", id: "ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966", xml: "<lnb-prec:contentReference id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><lnb-prec:component component-id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' doc-pguid='urn:editdraft:3E2E0BE4-7288-4447-BE00-A961AF79DF7C'/></lnb-prec:contentReference>", html: "<div id='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966'><p class='main_heading'>Announcements</p><div><p>No announcement or other public disclosure concerning this <b class='document-class'>Agreement</b> or any of the matters contained in it shall be made by, or on behalf of, a party without the prior written consent of the other party (such consent not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except as required by law, any court, any governmental, regulatory or supervisory authority (including any recognised investment exchange) or any other authority of competent jurisdiction.</p></div><div class='draftingnotesection' id='ukContentIteme7458132-b568-40f1-8980-6ce5a3bdbe30'><p class='main_heading'>Clause <a id-ref='ukContentItema764281a-9944-49b1-9286-74816e21d966' type='clause'/>&#8212;Announcements</p><div><p>This announcements clause governs the disclosure of information relating to the existence and subject matter of the agreement. For a long-form clause, examples of alternative wording and analysis of the operation of announcement provisions, see Precedent: <a normcite='0OKF_177745'>Announcements clause</a>.</p></div></div></div>"}]
